ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.subtitle=Learn how to use matrix enchanting
ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.desc1=&eQuark Oddities&r completely overhauls how the Enchantment Table works.
ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.desc2=At the bottom, you can see the amount of levels required to create an &6enchantment shape&r. That will add that shape to the list on the right. Some enchantments might require you have over a specific amount of xp, even if it doesn't cost that much to actually make it. &6The more Bookshelves you have, the more shapes you can create&r.
ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.desc3=Click an enchantment out of the list, and then place it anywhere in the 5x5 grid next to it (you can right-click while holding the shape to rotate it). That will apply that enchantment to the item. &6You can add as many enchantments as you have shapes, so long as they all fit together within the grid&r.
ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.desc4=If you have multiple shapes of one enchantment, place them on top of each other to upgrade the level of that enchantment.
ftbuniversity.quarkenchant.desc5=This can be disabled in the &6Mod Options...&r menu, searching and opening "Quark" (&nnot "Quark Oddities"&r), opening Oddities, then clicking the checkmark next to "Matrix Enchanting."

ftbuniversity.exu2search.title=Legitimizing Soaryn Chests Since 2014
ftbuniversity.exu2search.subtitle=Learn about ExU2's item locator
ftbuniversity.exu2search.desc1=Extra Utilities 2 adds a keybind that lets you &bhover over any item in your inventory and hit T&r, and it will &6spawn particles in any nearby blocks that have that item&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2search.desc2=This is incredibly useful for those that haven't done very much sorting in their base yet, as you can find what specific chest has a certain item.

ftbuniversity.ironchests.title=Bigger on the Inside
ftbuniversity.ironchests.subtitle=Make an upgraded Chest
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc1=The mod &eIron Chests&r adds several tiers of Chests that have &6more storage space&r.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc2=&bCopper&r has &645&r slots.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc3=&bIron&r has &654&r slots.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc4=&bSilver&r has &672&r slots.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc5=&bGold&r has &681&r slots.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc6=&bDiamond&r, &bCrystal&r, and &bObsidian&r all have &6108&r slots. Crystal is see-through, and Obsidian is blast-proof.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc7=There are also &bChest Upgrades&r that can be used on a Chest to upgrade it, without having to break it.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.desc8=Additionally, Shulkers can also be crafted into these advanced tiers.
ftbuniversity.ironchests.task1=Chests
ftbuniversity.ironchests.task2=Chest Upgrades

ftbuniversity.yabba.title=YABBA DABBA DOO
ftbuniversity.yabba.subtitle=Make an Item Barrel
ftbuniversity.yabba.desc1=&bItem Barrels&r from the mod &eYABBA&r work fairly similarly to &eStorage Drawers&r' Storage Drawers. They can &6store a massive amount of a single item&r. Right-click an item to insert it, left-click to extract.
ftbuniversity.yabba.desc2=Item Barrels have &6lower raw storage capability&r (fully upgraded, holding 4096 stacks compared to Storage Drawers' 7168), but has &6more unique upgrades&r, and having &6better aesthetic abilities&r.
ftbuniversity.yabba.desc3=Sneak right-click an Item Barrel to open its settings. There, you can toggle if it's locked, if it requires you to sneak to see its contents, and if it should show a progress bar instead of exact amounts.
ftbuniversity.yabba.desc4=Barrels keep their contents when broken.

ftbuniversity.ibconn.title=Barrel Controller
ftbuniversity.ibconn.subtitle=Make an Item Barrel Connector
ftbuniversity.ibconn.desc1=The &bItem Barrel Connector&r provides &6access to all connected Item Barrels&r.
ftbuniversity.ibconn.desc2=This &6only works for pipes&r and the like; &cyou can't use it manually&r. It's GUI simply allows you to see the stored items and their amounts.

ftbuniversity.antibarrel.title=Unstackables
ftbuniversity.antibarrel.subtitle=Make an AntiBarrel
ftbuniversity.antibarrel.desc1=The &bAntiBarrel&r &6stores unstackable items&r, like swords and the like.
ftbuniversity.antibarrel.desc2=It is &6not limited to a single item type&r. It can store items regardless of their NBT and damage.
ftbuniversity.antibarrel.desc3=This makes it &nextremely useful for mob farms&r, so you don't have to make some complex setup to void these items.

ftbuniversity.yabtier.title=This Isn't Even My Final Form
ftbuniversity.yabtier.subtitle=Make a tier upgrade
ftbuniversity.yabtier.desc1=These tier upgrades allow you to &6store more items&r in an Item Barrel. They &6must be placed in order&r: Iron, then Gold, then Diamond. Infinite Capacity can be installed at any point, however.
ftbuniversity.yabtier.desc2=â€¢ &bIron Tier&r can store 256 stacks.
ftbuniversity.yabtier.desc3=â€¢ &bGold Tier&r can store 1024 stacks.
ftbuniversity.yabtier.desc4=â€¢ &bDiamond Tier&r can store 4096 stacks.
ftbuniversity.yabtier.desc5=â€¢ &bInfinite Capacity&r, as the name implies, can store an infinite amount.
ftbuniversity.yabtier.task=Tier upgrades

ftbuniversity.yabups.title=Function Over Form
ftbuniversity.yabups.subtitle=Make a function upgrade
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc1=These items can be added to Item Barrels of any tier to add some functionality.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc2=&bObsidian Shell&r makes Barrels &6resist explosions&r.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc3=&bRedstone Output&r adds several options to the Barrel's GUI to allow it to &6emit a redstone signal based on the amount stored&r.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc4=&bHopper&r adds options to the GUI that allow it to &6work like a Hopper&r: pulling from inventories above, pushing into inventories below, and grabbing item entities on top. All of these are configurable.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc5=&bVoid Items&r allows the Barrel to &6accept items even when full, destroying them&r.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc6=&bCollect Pickups&r allows the Barrel, when broken and in your inventory, to &6automatically collect items that you pick up&r. This is excellent for storing Cobblestone, as you can bring it with you when you go mining.
ftbuniversity.yabups.desc7=&bItem Smelting&r will attempt to &6smelt the stored item every 20 seconds&r, dropping the result in front of it.
ftbuniversity.yabups.task=Function upgrades

ftbuniversity.barham.title=Form Over Function
ftbuniversity.barham.subtitle=Make the various Barrel decorative items
ftbuniversity.barham.desc1=The &bBarrel Hammer&r allows you to &6change a Barrel's model&r.
ftbuniversity.barham.desc2=To do this, sneak right-click the Hammer, choose a model, then right-click the Barrel to apply it.
ftbuniversity.barham.desc3=Likewise, the &bBarrel Painter&r allows you to &6change a Barrel's texture&r.
ftbuniversity.barham.desc4=Again, sneak-right click the Painter, choose a block to use the texture of, then right-click the Barrel to apply it.
ftbuniversity.barham.desc5=The &bBarrel Wrench&r allows you to &6rotate Barrels&r by right-clicking them. Sneak to instantly break the Barrel.

##Progression
ftbuniversity.progression.title=Introductions

ftbuniversity.progintro.title=Welcome to Mods!
ftbuniversity.progintro.subtitle=What makes mods special
ftbuniversity.progintro.desc1=This chapter will show you what makes each mod special, and generally &6when you should start playing with them&r.
ftbuniversity.progintro.desc2=Don't do these mods one at a time! Mods work best when mixed together!
ftbuniversity.progintro.desc3=The &6Akashic Tome&r (this quest's reward) can be crafted with any other book to store them. Right-click it to choose a book for it to transform into, and punch the air with it to reset it.
ftbuniversity.progintro.desc4=Throw a transformed book to to remove it, giving it back as an item.

ftbuniversity.progfor.title=Forestry
ftbuniversity.progfor.subtitle=Nature tech
ftbuniversity.progfor.desc1=&eForestry&r is a mod that deals with farming.
ftbuniversity.progfor.desc2=Its most famous feature is bee breeding, which can make bees that generate items, from string to diamonds. (Technically the inorganic bees are from an addon, but still.)
ftbuniversity.progfor.desc3=Forestry is great for &6early game&r, since it's fairly cheap and lets you automate wood and crops quickly.

ftbuniversity.progexu2.title=Extra Utilities 2
ftbuniversity.progexu2.subtitle=Magicky tech
ftbuniversity.progexu2.desc1=As the name implies, &eExtra Utilities 2&r mostly adds &6simple utility items&r. However, it also adds its own &6unique wireless energy system&r and several machines that use RF.
ftbuniversity.progexu2.desc2=ExU2 can be started from &6pretty early on, though some items have a bit of a resource requirement&r.

ftbuniversity.progbot.title=Botania
ftbuniversity.progbot.subtitle=Botania is a mod by Vazkii
ftbuniversity.progbot.desc1=&eBotania&r calls itself a tech mod with a theme of natural magic. So while it &6looks like a magic mod&r, it &6plays like a tech mod&r.
ftbuniversity.progbot.desc2=The bulk of Botania was covered in &dFTB Academy&r, so University will only go over the more complex aspects.
ftbuniversity.progbot.desc3=Botania can be accessed pretty much &6from the beginning&r, so you can jump in as soon as you have the materials.

ftbuniversity.progic2.title=Industrial Craft 2
ftbuniversity.progic2.subtitle=Laboratory tech
ftbuniversity.progic2.desc1=Unlike most other tech mods which use RF, &eIndustrial Craft 2&r uses &6EU&r for its energy system.
ftbuniversity.progic2.desc2=Its machines start off slower than other mods', but when upgraded are by far the fastest. It has &6nearly zero cross-mod interaction&r though.
ftbuniversity.progic2.desc3=IC2 should last the entire modpack, from &6beginning to end&r.

ftbuniversity.proglog.title=Logistics Pipes
ftbuniversity.proglog.subtitle=Logical automation
ftbuniversity.proglog.desc1=&eLogistics Pipes&r is a mod that adds really &6fun and interesting pipes&r for automating your base.
ftbuniversity.proglog.desc2=Logistics Pipes is &6fairly early game&r, but requires a bit of infrastructure in the way of energy.

ftbuniversity.progie.title=Immersive Engineering
ftbuniversity.progie.subtitle=Factory-y tech
ftbuniversity.progie.desc1=&eImmersive Engineering&r is a tech mod that uses RF. What makes it stand out is that all the machines are &6multiblocks that ooze with style&r.
ftbuniversity.progie.desc2=Immersive Engineering requires a lot of Coal and Iron, but &6if you have the resources you can jump in whenever&r.

ftbuniversity.progpneu.title=PneumaticCraft: Repressurized
ftbuniversity.progpneu.subtitle=Airy tech
ftbuniversity.progpneu.desc1=&ePneumaticCraft&r is a tech mod that uses &6air pressure and heat&r instead of electrical energy.
ftbuniversity.progpneu.desc2=PneumaticCraft is best approached around &6early-midgame&r.

ftbuniversity.progthaum.title=Thaumcraft 6
ftbuniversity.progthaum.subtitle=Magitechy magic
ftbuniversity.progthaum.desc1=&eThaumcraft&r is a magic mod that has themes of &6magitech and steampunk&r. It's also &6incredibly pretty&r, with absolutely magical visuals.
ftbuniversity.progthaum.desc2=Thaumcraft can be started &6from the beginning&r of a playthrough.
ftbuniversity.progthaum.reward=Vis Crystals

ftbuniversity.progblood.title=Blood Magic: Alchemical Wizardry
ftbuniversity.progblood.subtitle=Edgy magic
ftbuniversity.progblood.desc1=&eBlood Magic&r is a mod that &6uses Life Essence&r to power &6rituals&r, &6alchemy&r, and &6spells&r.
ftbuniversity.progblood.desc2=The first steps require a fair amount of precious ores, but it can be started &6fairly early game&r. 

ftbuniversity.progeio.title=Ender IO
ftbuniversity.progeio.subtitle=&mMicrocrafty&r&7 Convenient tech
ftbuniversity.progeio.desc1=&eEnder IO&r is a tech mod that uses RF. Its most unique feature is the Conduit system, where you can have &6pipes&r for items, energy, and fluids &6traveling through the same block&r together.
ftbuniversity.progeio.desc2=Ender IO machines come in several tiers and can be upgraded to &6last the entire modpack&r.

ftbuniversity.progmek.title=Mekanism v9
ftbuniversity.progmek.subtitle=Technological Technology
ftbuniversity.progmek.desc1=&eMekanism&r is a tech mod that uses RF.
ftbuniversity.progmek.desc2=Its mid-game is fairly nice with its Factories &6capable of handling up to 9 recipes at once&r, and its endgame Fusion Reactor &6makes a astonishingly high amount of RF&r.
ftbuniversity.progmek.desc3=Mekanism has several tiers for the different stages.

ftbuniversity.prognucc.title=NuclearCraft: Overhauled
ftbuniversity.prognucc.subtitle=Nuclear Technology
ftbuniversity.prognucc.desc1=&eNuclearCraft: Overhauled&r is a tech mod that adds multiblock nuclear reactors to &6generate massive amounts of RF or EU&r. It also has plenty of machines, aside from the reactors.
ftbuniversity.prognucc.desc2=It's also &6possibly the most complex mod in existence&r, which is only barely an exaggeration.
ftbuniversity.prognucc.desc3=NuclearCraft: Overhauled is a &6fairly late-game&r mod, due to the resource cost and complexity.

ftbuniversity.progrft.title=RFTools
ftbuniversity.progrft.subtitle=Really cool tech
ftbuniversity.progrft.desc1=&eRFTools&r is a tech mod that uses RF, as the name implies. The machines it adds are &6insanely useful&r for every stage of the game.
ftbuniversity.progrft.desc2=While some of RFTools are &6fairly early&r, the majority of the mod is pretty &6late-game&r.

ftbuniversity.progae2.title=Applied Energistics 2
ftbuniversity.progae2.subtitle=Digital storage
ftbuniversity.progae2.desc1=&eApplied Energistics 2&r is a tech mod that's dedicated to making &6storage and automation&r as convenient as possible.
ftbuniversity.progae2.desc2=AE2 can be started &6around early mid-game&r.

ftbuniversity.progadvr.title=Advanced Rocketry
ftbuniversity.progadvr.subtitle=Intergalactic tech
ftbuniversity.progadvr.desc1=&eAdvanced Rocketry&r is a tech mod that's dedicated to &6space travel&r, and it's really cool.
ftbuniversity.progadvr.desc2=By itself, the mod is honestly fairly bare-bones, with everything being randomly generated. We've gone through and added custom planets and asteroids ourselves, to show what the mod is capable of.
ftbuniversity.progadvr.desc3=Rocket science isn't exactly easy, so it won't be until about &6late mid-game&r, maybe early late-game before you'll be exploring the stars.

ftbuniversity.progrftd.title=RFTools Dimensions
ftbuniversity.progrftd.subtitle=Dimension tech
ftbuniversity.progrftd.desc1=&eRFTools Dimensions&r is an addon for RFTools that allows you to &6create your own dimensions&r to your liking.
ftbuniversity.progrftd.desc2=These designer dimensions can be anything from a regular Overworld where everything is lit and monsters never spawn, to an infinite ocean made out of Hootch, to a void of spheres made out of Blocks of Diamond.
ftbuniversity.progrftd.desc3=RFTools Dimension is &6&lEXTREMELY&r&6 late-game&r, as it requires a massive amount of RF for a dimension to run.

ftbuniversity.progenv.title=Environmental Tech
ftbuniversity.progenv.subtitle=Environmental tech
ftbuniversity.progenv.desc1=&eEnvironmental Tech&r is a tech mod that &6generates resources&r from RF, generate massive amounts of RF from the sun, and give yourself &6beacon-like effects anywhere&r in the world.
ftbuniversity.progenv.desc2=Environmental Tech is a &6fairly late-game mod&6, though you can &6make the early tiers around late mid-game&r.

ftbuniversity.progxnet.title=XNet
ftbuniversity.progxnet.subtitle=Digital automation
ftbuniversity.progxnet.desc1=&eXNet&r is dedicated to &6automation&r, transferring items, liquids, energy, and information. XNet is also &6amazingly performant&r, causing little to no lag.
ftbuniversity.progxnet.desc2=XNet requires RF but is rather cheap, so it can be used fairly early.

ftbuniversity.progintd.title=Integrated Dynamics
ftbuniversity.progintd.subtitle=Tree... crystal automation?
ftbuniversity.progintd.desc1=&eIntegrated Dynamics&r is an &6incredibly complex&r and powerful mod, dedicated to &6automation&r.
ftbuniversity.progintd.desc2=Integrated Dynamics' most important feature is the ability to &6read information about the world&r (or things within it), and then &6do things based on that&r.

##Automation
ftbuniversity.automationchap.title=Automation

###Logistics Pipes
###Many thanks to reddit user /u/suchtie for their guide here: https://www.reddit.com/r/feedthebeast/comments/c97545/guide_a_short_introduction_to_logistics_pipes_for/
ftbuniversity.logisticspipeschap.title=Logistics Pipes

ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.title=
ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.subtitle=Make Unrouted Transport Pipes
ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.desc1=&bUnrouted Transport Pipes&r are the most basic pipe available. They only serve to connect other pipes.
ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.desc2=If items try to pass through an Unrouted Transport Pipe that splits into multiple paths, the item will randomly choose a direction.
ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.desc3=All pipes that have any error will glow &cred&r.
ftbuniversity.unroutedpipes.desc4=Logistics Pipes uses the MCMultiPart API, which means they can &6share a blockspace with Bits&r.

ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.title=Gotta Go Fast
ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.subtitle=Make Highspeed Tubes
ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.desc1=&bHighspeed Tubes&r are much, &omuch&r faster than regular pipes, and should to connect regular pipes at long distances.
ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.desc2=&bHighspeed Speedup Tubes&r are required at both ends. They will speed items up when coming from the near side, and slow down when coming from the far side.
ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.desc3=&bHighspeed Line Tubes&r should be used for straight lines, and cannot curve. The other tube names should be mostly self-explanatory.
ftbuniversity.highspeedpipes.task3=Any non-straight Highspeed Tube

ftbuniversity.logpipewrenches.title=Pipe Gooey
ftbuniversity.logpipewrenches.subtitle=Make something that can manage pipes
ftbuniversity.logpipewrenches.task=Items that can open pipe GUIs
ftbuniversity.logpipewrenches.desc=Certain pipes have GUIs that can't be accessed normally. You can use either a &bWrench&r, if you have one, or a &bPipe Manager&r.

ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.subtitle=Make Basic Logistics Pipes
ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.desc1=&bBasic Logistics Pipes&r are one step above Unrouted Transport Pipes. They can connect to inventories and certain other blocks. 
ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.desc2=Open the Basic Logistics Pipe's GUI (with a Wrench or Pipe Manager) to set what items are allowed to enter the inventory it is placed on. You can also toggle &6Default route&r, which allows all items through.
ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.desc3=&cIf the inventory is full, items will be dropped out of the pipe into the world.&r
ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.desc4=Basic Logistics Pipes should be used where Unrouted Transport Pipes &6intersect&r, items will move in the correct path intelligently.
ftbuniversity.basiclogpipes.desc5=All intelligent pipes &6require energy to function&r.

ftbuniversity.logpowerjunction.title=
ftbuniversity.logpowerjunction.subtitle=Make a Logistics Power Junction
ftbuniversity.logpowerjunction.desc1=Logistics Pipe networks require power to function. Place down a &bLogistics Power Junction&r and connect it to the network with a Basic Logistics Pipe, then &6provide it with RF or EU&r.
ftbuniversity.logpowerjunction.desc2=You may need to place some pipes to update the network.

ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.title=Log Prog Com for Short
ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.subtitle=Make a Logistics Program Compiler
ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.desc1=Most Logistics Pipes require programs in their crafting recipes. These programs are made in the &bLogistics Program Compiler&r. Place one down and connect it to the LP network with a Basic Logistics Pipe.
ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.desc2=Place a &bLogistics Disk&r in the upper left slot and a &bLogistics Programmer&r in the upper right.
ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.desc3=On the left of the GUI, click one of the options and click &6Unlock&r. This will take some time and energy to unlock that tier of program.
ftbuniversity.logprogcomp.desc4=After that tier has been unlocked, you can pick a program of that tier to &6Compile&r on the right. After it's been compiled, you can &6Flash&r it onto that the Logistics Programmer to use it in crafting recipes. The Programmer is reusable, though you can only have one program flashed on it at a time.

####Routed Pipes
ftbuniversity.routedpipes.title=We are Routed, Fall Back!
ftbuniversity.routedpipes.subtitle=Learn what routed pipes are
ftbuniversity.routedpipes.desc1=Every pipe that isn't Unrouted is, by definition, routed. 
ftbuniversity.routedpipes.desc2=Routed pipes are the only pipes that connect to inventories and other special blocks, and are also the only pipes that can accept upgrades.

ftbuniversity.logprovider.title=Input
ftbuniversity.logprovider.subtitle=Make a Provider Logistics Pipe
ftbuniversity.logprovider.desc1=The &bProvider Logistics Pipe&r will make the system treat its inventory as a source, &6allowing other pipes to pull from it&r. This can be a chest, machine, or even an ME Interface or Drawer Controller!
ftbuniversity.logprovider.desc2=Open the Provider Logistics Pipe's GUI to set a blacklist or whitelist. You can also set it to keep the &6first and/or last stacks&r of the inventory, keep &61 item per stack&r, or keep &61 item per item type&r. 

ftbuniversity.logsupplier.title=Output
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.subtitle=Make a Supplier Logistics Pipe
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc1=The &bSupplier Logistics Pipe&r will attempt to pull items into the inventory it is connected to from any source within the system.
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc2=Open the Supplier Logistics Pipe's GUI to set a list of up to 9 items to keep stocked from Provider Pipes/Modules. If you place a stack of 32, it will try to keep it at 32 of that item in the inventory.
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc3=â€¢ If it is set to &6Bulk 50&r, it will only retrieve more when the inventory is at 50%% of the specified amount.
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc4=â€¢ &6Bulk 100&r is &nSUPPOSED&r to only refill when there's no remaining items, but it's bugged and works like Partial mode.
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc5=â€¢ &6Infinite&r will make it pull regardless of how much is already in the inventory.
ftbuniversity.logsupplier.desc6=â€¢ &6Partial&r will pull when any amount is removed.

ftbuniversity.logrequest.title=Who Needs Digital Storage?
ftbuniversity.logrequest.subtitle=Make a Request Logistics Pipe
ftbuniversity.logrequest.desc1=The &bRequest Logistics Pipe&r will allow you to manually request any item from sources within the system. If the Pipe is connected to an inventory, the requested items will enter it. Otherwise, the items will be spit out into the world.
ftbuniversity.logrequest.desc2=You can open the Pipe's GUI with just your hands.

ftbuniversity.logordreq.subtitle=Make a Remote Orderer Logistics Pipe
ftbuniversity.logordreq.desc1=The &bRemote Orderer&r can be connected to a &bRemote Orderer Logistics Pipe&r by sneak right-clicking.
ftbuniversity.logordreq.desc2=Then, you can right-click the connected Remote Orderer, you can &6use it like a Request Logistics Pipe&r, and the items will be sent to the connected inventory.
ftbuniversity.logordreq.desc3=If you connect it to an Ender Chest, you can request items from your base from anywhere and take them out using an Ender Pouch.

ftbuniversity.logfire.subtitle=Make a Logistics Firewall Pipe
ftbuniversity.logfire.desc1=You can open the &bLogistics Firewall Pipe&r's GUI to restrict specific connections from passing through it.
ftbuniversity.logfire.desc2=You can set a blacklist/whitelist of 36 items, as well as toggling Providing, Crafting, and Sorting Logistics Pipes, as well as whether power flows through it.

ftbuniversity.loginvsyscon.subtitle=Make a Logistics Inventory System Connector
ftbuniversity.loginvsyscon.desc1=You can use a pair of &bLogistics Inventory System Connectors&r to wirelessly connect separate pipe systems together through the inventories they are placed on.
ftbuniversity.loginvsyscon.desc2=Open the pipe's GUI and click &6Change&r at the top to set the channel. Click &6Add&r to create a channel, then click the channel and then &6Select&r to connect to it. All systems on the same channel will be connected.
ftbuniversity.loginvsyscon.desc3=If an item on one end tries to pass through to the other end, it will be sent to the inventory the pipe is placed on. You should use some non-Logistics Pipes method to move items from that inventory to the inventory the connected pipe is placed on.
ftbuniversity.loginvsyscon.desc4=An &6Ender Chest&r is the most simplest way to connect them.

ftbuniversity.craftlogi.title=Simple Item Autocrafting
ftbuniversity.craftlogi.subtitle=Make a Logistics Crafting setup
ftbuniversity.craftlogi.desc1=The &bCrafting Logistics Pipe&r can be placed on a block and be set a recipe, and &6the output item will be show up in Request Pipes/Tables&r.
ftbuniversity.craftlogi.desc2=You can connect it to a &bLogistics Crafting Table&r, then set the recipe inside there. Then, open the Pipe's GUI and click &6Import&r to automatically set the recipe there. You can then request the resulting item and the ingredients will be sent to the Table, and then the item will be sent to you.
ftbuniversity.craftlogi.desc3=Nested recipes work; if you have a recipe for Logsâ†’Planks, and Planksâ†’Chests, you can make Chests from Logs. Any excess items will either jam or be sent back into the system, as if they were just added.
ftbuniversity.craftlogi.desc4=If the machine it's placed on has separate input and output sides, &6see the Satellite Logistics Pipe quest&r.

ftbuniversity.craftlogi2.title=The More You Know
ftbuniversity.craftlogi2.subtitle=The other quest ran out of room, so...
ftbuniversity.craftlogi2.desc1=Since you can only have one crafting recipe per pipe/table, you will likely end up with a wall of them. Best to dedicate the space now. If you have multiple recipes that give the same item, it will try using the &6highest priority one first&r.
ftbuniversity.craftlogi2.desc2=You can connect it to a Furnace and have the recipe be Sand input, Glass output, and when you request Glass it will send the Sand to the Furnace to be smelted, then pull

ftbuniversity.fuzcraftlog.subtitle=Make a Logistics Fuzzy Crafting Table
ftbuniversity.fuzcraftlog.desc1=The &bLogistics Fuzzy Crafting Table&r allows you to craft items using non-specific ingredients. For instance, making Sticks out of any type of Planks.
ftbuniversity.fuzcraftlog.desc2=&6Hover over the ingredients&r to toggle whether or not it should use the &bore dictionary&r, &bignore damage&r, &bignore NBT&r, and/or... &owhatever &bore prefix&r is.
ftbuniversity.fuzcraftlog.desc3=The Crafting Logistics Pipe needs to have a &6Fuzzy Upgrade&r for it to actually send those items to the Table.

ftbuniversity.logcraftsign.subtitle=Make a Crafting Sign Creator
ftbuniversity.logcraftsign.desc1=You can use the &bCrafting Sign Creator&r on any side of a Crafting Logistics Pipe to place a sign on it, which will &6display which item it crafts&r.
ftbuniversity.logcraftsign.desc2=It can place 250 signs. You can use it on an existing sign to remove it, adding one back to the Creator.

ftbuniversity.satlog.subtitle=Make a Satellite Logistics Pipe
ftbuniversity.satlog.desc1=The Crafting Logistics Pipe must be placed on the side of the machine that it can pull the finished item from. If that side cannot also &oaccept&r items, place a &bSatellite Logistics Pipe&r where it can.
ftbuniversity.satlog.desc2=Open its GUI to give it a name, and then in the Crafting Pipe you can click &6Select&r and then choose a Satellite Pipe on the same system to send the highlighted items there.
ftbuniversity.satlog.desc3=The &6Advanced Satellite Upgrade&r can allow you to set all 9 slots to go to Satellite Pipes. You can also set them to to go to separate Satellite Pipes, if you wish.

ftbuniversity.logsys.

ftbuniversity.logreqtable.title=This Quest Has a Long Name so It Has Room for All the Text
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.subtitle=Make a Logistics Request Table
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc1=The &bLogistics Request Table&r can request and store items, and has a built-in crafting table.
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc2=You can set a crafting recipe then click one of the [+] buttons to request the items required for it.
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc3=You can insert a Logistics Disk into the black-outlined slot, then click the &6Disk&r button at the bottom right. There, you can create macros (item sets) to request all at once.
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc4=Click &6Add/Edit&r to create a macro. It will show all the items currently available, and you can click from them to add them to the macro. Left-click to increase the amount given by one, right-click to decrease by one.
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc5=Name and save the macro, then it'll be added to the Disk's macro list. There you can select macros from the list and click &6Request&r to request all the items in the macro.
ftbuniversity.logreqtable.desc6=Items that are placed into the &6Sort&r slot will be sent back into the system to be sorted.

####Modules
ftbuniversity.logchass1.title=Modular Logistics Pipes
ftbuniversity.logchass1.subtitle=Make a Logistics Chassis Mk1
ftbuniversity.logchass1.desc1=&bLogistics Chassis&r can hold &bModules&r, which can serve the same function as certain Logistics Pipes. Open the Chassis' GUI to insert a Module.
ftbuniversity.logchass1.desc2=Not all Modules have a Pipe equivalent, and not all Pipes have a Module equivalent.
ftbuniversity.logchass1.desc3=The &bLogistics Chassis Mk1&r can hold &6one Module&r.
ftbuniversity.logchass1.desc4=Chassis are routed pipes, the quest's just over here for symmetry ;)

ftbuniversity.logchass2.subtitle=Make a Logistics Chassis Mk2
ftbuniversity.logchass2.desc=The &bLogistics Chassis Mk2&r can hold &6two Modules&r.

ftbuniversity.logchass3.subtitle=Make a Logistics Chassis Mk3
ftbuniversity.logchass3.desc=The &bLogistics Chassis Mk3&r can hold &6three Modules&r.

ftbuniversity.logchass4.subtitle=Make a Logistics Chassis Mk4
ftbuniversity.logchass4.desc=The &bLogistics Chassis Mk4&r can hold &6four Modules&r.

ftbuniversity.itemsinkmodule.title=Fill by Item
ftbuniversity.itemsinkmodule.subtitle=Make an ItemSink Module
ftbuniversity.itemsinkmodule.desc1=The &bItemSink Module&r is the Module equivalent of the Basic Logistics Pipe. However, if its inventory is full, items will not even try to enter, and thus &6won't be spit out into the world&r.
ftbuniversity.itemsinkmodule.desc2=Click the [!] next to the installed Module to open its GUI to set a &6whitelist of up to 9 items&r, or enable it as a default route.

ftbuniversity.modpolysink.title=Fill by Mod
ftbuniversity.modpolysink.subtitle=Make a Mod Based ItemSink Module
ftbuniversity.modpolysink.desc1=The &bMod Based ItemSink Module&r's whitelist works based on the &6mod the item is from&r, rather than the specific item itself.
ftbuniversity.modpolysink.desc2=Open its GUI then add an item to the top slot. Click &6Add&r to add that item's mod to the whitelist. Similarly, click a mod from the list and click &6Remove&r to remove it.

ftbuniversity.oredictsink.title=Fill by Item Type
ftbuniversity.oredictsink.subtitle=Make an OreDict ItemSink Module
ftbuniversity.oredictsink.desc1=The &bOreDict ItemSink Module&r's whitelist works based on the &6ore dictionary&r, rather than specific items.
ftbuniversity.oredictsink.desc2=Open its GUI then add an item to the top slot, and the item's ore dictionary name will appear next to it. You can use the buttons to scroll if there are too many to fit.
ftbuniversity.oredictsink.desc3=Click a name off the top list to add it to the whitelist. Click a name off the whitelist on the bottom to remove it.

ftbuniversity.polysink.title=POLYMORPHIC SENTIENT &mROCKS&r PIPES!
ftbuniversity.polysink.subtitle=Make a Polymorphic ItemSink Module
ftbuniversity.polysink.desc=The &bPolymorphic ItemSink Module&r works like a regular ItemSink Module, except it only accepts items that are already in the inventory.

ftbuniversity.tabsup.title=Green is Not a Creative Color
ftbuniversity.tabsup.subtitle=Make a Creative Tab Based ItemSink Module
ftbuniversity.tabsup.desc1=The &bCreative Tab Based ItemSink Module&r's whitelist works based on the creative mode tab the item is in, rather than the specific item itself.
ftbuniversity.tabsup.desc2=Open its GUI then add an item to the top slot. Click &6Add&r to add that item's creative tab to the whitelist. Similarly, click a creative tab from the list and click &6Remove&r to remove it.
ftbuniversity.tabsup.desc3=This is useful since you could make an inventory that automatically fills up with building blocks, since there's a creative tab for those.

ftbuniversity.provmod.subtitle=Make a Provider Module
ftbuniversity.provmod.desc1=The &bProvider Module&r is the Module equivalent of the Provider Logistics Pipe.
ftbuniversity.provmod.desc2=It will make the system treat its inventory as a source, &6allowing other pipes to pull from it&r. This can be a chest, machine, or even an ME Interface or Drawer Controller!
ftbuniversity.provmod.desc3=Open the Provider Module's GUI to set a blacklist or whitelist. You can also set it to keep the &6first and/or last stacks&r of the inventory, keep &61 item per stack&r, or keep &61 item per item type&r. 

ftbuniversity.terminus.title=Overflow
ftbuniversity.terminus.subtitle=Make a Terminus Module
ftbuniversity.terminus.desc1=The &bTerminus Module&r will &6catch items that have nowhere else to go&r, not including default routes. It has a whitelist in its GUI to choose which items will be sent there as overflow.
ftbuniversity.terminus.desc2=If you have a Drawer full of Cobblestone connected to an ItemSink Module or a Basic Logistics Pipe, the Cobblestone will have nowhere to go, clogging the input chest or popping out into the world.
ftbuniversity.terminus.desc3=However, if you have a Terminus Module with Cobblestone in its whitelist, the Cobblestone will move there instead. &6It's best to have a Trash Can or something similar here, so the overflow doesn't overflow.&r

ftbuniversity.passsup.subtitle=Make a Passive Supplier Module
ftbuniversity.passsup.desc1=The &bPassive Supplier Module&r works somewhat similarly to the ItemSink Module, with some extra options. &6It will not actively request items, but will allow items to enter it based on its whitelist&r.
ftbuniversity.passsup.desc2=The Passive Supplier Module will &6try to keep the specific amount of each item&r in the whitelist. If you click half a stack of an item into it, it will stop requesting once half a stack of that item is in the inventory.
ftbuniversity.passsup.desc3=You can also left/right-click the whitelist entry with the item to decrease/increase the amount by 1.

ftbuniversity.actsup.subtitle=Make an Active Supplier Module
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc1=The &bActive Supplier Module&r is the module equivalent of the Supplier Logistics Pipe.
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc2=Open the Active Supply Module's GUI to set a list of up to 9 items to keep stocked from Provider Pipes/Modules. If you place a stack of 32, it will try to keep it at 32 of that item in the inventory.
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc3=â€¢ If it is set to &6Bulk 50&r, it will only retrieve more when the inventory is at 50%% of the specified amount.
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc4=â€¢ &6Bulk 100&r is &nSUPPOSED&r to only refill when there's no remaining items, but it's bugged and works like Partial mode.
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc5=â€¢ &6Infinite&r will make it pull regardless of how much is already in the inventory.
ftbuniversity.actsup.desc6=â€¢ &6Partial&r will pull when any amount is removed.

ftbuniversity.extractmodule.subtitle=Make an Extractor Module
ftbuniversity.extractmodule.desc1=The &bExtract Module&r extracts items out of the inventory its on and &6sends them to any valid destination&r.
ftbuniversity.extractmodule.desc2=You can set it to extract items from any side of the block it's connected to, not only the side it's on.

ftbuniversity.advextractmod.subtitle=Make an Advanced Extractor Module
ftbuniversity.advextractmod.desc1=The &bAdvanced Extractor Module&r works like the Extract Module, except it has a &69-slot whitelist/blacklist&r.
ftbuniversity.advextractmod.desc2=The &6Sneaky&r button allows you to choose which side of the inventory to extract from, instead of only the side it's on.

ftbuniversity.quicksort.subtitle=Make a QuickSort Module
ftbuniversity.quicksort.desc1=The &bQuickSort Module&r works like an Extractor Module, except it only sends items that have a non-default destination.
ftbuniversity.quicksort.desc2=That means you can dump everything into the inventory it's on, and &6only items that have a set destination will be extracted&r.

ftbuniversity.enchsink.subtitle=Make an Enchantment Sink Module
ftbuniversity.enchsink.desc1=The &bEnchantment Sink Module&r works like an ItemSink Module, except for &6enchanted items&r.
ftbuniversity.enchsink.desc2=Any enchanted item (&naside from books&r) pulled from an Extractor Module will go to the Enchantment Sink Module.

ftbuniversity.enchsink2.subtitle=Make an Enchantment Sink Module Mk2
ftbuniversity.enchsink2.desc1=The &bEnchantment Sink Module Mk2&r is an upgrade to the Enchantment Sink Module.
ftbuniversity.enchsink2.desc2=The Mk2 has an &6item whitelist&r, so you can have one destination that fills up with enchanted Iron Pickaxes, and another with enchanted Gold Swords, etc.

####Upgrades

ftbuniversity.logpipecont.subtitle=Make a Pipe Controller
ftbuniversity.logpipecont.desc=The &bPipe Controller&r allows you to see a pipe's statistics, upgrades, Security Cards, and &kfix this later&r.

ftbuniversity.logupgs.title=Upgrades
ftbuniversity.logupgs.subtitle=Learn how Upgrades work
ftbuniversity.logupgs.desc1=&6Upgrades&r enhance pipes in certain ways, depending on which upgrade you install.
ftbuniversity.logupgs.desc2=Right-click a routed pipe with a &bPipe Controller&r, then install up to 9 upgrades in the second slot.

ftbuniversity.logmodupg.subtitle=Make a Module Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logmodupg.desc1=The &bModule Upgrade&r is installed to a Chassis to allow the Modules to be upgraded.
ftbuniversity.logmodupg.desc2=When the Module Upgrade is installed, the &6Module menu will have two upgrade slots per Module&r.

ftbuniversity.actspedupg.subtitle=Make an Action Speed Upgrade
ftbuniversity.actspedupg.desc1=The &bAction Speed Upgrade&r can be installed onto Extractor Modules to &6make them work more often&r.
ftbuniversity.actspedupg.desc2=The more you install, the more often it works. You can have up to 16 per slot.

ftbuniversity.itmspedupg.title=Gotta Go Fast, but Not Too Fast
ftbuniversity.itmspedupg.subtitle=Make an Item Speed Upgrade
ftbuniversity.itmspedupg.desc1=The &bItem Speed Upgrade&r speeds up items that pass through it.
ftbuniversity.itmspedupg.desc2=They can be installed on any routed pipe. A single upgrade doesn't do much, but you can install up to 16 in a single slot, and there's 9 slots.

ftbuniversity.itmextupg.subtitle=Make an Item Extraction Upgrade
ftbuniversity.itmextupg.desc1=The &bItem Extraction Upgrade&r can be installed onto Extractor Modules to &6make them extract more items at a time&r.
ftbuniversity.itmextupg.desc2=One upgrade will make it extract 8 items at a time, and two will &ksee mod author, bugged&r.

ftbuniversity.itmstkupg.subtitle=Make an ItemStack Extraction Upgrade
ftbuniversity.itmstkupg.desc1=

ftbuniversity.logopq.title=What's Inside? Who knows!
ftbuniversity.logopq.subtitle=Make an Opaque Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logopq.desc1=The &bOpaque Upgrade&r will disable rendering for any item that's passing through it.
ftbuniversity.logopq.desc2=The item will become visible again immediately after it's not in that specific pipe anymore, so... it's not exceedingly useful unless you make the entire line out of routed pipes and install the upgrade onto all of them.

ftbuniversity.logfuzzy.title=Fuzzy, not Hairy
ftbuniversity.logfuzzy.subtitle=Make a Fuzzy Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logfuzzy.desc1=The &bFuzzy Upgrade&r will allow certain pipes/modules to &6ignore metadata and/or NBT&r.
ftbuniversity.logfuzzy.desc2=Hover over the item slot in the whitelist to show the options for what to ignore.
ftbuniversity.logfuzzy.desc3=This can be used to keep all Wool colors or all Enchanted Books in the same inventory.

ftbuniversity.logdisc.title=&mSandstone Pipe&r
ftbuniversity.logdisc.subtitle=Make a Disconnection Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logdisc.desc1=The &bDisconnection Upgrade&r allows you to prevent routed pipes from connecting on certain sides.
ftbuniversity.logdisc.desc2=Use the Pipe Controller and open the Upgrades tab, then click the [!] under the installed upgrade to open its GUI.
ftbuniversity.logdisc.desc3=Left-click and drag to rotate your perspective. Right-click on a side to toggle whether or not it can connect.

ftbuniversity.logsneak.title=Why is it called that?
ftbuniversity.logsneak.subtitle=Make a Sneaky Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logsneak.desc1=&bSneaky Upgrades&r allow you to make pipes act as if they were connected to a different side of a block than they are.
ftbuniversity.logsneak.desc2=Use the Pipe Controller and open the Upgrades tab, then click the [!] under the installed upgrade to open its GUI.
ftbuniversity.logsneak.desc3=Left-click and drag to rotate your perspective. Right-click on the side of the block to choose to pull from that side.

ftbuniversity.logsneakcomb.title=The More the Merrier
ftbuniversity.logsneakcomb.subtitle=Make a Sneaky Combination Upgrade
ftbuniversity.logsneakcomb.desc=The &bSneaky Combination Upgrade&r allows you to install up to 9 Sneaky Upgrades at once.

###XNet
ftbuniversity.xnetchapter.title=XNet

ftbuniversity.xnetbook.subtitle=Make the XNet Manual
ftbuniversity.xnetbook.desc=The &bXNet Manual&r is &eXNet&r's guidebook, and has information on pretty much everything from the mod.

ftbuniversity.xncontroller.subtitle=Make a Controller
ftbuniversity.xncontroller.desc1=A &6network&r is defined by the machines connected to the Controller via Cables and Connectors.
ftbuniversity.xncontroller.desc2=Every network requires exactly one &bController&r, no more, no less.
ftbuniversity.xncontroller.desc3=The Controller is where the input/output of Connectors on the network are set, and is also where &6power&r is input.

ftbuniversity.xnconnector.title=Connectors
ftbuniversity.xnconnector.subtitle=Make a Connector
ftbuniversity.xnconnector.desc1=&bConnectors&r &6connect adjacent blocks to the network&r.
ftbuniversity.xnconnector.desc2=A Connector must be placed &6on the Controller&r, and then another placed on any block you want to &6interface with&r.
ftbuniversity.xnconnector.desc3=Connectors come in four colors, which only connect to Network Cables of the same color.
ftbuniversity.xnconnector.desc4=Connectors have a GUI that allows you to &6toggle connections to each side&r. That way, if it's touching two machines, you can set it to only connect to one. You can also &6rename it&r there.

ftbuniversity.advconnectors.title=Advanced Connectors
ftbuniversity.advconnectors.subtitle=Make an Advanced Connector
ftbuniversity.advconnectors.desc1=&bAvanced Connectors&r work like regular Connectors, but are generally faster and more powerful.
ftbuniversity.advconnectors.desc2=Regular Connectors can only insert/extract from the side they are placed on, but Advanced Connectors can &6IO from any side of the block&r they're on.
ftbuniversity.advconnectors.desc3=Regular Connectors, at maximum, can move &610,000RF/t&r and &61,000mB/t&r.
ftbuniversity.advconnectors.desc4=Advanced Connectors, at maximum, can move &6100,000RF/t&r and &65,000mB/t&r.

ftbuniversity.xnfacade.subtitle=Make a Facade
ftbuniversity.xnfacade.desc=Click a &bFacade&r on a block, then on a Cable/Connector to make it look like that block.

ftbuniversity.xncables.title=Network Cables
ftbuniversity.xncables.subtitle=Make a Network Cable
ftbuniversity.xncables.desc1=&bNetwork Cables&r are used to &6connect Connectors&r, and do nothing else.
ftbuniversity.xncables.desc2=They come in &6four colors&r, which only connect to other Cables/Connectors of the same color.
ftbuniversity.xncables.desc3=&6Sneaking while holding a Cable&r or Connector will show other Cables/Connectors placed in the world, even from behind walls.

ftbuniversity.xnet1.title=Using the Network
ftbuniversity.xnet1.subtitle=Learn how to use the Controller
ftbuniversity.xnet1.desc1=Once you've used Connectors and Network Cables to connect the Controller to certain blocks, you can begin &6using the network&r.
ftbuniversity.xnet1.desc2=In the Controller, there are &68 channels&r for each block on the network. Items, energy, etc can only &6move within a channel&r. Additionally, &6each channel can only transfer one thing&r.
ftbuniversity.xnet1.desc3=At the top left, click on a channel number and choose what it will move. &6xnet.energy&r, &6xnet.item&r, and &6xnet.fluid&r should be fairly self-evident; the others will be explained elsewhere.

ftbuniversity.xnet2.title=Automating a Smelter
ftbuniversity.xnet2.subtitle=Go through an example automation setup
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc1=This quest will walk you through automating an Alloy Smelter, though the general idea can be transferred to any machines, really.
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc2=For now, set the first channel to &nxnet.energy&r and click &6Create&r. Give it a name if you want, then &6click on the first box to the right of the Generator&r on the left.
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc3=On the right, click &6Create&r. Click &6Ins&r so it swaps to &6Ext&r, so it pulls energy out of the Generator and into the channel. You can set the rate it pulls (yes, the tooltip is bugged, see the Advanced Connectors quest for the max rates), as well as the &6minimum RF&r in the generator before it starts extracting (which could be useful if you connect it to storage instead, so it stops if it goes below a certain amount).
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc4=Then, on the Alloy Smelter, &6create a new connection on the same channel&r. Keep is as &6Ins&r, and it will start filling the Smelter with energy from the generator. You can set the rate and max RF here as well.
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc5=Edit the &6second channel&r and set it to &nxnet.item&r. Extract items from the Chest and insert them into the Smelter. Item connections can have a &6blacklist/whitelist&r set, with NBT and all that good stuff. Just hover over all the buttons, the tooltips should explain.
ftbuniversity.xnet2.desc6=On the &6third channel&r, also set to &nxnet.item&r, extract items from the Smelter and insert them into the Chest.

ftbuniversity.xnet3.title=Distribution Modes
ftbuniversity.xnet3.subtitle=Learn about Distribution Modes
ftbuniversity.xnet3.desc1=On item channels, you can toggle them between &6Priority&r and &6Roundrobin&r modes.
ftbuniversity.xnet3.desc2=In &6Priority&r mode, items extracted will try to go to the destination with the &6highest priority first&r.
ftbuniversity.xnet3.desc3=In &6Roundrobin&r mode, it will try to &6equally distribute&r the items over all destinations.
ftbuniversity.xnet3.desc4=Fluid channels have the same, though Roundrobin is called &6Distribute&r instead.

ftbuniversity.xnlogic.title=Logic
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.subtitle=Learn how to use Logic channels
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc1=&bxnet.logic&r channels can have &6sensors&r to measure things (redstone signal strength, item count, etc).
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc2=There are &65 sensor modes&r and &66 operators&r. Set the amount to compare with, and optionally the item/fluid to count.
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc3=Set the &6output color&r. Every other connection of any type &6can be set to only work when a color is being enabled&r.
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc4=So, you could have a sensor checking &6if the amount of RF in your storage is low&r, it &6outputs Red&r.
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc5=A connector that moves fuel to a generator could then be &6set to only work if Red is eanbled&r, so it only works when the RF is low.
ftbuniversity.xnlogic.desc6=Connectors can depend on up to 4 colors.

# Hey, fun fact
# Literally no tutorials exist that explain Routers that are from 1.12.2, so I spent about half an hour with a building headache
# trying to figure out what I was doing wrong, until I noticed that ALL THE TUTORIALS ARE FROM 2017

ftbuniversity.xnrouter.title=Routing
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.subtitle=Make a Router
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc1=A single network is limited to only 8 channels. This is good enough for most purposes, but not for everything.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc2=the &bRouter&r allows you to connect multiple networks to each other. Connect a Router to both networks.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc3=On the first network, &6create a named channel&r that, say, pulls items from a chest.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc4=On the second network, &6create another named channel&r that &oinserts items into&r a chest.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc5=In the Router, there is a list of all the channels in both networks. Find the two you want to connect, and &6give them the same name&r.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter.desc6=Channels in different networks but connected with a Router will be &6treated as a single Channel&r. In this example, items will move from the chest in the first network to the chest in the second.

ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.title=Multiple Routers
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.subtitle=Learn how to use multiple Routers
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.desc1=A single Router can connect up to 6 networks, but even that might not be enough.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.desc2=Connect a Router to a single network, then use &bRouting Connectors&r and &bRouting Network Cable&r to connect it to another Router that's on a different network.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.desc3=In any Router on a network with a named channel, &6publish it&r by giving it a Router-name. On any other Router connected via Routing Connectors, that channel will be shown in as a &6Remote Channel&r.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.desc4=Just as you would with a single Router, give a Router-name to a channel on a different network that matches an existing Router-name of a Remote Channel. This will connect the two.
ftbuniversity.xnrouter2.desc5=You can only have &632 published channels&r on a routing network. All networks on the routing network must be connected via the same Cables; if networks are connected like A-B-C, B can see A and C, but A cannot see B.

ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.subtitle=Make a Wireless Router setup
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.desc1=The &bWireless Router&r can be connected to a Router network (using a Routing Connector etc), and then other Wireless Routers within range will have access to Remote Channels on the network.
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.desc2=The Wireless Router needs RF, but also must have an Antenna placed on top. Directly above, place an &bAntenna Base&r, then place up to 2 &bAntennas&r.
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.desc3=Having just one Antenna gives a range of &6100 blocks&r, costing &620RF/t per channel&r; having 2 Antennas gives a range of &6500 blocks&r, costing &650RF/t per channel&r.
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.desc4=You can also place an &bAntenna Dish&r on the Base instead, giving it &6infinite range&r across dimensions, though it would cost &6500RF/t per channel&r.
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.desc5=By default, Wireless Routers only connect to other Wireless Routers &6owned by the same player&r. In their GUI, you can set them to Public to allow anyone to access them.
ftbuniversity.wirelessrouter.task=Antenna parts

###Integrated Dynamics
ftbuniversity.intdynchap.title=Integrated Dynamics

ftbuniversity.stringetc.title=What Do These Words &oMEAN&r?!
ftbuniversity.stringetc.subtitle=Learn what a string, integer, double, etc are
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc1=A &bString&r is just &6any text&r, including letters, numbers, and punctuation.
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc2=An &bInteger&r is a &6whole number&r, positive or negative.
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc3=A &bDouble&r is a &6number with a decimal point&r, like 5.0 instead of 5.
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc4=A &bLong&r is a &6whole number&r; longs can handle much larger values than integers.
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc5=A &bBoolean&r is a simple &6true/false&r.
ftbuniversity.stringetc.desc6=A &bList&r is a &6group of values&r, which can be of any other type, though only one per list.

ftbuniversity.intbook.subtitle=Get "On the Dynamics of Integration"
ftbuniversity.intbook.desc1=&bOn the Dynamics of Integration&r is &eIntegrated Dynamics&r' guide book.
ftbuniversity.intbook.desc2=It has pages for pretty much everything in the mod, teaching concepts, walking through tutorials, and describing the mod on a block-by-block basis.
ftbuniversity.intbook.desc3=Seriously, &6give the tutorial section a read&r. It does a really good job of walking you through the mod.

ftbuniversity.menrilchunk.title=Menril
ftbuniversity.menrilchunk.subtitle=Chop a Menril tree
ftbuniversity.menrilchunk.desc1=&bMenril trees&r, which spawn rarely everywhere but very common in the &6Meneglin&r biome.
ftbuniversity.menrilchunk.desc2=When chopped, Menril trees drop &bMenril Wood&r, &bMenril Berries&r, and &bCrystallized Menril Chunks&r, all of which are important crafting components.

ftbuniversity.idsqueezer.title=Knowledge Juice
ftbuniversity.idsqueezer.subtitle=Make a Squeezer
ftbuniversity.idsqueezer.desc1=Right-click Menril Wood into a &bSqueezer&r to insert it, then jump up and down on top of it to squish it down, producing &6Menril Resin&r.
ftbuniversity.idsqueezer.desc2=The Menril Resin will automatically be output to a fluid container on &6two if its sides&r.
ftbuniversity.idsqueezer.desc3=Give the Squeezer a &6redstone signal&r to reset it.

ftbuniversity.idwrench.subtitle=Make a Wrench
ftbuniversity.idwrench.desc1=The &bWrench&r is a wrench. It does wrench things.
ftbuniversity.idwrench.desc2=Right-clicking a Logic Cable connection will disable that connection. Right-clicking while sneaking will break the part itself.

ftbuniversity.labeller.subtitle=Make a Labeller
ftbuniversity.labeller.desc=You can put any item into the &bLabeller&r's GUI, type something in the text box, then click &6Write&r to rename the item.

ftbuniversity.mechanicalsqueezer.subtitle=Make a Mechanical Squeezer
ftbuniversity.mechanicalsqueezer.desc1=The &bMechanical Squeezer&r &6uses RF&r to convert Menril Wood into Menril Resin, at the same time as producing Crystallized Menril Chunks.
ftbuniversity.mechanicalsqueezer.desc2=In its GUI, you can toggle whether or not it should auto-eject fluids to adjacent tanks.

ftbuniversity.dryingbasin.subtitle=Make a Drying Basin
ftbuniversity.dryingbasin.desc1=The &bDrying Basin&r will dry items/fluids inserted into it. Some recipes may require both items &oand&r fluids to work; see its uses in JEI.
ftbuniversity.dryingbasin.desc2=Its most important use is to &6convert Menril Resin into a Block of Crystallized Menril&r.

ftbuniversity.idfacade.title=Facades
ftbuniversity.idfacade.subtitle=Make a Facade
ftbuniversity.idfacade.desc1=&bFacades&r can hide your Logic Cables, making them look like a different block.
ftbuniversity.idfacade.desc2=Craft a Facade with any block, then right-click it on the Logic Cable to disguise it.

ftbuniversity.mechdrybas.subtitle=Make a Mechanical Drying Basin
ftbuniversity.mechdrybas.desc=The &bMechanical Drying Basin&r works just like the Drying Basin, but uses RF.

ftbuniversity.logiccable.subtitle=Make Logic Cables
ftbuniversity.logiccable.desc=&bLogic Cables&r are the mod's pipes; they connect network components.

ftbuniversity.monoconn.subtitle=Make a Mono-Directional Connector
ftbuniversity.monoconn.desc1=&bMono-Directional Connectors&r allow you to &6connect sections of a network wirelessly&r.
ftbuniversity.monoconn.desc2=Place two MDCs facing each other (so a straight line from one reaches the other). That's all you have to do to connect them! They also even work if blocks are in the way.

ftbuniversity.omnicon.subtitle=Make Omni-Directional Connectors
ftbuniversity.omnicon.desc1=&bOmni-Directional Connectors&r, which are crafted in pairs, will connect the networks they are placed on wirelessly. This includes &6across dimensions&r.
ftbuniversity.omnicon.desc2=As the recipe for an ODC gives 2, those 2 are paired together.

ftbuniversity.variablecard.subtitle=Make a Variable Card
ftbuniversity.variablecard.desc1=&bVariable Cards&r are the primary mode of &6logic transport&r. They contain a reference to a certain value with a certain value type.
ftbuniversity.variablecard.desc2=Network components (like a Redstone Reader) have &6Aspects&r (Redstone, Comparator, etc) of specific &6Types&r (Boolean, Integer, etc).
ftbuniversity.variablecard.desc3=For components that read/set variables (like Readers), you can insert a Variable Card next to an Aspect to &6save a reference to that variable&r.
ftbuniversity.variablecard.desc4=Then, you would insert the set Variable Card into something that &ouses&r a variable (say, a Display Panel) and it will do some logic with it.
ftbuniversity.variablecard.desc5=&6An unset Variable Card functions as a Boolean: True variable.&r

ftbuniversity.displaypanel.subtitle=Make a Display Panel
ftbuniversity.displaypanel.desc1=The &bDisplay Panel&r takes a Variable Card and will display its value.
ftbuniversity.displaypanel.desc2=For instance, if given a Card for the integer value of a redstone signal, the Panel will display the numerical strength of the signal.

ftbuniversity.redstoneio.title=Redstone Signal Transfer
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.subtitle=Learn how a simple Reader/Writer combo works
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.desc1=One of the most simple things you can do with Integrated Dynamics is to &btransfer a redstone signal&r.
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.desc2=At the location you want to input the signal, place a &bRedstone Reader&r.
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.desc3=In the Reader's GUI, find the variable we want (in this situation, &6Aspect: Redstone&r, &6Type: Integer&r), and &6use a Variable Card to get a reference to it&r.
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.desc4=If this Variable Card is inserted into anything on the same network that can accept it, it will try to &6match the variable as it changes&r in the Reader.
ftbuniversity.redstoneio.desc5=Insert the Variable Card into the &6Aspect: Redstone&r, &6Type: Integer&r slot of a &bRedstone Writer&r, and it will output a signal that matches the signal given to the Reader.

ftbuniversity.readers.title=Readers
ftbuniversity.readers.subtitle=Make any Reader
ftbuniversity.readers.desc1=&bReaders&r take information from the world and &6expose them as variables&r.
ftbuniversity.readers.desc2=Different Readers take different information; their &6tooltips&r give short explanations for each.
ftbuniversity.readers.desc3=Each also have some pages in &nOn the Dynamics of Integration&r, if the tooltips aren't informative enough.

ftbuniversity.writers.title=Writers
ftbuniversity.writers.subtitle=Make any Writer
ftbuniversity.writers.desc1=&bWriters&r take a variable from a &6Variable Card&r and do some sort of logic with them.
ftbuniversity.writers.desc2=There are actually fairly few functional Writers. See their tooltips or the book for information on each.
ftbuniversity.writers.desc3=You may expect them to work like Refined Storage's Reader/Writers, but you &ccannot move items, fluids, or energy&r with Integrated Dynamics alone.
ftbuniversity.writers.desc4=That's not to say you can't move items etc at all; the addon &eIntegrated Tunnels&r adds components that do this. We'll go over those later.

ftbuniversity.logprogram.title=Logic Operations
ftbuniversity.logprogram.subtitle=Make a Logic Programmer
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc1=The &bLogic Programmer&r allows you to take a variable, do some math on it, and turn that into another variable.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc2=This can also be used to make &6variables that can't be made with Readers&r, like arbitrary strings or integers.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc3=On the left is a list of variable types and operators. Choose one (for now, let's make a string), set what you want it to be, then &6insert a Variable Card&r into the bottom right slot. This will set the Card to the variable you just made.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc4=&6Operators&r take existing variables to make new ones. For instance, a &6+&r operator takes two integer variables and adds them, making a third variable.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc5=Not all operators are strictly math. The &6name&r operator takes a named object (like an item) and converts it into a string variable.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc6=This could be used with the &6contains&r operator to give a positive boolean value if, for example, the item "minecraft:iron_ingot" is turned into the string "Iron Ingot," which is then checked to see if it contains the phrase "Ingot."
ftbuniversity.logprogram.desc7=Operators that depend on variables require that those variables exist in the network. You can put the base variables in the &bVariable Store&r block, which does nothing with the Variable Cards except expose them to the network.
ftbuniversity.logprogram.task=Logic Programmer

ftbuniversity.proxies.subtitle=Make a Proxy
ftbuniversity.proxies.desc1=The &bProxy&r can have a Variable Card stored in it, and then can have additional Cards bound to it.
ftbuniversity.proxies.desc2=Variable Cards bound to a Proxy will &6always match the output of the Proxie's Card&r, even if it changes. The Proxy must have a Card stored in the top slot to work.
ftbuniversity.proxies.desc3=This can also be used to effectively &6copy Variable Cards&r.

ftbuniversity.delayer.subtitle=Make a Delayer
ftbuniversity.delayer.desc1=The &bDelayer&r can have a Variable Card stored in it, and then can have additional Cards bound to it.
ftbuniversity.delayer.desc2=Variable Cards bound to a Delayer will &6store a List of the previous outputs of the main Variable&r. The Delayer must have a Card stored in the top slot to work.
ftbuniversity.delayer.desc3=In the Delayer's GUI allows you to set how often it checks, as well as how large the list is.

ftbuniversity.materializer.title=Constants
ftbuniversity.materializer.subtitle=Make a Materializer
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc1=The &bMaterial&r accepts a variable, and then if you insert a second Variable Card, it will turn it into a &6constant of the variable's current value&r.
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc2=For instance, if you put a Block variable in the top, make it so that variable is set to Cobblestone, then insert a Variable Card into the bottom right, it creates a &6Block variable that is always equal to Cobblestone&r.
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc3=This is very useful for comparing values. Instead of doing:
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc4=&cname(&7Block:[variable]&c)&9==&cString:"Cobblestone"&r
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc5=you would instead do:
ftbuniversity.materializer.desc6=&7Block:[variable]&9==&7Block:"minecraft:cobblestone"&r

ftbuniversity.iddoor.title=Secret Tunnel
ftbuniversity.iddoor.subtitle=Make a door that only opens for you
ftbuniversity.iddoor.desc1=Place an &6Entity Reader&r on the ground, and take the Entity variable from it. While standing on the Entity Reader, put the variable into the Materializer and get a constant from it.
ftbuniversity.iddoor.desc2=Use the &6==&r operator to see if the Entity variable in the Reader matches your constant.
ftbuniversity.iddoor.desc3=Insert this final operator Variable Card into a &6Redstone Writer&r that is powering a door.

ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.title=Item Transfer
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.subtitle=Make an item transfer system with Integrated Tunnels
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc1=&eIntegrated Tunnels&r is an addon for Integrated Dynamics that gives it the ability to &6import, store, and export items/fluids/energy within a network&r.
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc2=To begin with, make the &bItem Interface&r. Place this on an inventory, like a Chest, and imported items will be stored here.
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc3=Next, place an &bItem Importer&r on an inventory that you want to pull from. In it, there are slots for variables that control if it should import all items, import specific items, import only from a specific slot, etc.
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc4=Now, items placed in this inventory should &6extremely quickly&r be moved to the inventory with an Item Interface.
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc5=Place an &bItem Exporter&r on an inventory that you want to push into. Like the importer, it has variables that can control what gets exported.
ftbuniversity.integratedtunnels.desc6=Congrats! You have now automated item transfer! These skills will very easily transfer to fluids and energy, as they all work in the same &6insert, store, export&r method.

ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.title=Whitelists
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.subtitle=Learn how to whitelist what is moved
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.desc1=The "Import/Export All Items" booleans are fairly obvious in what they do, but you &oprobably&r won't always want to move &oeverything&r.
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.desc2=Importers and Exporters have the various variables that allow you to &bspecify what is moved&r.
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.desc3=For instance, you can put a Variable Card set to Menril Wood (set using the &7Type: Item&r function of a &6Logic Programmer&r) into the &7Export Item&r slot of an Item Exporter, and it will only export Menril Wood.
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.desc4=Or, you could make a &6List&r of items, or even &6predicate&r (math, basically).
ftbuniversity.itwhitelist.desc5=The amount of possibilities are staggeringly high, as is the time it would take to mention even a fraction of them, so I won't. You should have (roughly) all the knowledge you need, experiment!

ftbuniversity.worldints.title=Placing and Breaking
ftbuniversity.worldints.subtitle=Make any World Importer/Exporter
ftbuniversity.worldints.desc1=&bWorld Importers/Exporters&r, as the names suggest, interact with the world instead of inventories.
ftbuniversity.worldints.desc2=World Item, Fluid, and Block Yada-yadas, in order, &6pick up and drop items&r, &6place and pick up fluids&r, and &6place and mine blocks&r.
ftbuniversity.worldints.desc3=These can have whitelists, so you could automate placing Stone next to a Pure Daisy, then only allow it to break Livingrock.
ftbuniversity.worldints.task=Any World Importer/Exporter

ftbuniversity.playersim.subtitle=Make a Player Simulator
ftbuniversity.playersim.desc1=The &bPlayer Simulator&r will &6simulate clicking&r, as if it were a player.
ftbuniversity.playersim.desc2=It has variables for clicking with no item or clicking with a random or specific item in the network (via Item Interfaces)
ftbuniversity.playersim.desc3=Every variable have aspects. The most important one, in my opinion, would be a &9Boolean: Right Click&r. If true, it simulates a right-click. If false, it simlates a left-click, which can punch mobs and break blocks (if &9Continuous Click&r is set to true).

ftbuniversity.itnonitems.title=Items Aren't Everything
ftbuniversity.itnonitems.subtitle=Make any non-item tunnel
ftbuniversity.itnonitems.desc=There are also &bInterfaces&r, &bImporters&r, and &bExporters&r for fluid and energy!
ftbuniversity.itnonitems.task=Non-item thingamabobs

ftbuniversity.energybattery.subtitle=Make an Energy Battery
ftbuniversity.energybattery.desc1=If RF is imported into the network, but it doesn't have any valid Energy Interface to store it in, it will be stored in any &bEnergy Battery&r connected to the network.
ftbuniversity.energybattery.desc2=Energy Batteries do not have to be connected with an Interface, they &6automatically connect to adjacent Logic Cables&r.
ftbuniversity.energybattery.desc3=You can &6craft two Energy Batteries together&r to combine their storage. The highest possible RF in a single battery is &6655,360,000 RF&r.
ftbuniversity.energybattery.desc4=Sneak right-clicking an Energy Battery in your inventory will make it charge your items.

ftbuniversity.worldenergy.title=Charger
ftbuniversity.worldenergy.subtitle=Make a World Energy Importer/Exporter
ftbuniversity.worldenergy.desc=The &bWorld Energy Importer and Exporter&r can be used to &6uncharge and charge dropped items&r using energy in the network.
ftbuniversity.worldenergy.task=World Energy Importer/Exporter

ftbuniversity.storageterminal.subtitle=Make a Storage Terminal
ftbuniversity.storageterminal.desc1=The &bStorage Terminal&r allows access to all stored items and fluids in the network (connected by Interfaces).
ftbuniversity.storageterminal.desc2=You can use the Storage Terminal like a chest, removing and adding items is almost exactly identical.
ftbuniversity.storageterminal.desc3=For fluids and energy, pick them up like you would an item, then click them on a container in your inventory.
ftbuniversity.storageterminal.desc4=Additionally, there is a tab that has a 3x3 crafting grid, allowing you to craft using items in storage.
ftbuniversity.storageterminal.desc5=The Storage Terminal is added by the addon &eIntegrated Terminals&r; it is not there by default.

ftbuniversity.intcrafting.subtitle=Make a Crafting Interface
ftbuniversity.intcrafting.desc1=The &bCrafting Interface&r is the first step to auto-crafting using your network.
ftbuniversity.intcrafting.desc2=Attach the Crafting Interface &6to the machine you want to craft with&r. For regular 3x3 crafting recipes, attach it to a Crafting Table; for smelting recipes, attach it to a Furnace; etc.
ftbuniversity.intcrafting.desc3=Using a &6Logic Programmer&r, click &9Recipe&r and set the crafting recipe you want. For instance, place 8 Oak Planks in the left slots, then place a Chest in the right slots.
ftbuniversity.intcrafting.desc4=Insert this Variable Card into one of the slots in the Crafting Interface, and the network will now have access to that recipe.

ftbuniversity.ictips.title=Crafting Tips
ftbuniversity.ictips.subtitle=Learn some tips for recipe-making
ftbuniversity.ictips.desc1=If the recipe gives only one unique item, place it in the top-most output slot. Otherwise, the recipe will think it also creates air, which confuses the network.
ftbuniversity.ictips.desc2=You can also shift-click the input slots to change what they accept (so you can set it to use OreDic, for instance).
ftbuniversity.ictips.desc3=Right-click a filled slot to increase the amount by 1; left-click to decrease by 1.

ftbuniversity.craftwriter.subtitle=Make a Craft Writer
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc1=The &bCraft Writer&r has 4 options:
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc2=â€¢ Craft using a specific recipe, which takes a recipe variable
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc3=â€¢ Craft a specific item using any recipe, which takes an item variable
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc4=â€¢ Craft a fluid using any recipe, which takes a fluid variable
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc5=â€¢ Craft energy using any recipe, which takes an integer variable
ftbuniversity.craftwriter.desc6=By default, it &6crafts only the item is not in the network&r at all. So, it'll craft once, then stop. Enabling &9Ignore Storage Contents&r will make it craft forever.

ftbuniversity.craftjob.subtitle=Make a Crafting Job Terminal
ftbuniversity.craftjob.desc1=The &bCrafting Job Terminal&r has a list of all current crafting jobs in its network.
ftbuniversity.craftjob.desc2=You can click on any crafting job to cancel it.

ftbuniversity.integratednbt.subtitle=Make an NBT Extractor
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc1=The addon &eIntegrated NBT&r adds several things that help make it easier to work with NBT in items and fluids.
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc2=The main thing is the &bNBT Extractor&r, which allows you to isolate a specific NBT tag from an NBT tree as a variable.
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc3=To begin with, the &6Logic Controller&r has several operators dedicated to working with NBT. The simplest would be &9NBT()&r, which simply grabs all the NBT from an item and stores it in a Variable Card, giving it the "&eOutput Type: &9NBT&r".
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc4=You would insert this Variable Card into the left slot of the NBT Extractor, which would expose that item's NBT tree in the window above.
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc5=Pick the specific NBT element that you want, then it will be saved to a Variable Card on the right.
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc6=Variable Cards in the NBT Extractor are available to the network, so you &6do not have to put them into a Variable Store&r.
ftbuniversity.integratednbt.desc7=From here, you can do basically whatever you want with the Variable Card. You could whitelist an Item Importer to only pull items that have no RF, export them to a charger, then put them back into the chest it came from, perhaps. The possibilities are limited only by your creativity.

###AE2
ftbuniversity.ae2chap.title=Applied Energistics 2

ftbuniversity.certus.title=Certainly Quartz
ftbuniversity.certus.subtitle=Get some Certus Quartz
ftbuniversity.certus.desc1=&bCertus Quartz&r is one of the most-used materials in Applied Energistics 2.
ftbuniversity.certus.desc2=It comes in two types, normal and charged. &bCharged Certus Quartz&r drops from its ore, but can also be made in the &6Charger&r.
ftbuniversity.certus.desc3=Mekanism also adds a way to craft it, but that's on Mekanism's side, not AE2's.
ftbuniversity.certus.reward=Certus Quartz

ftbuniversity.fluix.title=Fluix Buddies
ftbuniversity.fluix.subtitle=Get some Fluix Crystals
ftbuniversity.fluix.desc1=&bFluix Crystals&r are another resource, but they don't generate naturally.
ftbuniversity.fluix.desc2=Instead, &6throw some Charged Certus Quartz, Nether Quartz, and Redstone dust into water&r and wait a second.

ftbuniversity.purecrystals.title=Purity
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.subtitle=Get some Pure Crystals
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.desc1=The final new material is &bPure Crystals&r.
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.desc2=To make Pure Crystals, throw a &bSeed&r of that type in some Water and just let it grow. It takes a &nvery long time&r, but eventually it will turn into a Pure Crystal.
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.desc3=It is &6highly recommended to use Crystal Growth Accelerators&r, as they drastically reduce the time required.
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.desc4=There are Pure variations of Nether Quartz, Certus Quartz, and Fluix Crystals.
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.task1=Crystal Seeds
ftbuniversity.purecrystals.task2=Pure Crystals

ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.title=ME and Mine
ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.subtitle=Make an Energy Acceptor
ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.desc1=Applied Energistics 2 does not use RF or EU. Rather, it has &6its own energy system&r called "AE".
ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.desc2=The &bEnergy Acceptor&r can convert EU/RF to AE, at a rate of 1EU=2AE and 2RF=1AE.
ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.desc3=AE power can be &6transferred via any Cable&r from AE2.
ftbuniversity.ae2energyacceptor.desc4=&nHowever&r, the &6ME Controller can also convert&r RF/EU to AE, and at a much faster rate. You have to make that eventually anyway, so &6this quest is optional&r.

ftbuniversity.ae2energycell.subtitle=Make an Energy Cell
ftbuniversity.ae2energycell.desc1=&bEnergy Cells&r store AE power, acting as a backup in case the network stops receiving it externally.
ftbuniversity.ae2energycell.desc2=The lower tier stores &6200,000 AE&r, and the higher stores &61,600,000 AE&r.
ftbuniversity.ae2energycell.task=Energy Cell

ftbuniversity.vibrationchamber.title=Bad Vibes
ftbuniversity.vibrationchamber.subtitle=(Don't) Make a Vibration Chamber
ftbuniversity.vibrationchamber.desc1=The &bVibration Chamber&r burns furnace fuels to generate AE.
ftbuniversity.vibrationchamber.desc2=This is the only in-house way of generating power for AE2, but like... &6there's so many better ways&r to generate RF and then convert to AE that this doesn't really have any reason to exist.
ftbuniversity.vibrationchamber.desc3=As such, &6this quest is entirely optional&r.

ftbuniversity.growthaccelerator.title=Basically Impossible Without This
ftbuniversity.growthaccelerator.subtitle=Make a Crystal Growth Accelerator
ftbuniversity.growthaccelerator.desc1=&bCrystal Growth Accelerators&r use AE power to &6speed up the growth of adjacent crystal Seeds&r.
ftbuniversity.growthaccelerator.desc2=It is powered from the top or bottom, and it speeds up Seeds that are &6touching its sides&r.
ftbuniversity.growthaccelerator.desc3=You can have &6up to 5&r surrounding one Water block while still leaving room for you to throw Seeds in.

ftbuniversity.inscriber.subtitle=Make an Inscriber
ftbuniversity.inscriber.desc1=The &bInscriber&r is required to craft &6Processors&r, which are used very often in crafting recipes.
ftbuniversity.inscriber.desc2=In the top slot, insert an &6Inscriber Press&r (more on that in the quest above), then insert the appropriate item in the center. Give it RF and it will slowly start working.
ftbuniversity.inscriber.desc3=Inscribers are &6fairly hard to automate&r, as they can only have one item in each slot at a time. Placed upright, the top face is the &6top input&r, the bottom is the &6bottom input&r, and sides are both the &6middle input and the output&r.

ftbuniversity.ae2compass.subtitle=Make a Meteorite Compass
ftbuniversity.ae2compass.desc1=Normally, you have to use the &bMeteorite Compass&r to find meteorites, at the center of which will have a chest with a &6random Inscriber Press&r.
ftbuniversity.ae2compass.desc2=This is fun the first couple times, but can get annoying when you have 6 Logic Presses and nothing else. It can also cause lag, due to world generation.
ftbuniversity.ae2compass.desc3=So, &6we've added recipes for Presses and Sky Stone&r, to hopefully mitigate some of those issues. Meteorites still spawn, but aren't necessary.
ftbuniversity.ae2compass.task=Craftables

ftbuniversity.ae2acceleration.subtitle=Make an Acceleration Card
ftbuniversity.ae2acceleration.desc1=&bAcceleration Cards&r can be inserted into certain AE2 machines to make them work faster.
ftbuniversity.ae2acceleration.desc2=You can install multiple to increase their work speed even more.

ftbuniversity.mecontroller.title=ME!ME!ME!
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.subtitle=Make an ME Controller
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc1=The &BME Controller&r is the brain of every ME (matter-energy) network. &6You can only have one Controller multiblock per network.&r
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc2=This quest will go over its &6construction&r, the quest above will explain how it works.
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc3=When making the multiblock, &6prioritize how many faces are available&r; meaning, how many Cables can be attached directly.
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc4=The multiblock must be a &67x7x7 or smaller&r.
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc5=Controllers can only have a single axis with 2 connections; that is, it can be &6shaped like âŠ¥&r but &cnot +&r.
ftbuniversity.mecontroller.desc6=The Controller can convert EU/RF to AE, at a rate of 1EU=2AE and 2RF=1AE.

ftbuniversity.ae2channels.title=Change the Channel
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.subtitle=Learn about Channels
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc1=&bChannels&r are a system unique to AE2. Cables can only support so many channels, with each device taking up one.
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc2=You can theoretically have an ME network &6without a Controller&r, but it would &6only be able to support 8 channels&r.
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc3=Normal &6Cables can carry 8 channels&r, while &6Dense Cables can carry 32&r, though they cannot connect to devices directly.
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc4=A Dense Cable can support 4 fully maxed normal Cables.
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc5=Each face of an ME Controller &6provides up to 32 channels&r, limited by the Cable connecting to it.
ftbuniversity.ae2channels.desc6=Channels will take the &6shortest path&r from the Controller to the device.

ftbuniversity.ae2channellink.title=They're Very Complex, Sorry
ftbuniversity.ae2channellink.subtitle=If that didn't explain it well enough, click this to go to the mod's wiki page on channels.

ftbuniversity.networktool.subtitle=Make a Network Tool
ftbuniversity.networktool.desc1=The &bNetwork Tool&r is AE2's wrench, though it has some extra features.
ftbuniversity.networktool.desc2=Using any wrench on a device will remove it from its Cable.
ftbuniversity.networktool.desc3=Clicking the ME Controller with a Network Tool will show all machines in the ME network, along with how much power it is using per tick.
ftbuniversity.networktool.desc4=Sneak right-clicking the Network Tool will open its GUI, allowing you to &6insert 9 stacks of upgrade Cards&r. When in a device GUI, the Tool's Cards will be available.

ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.title=You Basic
ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.subtitle=Make ME Glass Cables
ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.desc1=&bME Glass Cables&r are the most basic form of ME Cable.
ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.desc2=They can &6carry 8 channels&r, and can &6support devices&r attached to them.
ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.desc3=&bME Covered Cables&r are &6functionally identical&r to Glass Cables.
ftbuniversity.ae2glasscable.task=Either Fluix Cable

ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.title=&4&lâ–ˆ&c&lâ–ˆ&6&lâ–ˆ&e&lâ–ˆ&2&lâ–ˆ&a&lâ–ˆ&b&lâ–ˆ&3&lâ–ˆ&1&lâ–ˆ&9&lâ–ˆ&d&lâ–ˆ
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.subtitle=Make any colored Cable
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.desc1=Cables of all kinds can be color-coded to prevent unwanted connections.
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.desc2=Colored Cables &6only connect to Cables of the same color&r, though all colors connect to normal Fluix Cables.
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.desc3=This is especially useful for when you have several paths within a small area that you don't want interacting, to make sure channels only go along certain paths.
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.desc4=Also, certain devices will match the color of the Cable they are on!
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.task=Colored Cables
ftbuniversity.ae2colorcables.reward=Dyes

ftbuniversity.quartzfiber.title=Technically You Already Had to Make These, But...
ftbuniversity.quartzfiber.subtitle=Make Quartz Fiber
ftbuniversity.quartzfiber.desc1=&bQuartz Fiber&r can be placed between two Cables to &6allow energy, but &onot&r &6channels, to pass through&r.

ftbuniversity.mesmartcable.title=You Smart
ftbuniversity.mesmartcable.subtitle=Make ME Smart Cables
ftbuniversity.mesmartcable.desc1=&bME Smart Cables&r have all the same functionality as normal ME Cables, but will &6display how many channels are passing through them&r.
ftbuniversity.mesmartcable.desc2=In addition to being convenient, it also just looks super cool.

ftbuniversity.medense.title=Dummy Thicc
ftbuniversity.medense.subtitle=Make ME Dense Covered Cables
ftbuniversity.medense.desc1=&bME Dense Covered Cables&r can carry up to &632 channels&r, but cannot directly support devices.
ftbuniversity.medense.desc2=Pre-P2P (we'll get to that eventually), it would be smart to directly connect these to the Controller, and then from there branch off into normal Cables.

ftbuniversity.smartdense.title=Big Brain
ftbuniversity.smartdense.subtitle=Make ME Dense Smart Cables
ftbuniversity.smartdense.desc=&bME Dense Smart Cables&r work exactly like Dense Covered Cables, but they &6show how many channels are passing through them&r.

ftbuniversity.ae2facade.title=The C is Silent, and the S is Invisible
ftbuniversity.ae2facade.subtitle=Make any Cable Facade
ftbuniversity.ae2facade.desc1=&bCable Facades&r can be attached to any ME Cable, &6making that side look like the block it's made out of&r.
ftbuniversity.ae2facade.desc2=Additionally, Torches, Levers, and the like can be placed on Facades, as if they were a solid block.
ftbuniversity.ae2facade.desc3=Facades can be placed on the same face as a device, so you can make your Terminals etc flush with the wall.
ftbuniversity.ae2facade.task=Any Cable Facade

ftbuniversity.mechest.subtitle=Make an ME Chest
ftbuniversity.mechest.desc1=The &bME Chest&r is the most simple way to use AE2 to store items.
ftbuniversity.mechest.desc2=Click any side other than the top to insert a &6Storage Cell&r, and click the top to access items inside it.
ftbuniversity.mechest.desc3=The ME Chest is capable of &6working independently&r of an ME Controller, as it can accept RF/EU directly. However, if connected to a network, the network will also be able to access its contents.

ftbuniversity.meterminal.title=Storage Access
ftbuniversity.meterminal.subtitle=Make an ME Terminal
ftbuniversity.meterminal.desc1=The &bME Terminal&r is the first of many devices, and allows you to &6access all items in the ME network&r (we'll get to storing items in a bit).
ftbuniversity.meterminal.desc2=On the left, you have several &6buttons&r. Their &6tooltips&r should be fairly self-explanatory.
ftbuniversity.meterminal.desc3=The top right has a button to show what the system is &6auto-crafting&r, as well as 5 slots for &6View Cells&r. We'll cover both of those later.

ftbuniversity.craftingterminal.subtitle=Make an ME Crafting Terminal
ftbuniversity.craftingterminal.desc=The &bME Crafting Terminal&r works exactly like an ME Terminal, but &6has a 3x3 crafting grid&r.

ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.title=Cells at Work
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.subtitle=Make a Cell Workbench
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.desc1=The &bCell Workbench&r allows you to &6configure Cells&r.
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.desc2=You can insert a &6Storage Cell&r into the top right slot, and then in the slots below set an &6item whitelist&r of what is allowed to enter that Cell. This is called &6partitioning&r.
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.desc3=An example use of this would be to put all ores into one cell, all ingots into another, etc. That way, the cell won't get full of any random junk you put into the system.
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.desc4=You can also click the Wrench button to automatically partition the Cell to what it's currently holding.
ftbuniversity.cellworkbench.desc5=You can insert a &6Fuzzy Card&r to make that Cell ignore damage and nbt, and you can insert an &6Invert Card&r to make it a blacklist instead of a whitelist.

ftbuniversity.viewcell.title=Filter
ftbuniversity.viewcell.subtitle=Make a View Cell
ftbuniversity.viewcell.desc=Partition a &bView Cell&r, and then insert it into the top right slots of Terminals to filter what's visible to match the View Cell's whitelist/blacklist.

ftbuniversity.medrive.title=Storing Items
ftbuniversity.medrive.subtitle=Make an ME Drive and Storage Cell
ftbuniversity.medrive.desc1=The &bME Drive&r can store up to 10 &bStorage Cells&r, allowing their contents to be visible to the network.
ftbuniversity.medrive.desc2=Storage Cells can store items, with higher tiers storing more.
ftbuniversity.medrive.desc3=&oTechnically&r, Storage Cells store &6bytes&r, not items. A certain amount of bytes is required for unique items; &62 of the same item uses less bytes than 2 different items&r.
ftbuniversity.medrive.desc4=&6Higher tier Cells have more bytes&r, but also require &6more bytes per unique item&r. That makes them more useful for storing a large amount of a small variety of items.
ftbuniversity.medrive.desc5=Additionally, every cell is &6limited to 63 unique items&r.
ftbuniversity.medrive.task=Any Storage Cell

ftbuniversity.meimport.title=I
ftbuniversity.meimport.subtitle=Make an ME Import Bus
ftbuniversity.meimport.desc1=The &bME Import Bus&r will pull items from the inventory it is facing, inserting them into its ME network.
ftbuniversity.meimport.desc2=In its GUI, you can set a &6whitelist&r. Defaulting to 1 item, up to 2 &6Capacity Cards&r can be installed to increase the amount to 9.
ftbuniversity.meimport.desc3=You can also install a &6Fuzzy Card&r to make it ignore NBT/Damage, as well as &6Acceleration Cards&r to make it work faster.

ftbuniversity.meexport.title=O
ftbuniversity.meexport.subtitle=Make an ME Export Bus
ftbuniversity.meexport.desc1=The &BME Export Bus&r will push items (set by a whitelist in its GUI) from its ME network into the inventory it is facing.
ftbuniversity.meexport.desc2=Its whitelist by default only has 1 slot, but can be upgraded to 9 with &6Capacity Cards&r.
ftbuniversity.meexport.desc3=You can also install a &6Fuzzy Card&r to make it ignore NBT/Damage, as well as &6Acceleration Cards&r to make it work faster.
ftbuniversity.meexport.desc4=Additionally, you can insert a &6Crafting Card&r to allow it to craft items to export if they run out. Naturally, this only works if the items can be auto-crafted by the network.

ftbuniversity.metoggle.title=Disconneeeeeeeeeeeect
ftbuniversity.metoggle.subtitle=Make an ME Toggle Bus
ftbuniversity.metoggle.desc1=The &bME Toggle Bus&r, when given a redstone signal, will not allow channels or energy to pass through it. This effectively disconnects everything past it.
ftbuniversity.metoggle.desc2=The &bInverted ME Toggle Bus&r does the opposite, disabling when not given a signal.

ftbuniversity.levelemitter.subtitle=Make an ME Level Emitter
ftbuniversity.levelemitter.desc1=The &bME Level Emitter&r will output a redstone signal &6when a specified item is above/below a specified amount&r.
ftbuniversity.levelemitter.desc2=You can also set it to emit the signal when the ME network's &6energy is below a specified amount&r, so you can automatically start an emergency generator to power it back up.

ftbuniversity.storagebus.title=External Storage
ftbuniversity.storagebus.subtitle=Make an ME Storage Bus
ftbuniversity.storagebus.desc1=The &bME Storage Bus&r, when placed on an inventory, will connect that inventory to the ME system.
ftbuniversity.storagebus.desc2=In &6Bi-Directional&r mode, items can be pulled from it, as well as being pushed into it. When items are inserted into the ME system, they will try to go to Storage Buses that already have that item before Storage Cells.
ftbuniversity.storagebus.desc3=In &6Extract Only&r, you can only pull from it. 
ftbuniversity.storagebus.desc4=In &6Insert Only&r and with &6no whitelist&r, items in it will not be available, and it will act as a lowest-possible priority destination for items.
ftbuniversity.storagebus.desc5=In &6Insert Only&r and &6with a whitelist&r, items in the whitelist will enter that inventory, seemingly disappearing from the network.

ftbuniversity.storagemonitor.subtitle=Make an ME Storage Monitor
ftbuniversity.storagemonitor.desc1=The &bME Storage Monitor&r will display the amount of the set item in its storage.
ftbuniversity.storagemonitor.desc2=To set the item, simply right-click the Monitor with it.
ftbuniversity.storagemonitor.desc3=Right-click with an empty hand to unset items, and use a Wrench on it to lock it to an item.
ftbuniversity.storagemonitor.desc4=The Storage Monitor is &6not a Drawer&r; you cannot punch it to remove items.

ftbuniversity.capacitycard.subtitle=Make a Capacity Card
ftbuniversity.capacitycard.desc1=&bCapacity Cards&r can be installed to certain devices to increase their max whitelist size.
ftbuniversity.capacitycard.desc2=Generally, devices only have 1 slot available. Up to 2 Capacity Cards can be installed to bring it up to 9.

ftbuniversity.fuzzycard.subtitle=Make a Fuzzy Card
ftbuniversity.fuzzycard.desc1=The &bFuzzy Card&r can be installed to certain devices to allow them to match a specific range of damage, rather than specifically what is given to it.
ftbuniversity.fuzzycard.desc2=There are 6 modes: &6Match Any&r, then &6Split Damage at 99%%&r, &675%%&r, &650%%&r, and &625%%&r.
ftbuniversity.fuzzycard.desc3=Match Any makes it ignore damage entirely, and the Split Damages match when the damage is within that percentage of the full durability.
ftbuniversity.fuzzycard.desc4=All modes will ignore NBT.

ftbuniversity.redstonecard.subtitle=Make a Redstone Card
ftbuniversity.redstonecard.desc1=The &bRedstone Card&r can be installed to certain devices to allow them to be controlled by a redstone signal.
ftbuniversity.redstonecard.desc2=There are &6Always active&r, &6Active without signal&r, &6Active with signal&r, and &6Activate once per pulse&r.

ftbuniversity.mesecurity.title=That Thing That Wireless Terminals Need
ftbuniversity.mesecurity.subtitle=Make an ME Security Terminal
ftbuniversity.mesecurity.desc1=The &bME Security Terminal&r allows you to configure what people are allowed to do with your ME network. Ownership of the network is decided by who places the Security Terminal.
ftbuniversity.mesecurity.desc2=A &6Biometric Card&r can be inserted into the bottom left slot, then permissions can be toggled with the buttons on the right. Put the Biometric Card into one of the top slots to apply it.
ftbuniversity.mesecurity.desc3=A blank Biometric Card means "anyone but the owner." A player can sneak right-click the Biometric Card to set it to themselves.
ftbuniversity.mesecurity.desc4=And now, the only reason anyone ever actually makes a Security Terminal: you can &6insert a Wireless Terminal&r into the top right slot to &6bind it to that ME network&r.

ftbuniversity.meaccesspoint.subtitle=Make an ME Wireless Access Point
ftbuniversity.meaccesspoint.desc1=An &bME Wireless Access Point&r allows players &6within 16 blocks&r of itself to access the ME system using Wireless Terminals.
ftbuniversity.meaccesspoint.desc2=You can add &bWireless Boosters&r to the Access Point to increase the range, also increasing the cost. Having an entire stack installed increases the range to 528, at the total cost of 4,100 AE/t.

ftbuniversity.wirelessterminal.subtitle=Make a Wireless Terminal
ftbuniversity.wirelessterminal.desc1=The &bWireless Terminal&r uses AE power to access its bound ME network wirelessly. It works exactly like an ME Terminal.
ftbuniversity.wirelessterminal.desc2=You have to bind it to the network in a Security Terminal, and you must be within range of a Wireless Access Point.
ftbuniversity.wirelessterminal.desc3=It uses 1 AE/t for every block between you and the Access Point while being used.

ftbuniversity.wct2.subtitle=Make a Wireless Crafting Terminal
ftbuniversity.wct2.desc1=The &bWireless Crafting Terminal&r (which comes from an addon, &eWireless Crafting Terminal 2&r, not AE2) is an upgraded Wireless Terminal that has a 3x3 crafting grid.
ftbuniversity.wct2.desc2=Additionally, it can store 4 View Cells, has slots for your armor and baubles, has a trash can slot, and has slots for an &6Infinity Booster Card&r and &6Magnet Card&r, each of which are explained in their own quests.
ftbuniversity.wct2.desc3=Additionally additionally, you can wear the WCT as a bauble and access it using a keybind. The control name is "Open Wireless Crafting Terminal."

ftbuniversity.magnetcard.subtitle=Make a Magnet Card
ftbuniversity.magnetcard.desc1=A &bMagnet Card&r can be installed to the WCT to allow it to automatically insert picked up items into the ME network, instead of your inventory.
ftbuniversity.magnetcard.desc2=When installed, the WCT gets two new buttons: on the right, you can &6toggle&r the Magnet Card; directly above the Card slot, you can edit the Card's &6filter&r.
ftbuniversity.magnetcard.desc3=In the Magnet Filter GUI, you can add up to 27 items to be in either a whitelist of items to insert or a blacklist of items to not insert. You can also set it to ignore damage/nbt and use the ore dictionary.

ftbuniversity.infinitybooster.subtitle=Get an Infinity Booster Card
ftbuniversity.infinitybooster.desc=The &bInfinity Booster Card&r, dropped by the Wither and Ender Dragon, can be installed onto the WCT to give it an &6infinite range&r that also works &6across dimensions&r.

ftbuniversity.meioport.title=MEIOP
ftbuniversity.meioport.subtitle=Make an ME IO Port
ftbuniversity.meioport.desc1=The &bME IO Port&r lets you &6empty or fill a Storage Cell&r using the network.
ftbuniversity.meioport.desc2=This is particularly useful if, for instance, you are upgrading a Cell and need to empty it first. In that case, use &6Transfer data to Network&r.
ftbuniversity.meioport.desc3=Another use would be if you partition a Cell, and then want to make sure only that Cell has those items. In this case, use &6Transfer Data to Storage Cell&r.

ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.title=Spatial Storage is Complex, So This Quest is &lLong&r
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.subtitle=Make a Spatial Containment Structure
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc1=The &bSpatial Containment Structure&r is a multiblock that allows you to take an area in the world and store it digitally.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc2=Each &bSpatial Storage Cell&r can only hold a specific volume. A 2Â³ Cell can hold, at most, a 2x2x2 volume. A 16Â³ Cell holds up to 16x16x16, and so on.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc3=To set the volume to be moved, place 3 &bSpatial Pylons&r strips along the X, Y, and Z directions, branching off from a corner.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc4=To better visualize, &6imagine a cube&r. &6Three edges&r of the cube should be Spatial Pylons, and in &6the corner where they meet&r should be either a Cable or the Spatial IO Port.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc5=The volume to be stored in the Cell is a smaller cube, &6one layer deeper&r than the full cube.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc6=If using a 2Â³ cube, the outer cube would be 4x4x4, with 9 Spatial Pylons (3 on each side). If they are placed correctly, they will glow purple. If not, they will glow red.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc7=Spatial Pylons are &6extremely power-hungry&r, so you may need to provide the system some &6Dense Energy Cells&r.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc8=You can make them more efficient by adding more rows of Spatial Pylons. Break any second Pylon in an existing corner, replace it with a Cable, and then from there place a line of Pylons according to how large the volume is.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc9=All Spatial Pylons in the network are assumed to be in the same SCS, so you should probably &6isolate each to their own subnetwork&r.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc10=Once the Spatial Pylons are set up, connect a &bSpatial IO Port&r. Insert a Spatial Storage Cell in the left slot, give it a redstone pulse, and it will store the blocks in the SCS, removing them from the world. The Cell is moved to the output slot after.
ftbuniversity.spatialcontainment.desc11=The Cell technically doesn't just store the blocks; instead, it &6swaps what it currently has&r with what's in the SCS.

ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.title=Breaking and Placing
ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.subtitle=Make ME Annihilation/Formation Planes
ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.desc1=The &bME Annihilation Plane&r &6destroys the block it is facing&r, placing the drops into the ME network.
ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.desc2=It &6cannot be filtered&r, but will only break blocks if it has &6somewhere to put them&r. That means, if Cells are partitioned to not accept it, it will not be broken.
ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.desc3=The &bME Formation Plane&r will &6instantly place any block that is added to the network&r. As such, it pretty much &6has to be in its own subnetwork&r.
ftbuniversity.ae2breakplace.desc4=You can set a &6whitelist&r of what it can place (which can be increased with &6Capacity Cards&r), as well as toggle if blocks are placed or &6dropped as items&r.

ftbuniversity.ae2silk.title=Ego Death
ftbuniversity.ae2silk.subtitle=Make an ME Identity Annihilation Plane&r
ftbuniversity.ae2silk.desc=The &bME Identity Annihilation Plane&r works just like a regular Annihilation Plane, but applies &6Silk Touch&r.

ftbuniversity.mattercompressor.title=What's the Matter Compressor?
ftbuniversity.mattercompressor.subtitle=Make a Matter Compressor
ftbuniversity.mattercompressor.desc1=The &bMatter Compressor&r &6destroys items/fluids&r, condensing them into either &6Matter Balls&r or &6Singularities&r. Or, ya know, just deleting them.
ftbuniversity.mattercompressor.desc2=Insert a Storage Component into the top slot, click the button on the right to choose what you're making, and then just pump it full of trash.

ftbuniversity.mattercannon.subtitle=Make a Matter Cannon
ftbuniversity.mattercannon.desc1=The &bMatter Cannon&r shoots certain items as projectiles, dealing damage.
ftbuniversity.mattercannon.desc2=In order of damage, these items are &6Matter Balls&r, &6Iron Nuggets&r, &6Tin Nuggets&r and &6Lead Nuggets&r. The damage ranges from 1 to 11 hearts.
ftbuniversity.mattercannon.desc3=To load the Matter Cannon, &6treat it like a Storage Cell&r and insert the specific item into it. The most convenient way for this would be an ME Chest.
ftbuniversity.mattercannon.desc4=Additionally, projectiles will break blocks. More powerful ammo will break more.

ftbuniversity.colorapplicator.subtitle=Make a Color Applicator
ftbuniversity.colorapplicator.desc1=The &bColor Applicator&r uses &bPaint Balls&r to paint blocks. In particular, it can &6paint ME Cables&r.
ftbuniversity.colorapplicator.desc2=To &6load Paint Balls&r in, &6treat the Color Applicator like a Storage Cell&r and insert the Paint Balls in there. The most convenient way to do this would be an ME Chest.
ftbuniversity.colorapplicator.desc3=You can swap between different color Paint Balls inside by scrolling while sneaking.
ftbuniversity.colorapplicator.task=Paint Balls

ftbuniversity.quantumring.title=Quantum Network Bridge
ftbuniversity.quantumring.subtitle=Make a Quantum Network Bridge
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc1=The &bNetwork Bridge&r is a multiblock that works in pairs to allow you to wirelessly connect to ME networks at a distance.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc2=Make a ring of 8 &bME Quantum Rings&r around an &bME Quantum Link Chamber&r to form the multiblock.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc3=To link two Quantum Network Bridges, &bthrow down a Singularity and Ender Dust&r, and cause an &6explosion nearby&r. This will create a pair of linked &bQuantum Entangled Singularities&r.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc4=It would be a good idea to rename these in an Anvil, so as not to confuse them with other pairs.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc5=Insert one Quantum Entangled Singularity into each Quantum Link Chamber to connect them.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc6=&6Jumpstart the distant Bridge&r with some power to turn it on, at which point it will start drawing power from the home Bridge.
ftbuniversity.quantumring.desc7=At this point, connecting ME Cables to one of the 4 center Bridge blocks, and it will be on the same network as the other end.

ftbuniversity.meinterface.subtitle=Make an ME Interface
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc1=The &bME Interface&r is probably the most powerful device.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc2=Any item piped into it will instantly be sent to the ME network.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc3=You can insert an item (including the amount) into one of the &6Config&r slots, and it will always try to keep that many available to be pulled out.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc4=With the above two in mind, the Interface can &6function as both an Import &oand&r&6 Export Bus&r at the same time. You can set up to 9 items to store in the Interface and then pipe out, and then also pipe items into the Interface to enter the system!
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc5=Certain mods will treat the the ME Interface as a &6chest containing everything in the network&r. Most don't, however.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc6=Notably, you can &6point a Storage Bus from another network at it&r, and the other network will be able to access everything in the Interface's network, but not vice versa. This smaller network (the one with the Interface) is called a &6subnetwork&r.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.desc7=The main reason you would use ME Interfaces, however, is &6autocrafting&r. That is explained in the quests above.
ftbuniversity.meinterface.task=ME Interface

ftbuniversity.mepattern.subtitle=Make an ME Pattern Terminal
ftbuniversity.mepattern.desc1=The &bME Pattern Terminal&r allows you to set a recipe in its crafting grid, then &6encode&r the pattern to a &bBlank Pattern&r.
ftbuniversity.mepattern.desc2=You can also set if the recipe is allowed to use the ore dictionary.
ftbuniversity.mepattern.desc3=You can also toggle from &6Crafting Patterns&r, which just do normal crafting recipes, to &6Processing Patterns&r, which sends items out of the network to be processed externally.
ftbuniversity.mepattern.desc4=With Processing Patterns, you can set up to &69 item inputs&r and &63 item outputs&r, as well as the amount of each.
ftbuniversity.mepattern.desc5=Encoded Patterns are inserted into ME Interfaces. For Crafting Patterns, the Interface has to &6aim at a Molecular Assembler&r. For Processing Patterns, the Interface has to &6aim at any inventory&r, as long as the final result is inserted into the network from any source after.

ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.title=Crafting CPU
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.subtitle=Make a Crafting CPU
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.desc1=The &bCrafting CPU&r is a multiblock machine that manages a single auto-craft task from start to finish.
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.desc2=The CPU must be a cuboid, with at least 1 &bCrafting Co-Processing Unit&r and some &bCrafting Storage&r. &bCrafting Units&r are simply a filler block.
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.desc3=The &6more Crafting Co-Processing Units&r, the &6more subtasks&r it can handle at once. For instance, if making a Bookcase, it can do Logâ†’Planks at the same time as Paper+Leatherâ†’Books (assuming those recipes also exist in the network).
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.desc4=Complex recipes require more Crafting Storage.
ftbuniversity.craftingcpu.task=Crafting Storage

ftbuniversity.craftingmonitor.subtitle=Make a Crafting Monitor
ftbuniversity.craftingmonitor.desc=The &bCrafting Monitor&r can be incorporated into a Crafting CPU and it will display the current crafting task.

ftbuniversity.interfaceterminal.subtitle=Make an ME Interface Terminal
ftbuniversity.interfaceterminal.desc1=The &bME Interface Terminal&r will show all ME Interfaces on the network, allowing you to add/remove recipes at a distance.
ftbuniversity.interfaceterminal.desc2=Fun fact: you can &6rename Interfaces&r in an Anvil! That way, you could aim a renamed Interface at a Chest, then from there have pipes and stuff that automates the recipe externally, but the Interface Terminal would show its name instead of "Chest."

ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.subtitle=Make a Molecular Assembler
ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.desc1=The &bMolecular Assembler&r automatically crafts items using Encoded Patterns.
ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.desc2=When used with an ME Interface, it will use its Patterns.
ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.desc3=They can technically be used standalone, but then they can only have one Pattern.
ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.desc4=Either way, Molecular Assemblers &6do not take up Channels&r, though it can carry them.
ftbuniversity.molecularassemblar.desc5=You can add &6Acceleration Cards&r to them, making them craft items faster.

ftbuniversity.p2p1.title=Point-to-Point
ftbuniversity.p2p1.subtitle=Make a P2P Tunnel
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc1=&bP2P&r is one of the more complex (and definitely the most useful) concepts in AE2.
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc2=A pair of &bP2P Tunnels&r will essentially teleport certain things from one end to the other. You can only have one input tunnel, but several output tunnels.
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc3=The most common one is the &bP2P Tunnel - ME&r, which &6teleports channels&r.
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc4=Being able to teleport connections is staggeringly powerful. A pair of P2P Tunnels only use 2 channels, but can transfer 32 channels through them.
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc5=That means a single Dense Cable carrying only P2P Tunnels, each carrying separate full Dense Cables, can carry 32*32 channels. That's &61024 channels &nthrough a single Cable&r!
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc6=Sneak right-click on the P2P Tunnel you wish to be the input with a &bMemory Card&r, then right-click all the outputs with it to connect them.
ftbuniversity.p2p1.desc7=P2P channels &ccannot carry P2P channels&r.

ftbuniversity.p2p2.title=Maximizing Your Network
ftbuniversity.p2p2.subtitle=Learn what makes P2P &ocomplex&r
ftbuniversity.p2p2.desc1=To make the &bmost out of P2P&r, you're going to need to make &6two different ME networks&r.
ftbuniversity.p2p2.desc2=One Controller multiblock is the main one, with &6every visible face attached to an input P2P Tunnel - ME&r.
ftbuniversity.p2p2.desc3=The second Controller Multiblock would support &6the ME Cables powering the P2P&r.
ftbuniversity.p2p2.desc4=Use regular Cables to &6connect all the input P2Ps to a Dense Cable&r, then to the &6second Controller&r, and then just &6branch that to everywhere&r you want to use channels. Go down to a non-Dense Cable, &6smack an output P2P Tunnel on it, and then connect the Cables to that&r.

ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.title=I Teleported Bread
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.subtitle=Learn about other types of P2P
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc1=There are several other kinds of &bP2P Tunnel aside from ME&r. To get them, right-click certain items on an ME Tunnel. They stay that type when picked up with a Wrench.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc2=&bFE&r: Click with &6any RF cable&r. It teleports RF from the input and spreads it across all outputs.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc3=&bFluid&r: Click with a &6Bucket&r. It teleports fluids from the input and spreads it across all outputs.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc4=&bEU&r: Click with &6any EU cable&r. It teleports EU from the input and spreads it across all outputs.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc5=&bItem&r: Click with a &6Hopper, or anything that moves items&r. It teleports items from the input to outputs sequentially.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc6=&bRedstone&r: Click with &6anything Redstone&r. It teleports redstone signals from the input to all outputs equally.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc7=&bLight&r: Click with a &6Torch or Glowstone&r. It reads the light level of the input and then emits that light level out of all outputs. Kind of useful if you put the input outside facing the sun, so the outputs all show about what time of day it is.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.desc8=To get back to &bME&r, click it with an ME Cable.
ftbuniversity.p2pstyles.task=All P2P Tunnels

ftbuniversity.meessentia.title=Digital Magic
ftbuniversity.meessentia.subtitle=Make an ME Essentia Storage Cell
ftbuniversity.meessentia.desc1=The mod &eThaumic Energistics&r bridges the gap between Thaumcraft and AE2, allowing you to &6store Essentia digitally&r.
ftbuniversity.meessentia.desc2=Essentia is stored in &bME Essentia Storage Cells&r.
ftbuniversity.meessentia.task=Any ME Essentia Storage Cell

ftbuniversity.essentiaterminal.subtitle=Make an ME Essentia Terminal
ftbuniversity.essentiaterminal.desc1=The &bME Essentia Terminal&r allows you to manually &6insert and extract Essentia&r from the ME network.
ftbuniversity.essentiaterminal.desc2=To &6insert Essentia&r, grab a filled Phial in your cursor and click it anywhere in the top slots.
ftbuniversity.essentiaterminal.desc3=To &6extrat Essentia, grab an empty Glass Phial in your cursor and click it on an Aspect.

ftbuniversity.mearcane.subtitle=Make an Arcane Crafting Terminal
ftbuniversity.mearcane.desc1=The &bArcane Crafting Terminal&r has all the combined functionality of an &6Arcane Workbench&r and &6ME Crafting Terminal&r.
ftbuniversity.mearcane.desc2=It has &66 slots for primal Vis Crystals&r and can use &6atmospheric Vis&r.
ftbuniversity.mearcane.desc3=You can install an &6Arcane Charging Upgrade&r to make it function as if a &6Workbench Charger&r was installed.

ftbuniversity.essentiabus.title=Essentia IO
ftbuniversity.essentiabus.subtitle=Make the various Essentia Busses
ftbuniversity.essentiabus.desc=The &bME Essentia Import Bus&r, &bME Essentia Export Bus&r, and &bME Essentia Storage Bus&r all work exactly like the item forms, but using Essentia instead.
ftbuniversity.essentiabus.task=ME Essentia Busse

ftbuniversity.meinfusion.subtitle=Make an Essentia Infusion Provider
ftbuniversity.meinfusion.desc=The &bEssentia Infusion Provider&r acts as a source of Essentia for the &6Infusion Altar&r, providing it access to the &6Essentia stored in your network&r.

ftbuniversity.mecircetch.title=M.C. Etcher
ftbuniversity.mecircetch.subtitle=Make an ME Circuit Etcher
ftbuniversity.mecircetch.desc=The &bME Circuit Etcher&r can make Processors from their base ingredients, &6without making Printed Circuits&r. Additionally, each slot can have an entire stack rather than a single item.

ftbuniversity.lazyae2gen.desc1=It can accept an &6Acceleration Card&r. At the top right of the GUI, you can choose the input/output of every face.
ftbuniversity.lazyae2gen.desc2=This is from &eLazy AE2&r, an addon.

ftbuniversity.pulsecent.subtitle=Make a Pulse Centrifuge
ftbuniversity.pulsecent.desc=The &bPulse Centrifuge&r performs in-world crystal seed growing operations, &6purifying Crystals of all types&r.

ftbuniversity.fluixagg.subtitle=Make a Fluix Aggregator
ftbuniversity.fluixagg.desc=The &bFluix Aggregator&r performs in-world Fluix Crystal crafting operations, among certain other recipes.

ftbuniversity.levmain.subtitle=Make an ME Level Maintainer
ftbuniversity.levmain.desc1=The &bME Level Maintainer&r will &6automatically create crafting processes&r when specified items are &6below a specified threshold&r.
ftbuniversity.levmain.desc2=Place up to 5 items in the left slots, set the minimum amount to maintain in the center, then how many it tries to craft on the right.

ftbuniversity.pau.subtitle=Make a Preemptive Assembly Unit
ftbuniversity.pau.desc1=The &bPreemptive Assembly Unit&r works like an ME Interface. It can be given 9 recipes, 9 items to keep supplied, and has 9 input slots.
ftbuniversity.pau.desc2=However, the PAU &6tries to output the max amount of items it can&r, rather than waiting until a recipe is completed.

ftbuniversity.massass.title=Mass Assembler
ftbuniversity.massass.subtitle=Make a Mass Assembler
ftbuniversity.massass.desc1=The &bMass Assembler&r is a multiblock machine that &6functions like a Molecular Assembler&r, but is &6faster&r and holds &6more recipes&r.
ftbuniversity.massass.desc2=Every edge has to be made out of &bMass Assembler Frames&r, and the faces have to be made out of &bMass Assembler Vents&r.
ftbuniversity.massass.desc3=Inside, every block must be either an &bMA Pattern Provider&r or an &bMA Crafting Coprocessor&r. Each Pattern Provider adds 36 slots for patterns, and each Crafting Coprocessor makes it faster.
ftbuniversity.massass.desc4=One &bMass Assembler Controller&r must be placed on one of the walls, replacing a Vent. This is where Cables are connected. Right-click it to form the multiblock.

ftbuniversity.packauto.title=PackagedAuto
ftbuniversity.packauto.subtitle=Learn how to use PackagedAuto
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc1=&ePackagedAuto&r is an AE2 addon that allows you to make &6autocraft recipes that use more than 9 items&r.
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc2=To begin with, place down a &bPackage Recipe Encoder&r. Place 2 &bPackage Recipe Holders&r into the top left slot. Each can hold up to 20 recipes.
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc3=On the right side of the GUI, you can cycle through all the different crafting recipe options. &6Processing&r will simply dump all ingredients at once, &6Ordered&r will send the items in the order you put them in, then the rest are for &ePackagedExCrafting&r (we'll come back to those later).
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc4=In the bottom slots, set the recipe. Inputs on left, outputs on right. &6You can also use JEI's + button&r to autofill it. Once you are happy with your recipe, click &6Save&r at the top to save it to the Holder.
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc5=Take these 2 Holders with their recipes. Insert one into a &bPackager&r and one into an &bUnpackager&r, both of which must be on the system.
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc6=The recipe will now be available in Terminals etc. Items will enter the Packager, become Recipe Packages, then be sent to the Unpackager, which will unpack them, &6exporting them into an adjacent inventory&r.
ftbuniversity.packauto.desc7=At this point, treat the Unpackager like you would an ME Interface. Place it next to an inventory, then use some other method of crafting items outside of the ME system, then pipe the finished item into the system to complete the crafting operation.

ftbuniversity.packexc.title=PackagedExCrafting
ftbuniversity.packexc.subtitle=Learn how to use PackagedExCrafting
ftbuniversity.packexc.desc1=&ePackagedExCrafting&r is an addon for both &ePackagedAuto&r and &eExtended Crafting&r, designed to bridge the gap between them.
ftbuniversity.packexc.desc2=Essentially, while in the Recipe Encoder, set the recipe type to the Extended Crafting block you want the recipe to use (for instance, set to Advanced for crafting Ultimte Stew), then set the recipe.
ftbuniversity.packexc.desc3=Place down the &bPackage Crafter&r of the type you want to use adjacent to the Unpackager with the Recipe Holder you just made, and it will use that to craft the item.
ftbuniversity.packexc.desc4=If the Package Crafter is connected to the ME system, it will automatically send the craft result to storage, completing the crafting operation.
ftbuniversity.packexc.task=Package Crafters

ftbuniversity.ec2wireless.title=Wireless Fluid/Gas
ftbuniversity.ec2wireless.subtitle=Make a Wireless Fluid or Gas Terminal
ftbuniversity.ec2wireless.desc=&eExtra Cells 2&r adds &bWireless Terminals&r for fluids and gas. They work exactly as you would expect.

ftbuniversity.universalterm.title=All For One
ftbuniversity.universalterm.subtitle=Make any Wireless Universal Terminal
ftbuniversity.universalterm.desc1=The &bWireless Universal Terminal&r can work as any Wireless Terminal you add onto it.
ftbuniversity.universalterm.desc2=It can be crafted by combining (almost) any Terminal with any other Wireless Terminal. You can also add more Terminals by crafting them with the Universal Terminal.
ftbuniversity.universalterm.desc3=Sneak right-click the Universal Terminal to cycle through its types.

##Technology
ftbuniversity.techmods.title=Technology

###Forestry
ftbuniversity.forestrymod.title=Forestry

ftbuniversity.forestrybook.subtitle=Get the Forester's Manual
ftbuniversity.forestrybook.desc1=The &bForester's Manual&r is a fairly comprehensive guide to the mod.
ftbuniversity.forestrybook.desc2=Even though it explains pretty much everything, we are still opligated to make quests.

ftbuniversity.clockworkengine.subtitle=Make a Clockwork Engine
ftbuniversity.clockworkengine.desc1=The &bClockwork Engine&r can be wound by holding right-click on it, then will &6generate RF when released&r. The longer you use it, the longer it works. If you hold it too long, &cyou will take damage&r.
ftbuniversity.clockworkengine.desc2=Holding right-click until damaged then immediately letting go will generate &6a little over 25,000RF&r. All in all, it's not great, but it's alright for early-game when you can't afford anything better.

ftbuniversity.biogasengine.subtitle=Make a Biogas Engine
ftbuniversity.biogasengine.desc1=The &bBiogas Engine&r uses Lava to heat up an organic fluid (Biomass, Milk, etc) and then generates energy from that. It requires a redstone signal to run.
ftbuniversity.biogasengine.desc2=For reference, a bucket of &6Water generates 10,000RF&r and a bucket of &6Forestry's Biomass (not IC2's) generates 125,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.peatfiredengine.subtitle=Make a Peat-fired Engine
ftbuniversity.peatfiredengine.desc1=The &bPeat-fired Engine&r generates RF from Peat, which is made by placing Bog Earth next to Water for some time.
ftbuniversity.peatfiredengine.desc2=A single regular &6Peat generates 50,000RF&r, and &6Bituminous Peat generates 120,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.electricalengine.subtitle=Make an Electrical Engine
ftbuniversity.electricalengine.desc1=The &bElectrical Engine&r generates RF using &6IndustrialCraft 2's energy, EU&r.
ftbuniversity.electricalengine.desc2=One Coal burned in an IC2 Generator &6(4,000EU) generates about 16,000RF&r. A small amount is used to get it running at full speed.

ftbuniversity.forestrycarpenter.title=Connor the Carpenter
ftbuniversity.forestrycarpenter.subtitle=Make a Carpenter
ftbuniversity.forestrycarpenter.desc1=The &bCarpenter&r uses &6items and fluids for crafting recipes&r, as well as RF.
ftbuniversity.forestrycarpenter.desc2=&6Set the recipe&r using the grid in the top left, then &6put the ingredients in the bottom slots&r. Some recipes may require a specific fluid to be present in its tank, and some recipes may require specific items be in the top middle slot.
ftbuniversity.forestrycarpenter.desc3=If all the item and fluid ingredients are in and a valid recipe is set, it will use RF to craft the item.

ftbuniversity.thermionicfabricator.title=That Machine Every Expert Pack Uses
ftbuniversity.thermionicfabricator.subtitle=Make a Thermionic Fabricator
ftbuniversity.thermionicfabricator.desc1=The &bThermionic Fabricator&r uses RF to make &6Liquid Glass&r out of any Sand/Glass-type blocks, which it uses in recipes.
ftbuniversity.thermionicfabricator.desc2=Put the Sand or &6Glass in the top right&r slot, set a &6recipe in the top middle&r slots, then put the &6ingredients in the bottom&r. If the recipe is valid, it will heat up the Glass and then craft the item. Some recipes might require an &6additional item in the top right slot&r.
ftbuniversity.thermionicfabricator.desc3=&6It will not craft items if the output slot is not empty&r, so you should automate that.&r It also has a small, constant draw of RF to keep the Liquid Glass molten. A redstone signal will disable this.

ftbuniversity.forestryfermenter.title=Eco-friendly
ftbuniversity.forestryfermenter.subtitle=Make a Fermenter
ftbuniversity.forestryfermenter.desc1=The &bFermenter&r will mix specific combinations of items and fluids to &6create Biomass&r.
ftbuniversity.forestryfermenter.desc2=Liquid Honey and Fruit Juice make 50%% more Biomass than Water. More "complex" natural items (especially Forestry saplings) also generate more Biomass.

ftbuniversity.forestrybottler.title=Bottled Up
ftbuniversity.forestrybottler.subtitle=Make a Bottler
ftbuniversity.forestrybottler.desc=The &bBottler&r can &6fill and empty fluid containers&r. Place a full container in the top left slot to empty it, and place an empty container in the top right to fill it.

ftbuniversity.forestrymoistener.title=My Evil Moisture Buddy
ftbuniversity.forestrymoistener.subtitle=Make a Moistener
ftbuniversity.forestrymoistener.desc1=The &bMoistener&r can be used to &6create Mycelium, Podzol, Mossy Cobblestone, and the like&r.
ftbuniversity.forestrymoistener.desc2=&6Give it water and Wheat&r to allow it to work. This will create Mouldy and Decaying Wheat, which can be cycled through again to create Mulch.

ftbuniversity.forestrysqueezer.title=Juicer
ftbuniversity.forestrysqueezer.subtitle=Make a Squeezer
ftbuniversity.forestrysqueezer.desc=The &bSqueezer&r uses RF to &6squeeze fluids out of items&r.

ftbuniversity.forestrystill.title=Moonshine and Sunshine
ftbuniversity.forestrystill.subtitle=Make a Still
ftbuniversity.forestrystill.desc=The &bStill&r &6converts Biomass to Ethanol&r for use in a Biogas Engine, at a rate of 10:3.

ftbuniversity.forestryrainmaker.title=Make it Rain
ftbuniversity.forestryrainmaker.subtitle=Make a Rainmaker
ftbuniversity.forestryrainmaker.desc=The &bRainmaker&r can &6start and stop storms&r using Iodine Capsules or Dissipation Charges.

ftbuniversity.forestryraintank.subtitle=Make a Rain Tank
ftbuniversity.forestryraintank.desc=The &bRain Tank&r &6fills with water when rained on&r, and automatically outputs it through the bottom.

ftbuniversity.habitatformer.subtitle=Make a Habitat Former
ftbuniversity.habitatformer.desc1=The &bHabitat Former&r can &6change the climate in an area around it&r, which is useful for bees and trees. Set the area using the slider and button at the top right of the GUI.
ftbuniversity.habitatformer.desc2=You can manually set the target temeprature and humidity, choose it out of a list of presets, or insert a bee to automatically adjust to its preferred climate.
ftbuniversity.habitatformer.desc3=Lava is needed to raise the temperature and lower the humidity, and Water/Crushed Ice does the opposite.
ftbuniversity.habitatformer.desc4=You can sneak right-click a &6Habitat Screen&r on the Habitat Former to &6see the working area&r.

ftbuniversity.managedfarms.title=Do It For Me
ftbuniversity.managedfarms.subtitle=Make a Managed Farm
ftbuniversity.managedfarms.desc=&bManaged Farms&r are the easiest to set up. Give them soil, the base plant (seeds, saplings, etc), water, Fertilizer, and RF. It will &6automatically place the soil and seeds&r (and saplings etc), and then &6automatically harvest them&r when grown.
ftbuniversity.singleblockfarms.desc=These Farms function in a &6donut-ish shape&r. The outer limit is a 15x15 square, and the inner limit is 9x9. That leaves a 3 wide path for the farm to work in.
ftbuniversity.managedfarms.task=Any Managed Farm

ftbuniversity.manualfarms.title=I'll Do It Myself
ftbuniversity.manualfarms.subtitle=Make a Manual Farm
ftbuniversity.manualfarms.desc=&bManual Farms&r are a bit more complex to set up. They &6will not place the soil or plant new seeds at the start&r, but will still automatically harvest and replant.
ftbuniversity.manualfarms.task=Any Manual Farm

ftbuniversity.multifarms.title=The Fancy Stuff
ftbuniversity.multifarms.subtitle=Make a Multifarm
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc1=&bMultifarms&r are multiblock machines that can &6farm pretty much any kind of plant&r, from crops to trees to mushrooms. They need Water, Fertilizer, and Soil (generally Dirt) to function.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc2=Multifarms must always be 4 blocks tall, and the sides can be anywhere from 3 to 5 blocks long in either direction (so 3x3x4, 3x4x4, 5x5x4 etc are all valid).
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc3=The Multifarm blocks can be made out of different materials.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc4=The &bFarm Gearbox&r accepts power.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc5=The &bFarm Hatch&r can input and output items.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc6=The &bFarm Valve&r accepts Water.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc7=The &bFarm Control&r allows for redstone control over the farm (see Forester's Manual).
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc8=The rest of the Multifarm must be made out of &bbase Farm Blocks&r
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc9=&6(Technically a Multifarm only needs a Gearbox and base Farm Blocks, but the rest are required for automation and control.)&r
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc10=The smallest Multifarm has a &6diamond-shaped working area&r, extending 7 blocks from each side, connecting diagonally (&6see Manual&r). The biggest Multifarm would extend 11 blocks.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc11=Using any Farm block material (Stone Bricks etc), &6place down the pattern you want the Farm to work in&r, and it will automatically place Humus when it has Dirt and Water.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.desc12=By default, the Multifarm will only work with trees. See the next quest to change this.
ftbuniversity.multifarms.task1=Any base Farm Block
ftbuniversity.multifarms.task2=Any Farm Gearbox
ftbuniversity.multifarms.task3=Any Farm Hatch
ftbuniversity.multifarms.task4=Any Farm Valve
ftbuniversity.multifarms.task5=Any Farm Control

ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.title=Multifarm Control
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.subtitle=Configure a Circuit Board
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.desc1=Multifarms can be configured to change what they farm on each side using &bCircuit Boards&r. It has 4 tiers, for a maximum of 4 Electron Tubes. &6Each Electron Tube only changes one side&r, so to change them all from trees you would have to have the Intricate Circuit Board.
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.desc2=Each &bElectron Tube&r allows the Multifarm to &6farm a different plant&r. You can see these by holding shift while hovering over them, and reading their tooltip.
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.desc3=To install Electron Tubes onto a Circuit Board, right-click a &bSoldering Iron&r. Tab over to the kind of Board you want (generally Automatic Farm), and &6place the Electron Tubes into the slots&r (each slot being a cardinal direction).
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.desc4=Drag and drop the Circuit Board into &6center slot in the top left of the Multifarm GUI&r to install it.
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.task1=Any Circuit Board
ftbuniversity.multifarmcontrol.task2=Any Electron Tube

ftbuniversity.beeguide.title=NOT THE BEES
ftbuniversity.beeguide.subtitle=Start the long, long process of learning how Bees work
ftbuniversity.beeguide.desc1=Forestry &bbees&r are one of the most famous aspects of the mod scene in general.
ftbuniversity.beeguide.desc2=&6Bees give you Honey and Beeswax&r, which are pretty cool I guess. &6&oCool bees&r&6 give you Diamonds, Dragon Eggs, and potion effects when nearby&r.
ftbuniversity.beeguide.desc3=The path to cool bees is a long and complex one, but ultimately worth it. Bees will either consume your life completely or completely turn you off of the game for a year, until the PTSD fades into a distant memory.

ftbuniversity.beescoop.title=Why Can't We Bee Friends
ftbuniversity.beescoop.subtitle=Make a Scoop and a Bee Smoker
ftbuniversity.beescoop.desc1=Obviously, in order to be a beekeeper, you need some bees. Find a Hive of any kind anywhere in the world and mine it with a &bScoop&r.
ftbuniversity.beescoop.desc2=Naturally this will make the bees inside very angry, and they will come out to attack you. You can spray the Hive down with a &bBee Smoker&r to calm them down.
ftbuniversity.beescoop.desc3=This will net you some bees and possibly Honeycomb. The type of bee will depend on the Hive harvested. You'll want to get &6Princess&r and a good amount of &6Drones&r to begin with.
ftbuniversity.beescoop.task=Scoops
ftbuniversity.beescoop.rewards=Hives

ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.title=So What &lAre&r Bees?
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.subtitle=Learn about Bees
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.desc1=Bees come in two types, &bPrincesses&r and &bDrones&r, both of which are required. They are combined in an &6Apiary&r to create a &6Queen&r, which will then do the work.
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.desc2=The Queen will stay in its Apiary generating items. Upon its death, it will &6always give a single Princess&r and has a &6chance to give multiple Drones&r. This means if you ever want to get more Princesses, you have to get them from Hives in the world.
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.desc3=When two bees of &6different species are bred&r, there is a chance that the resultant Queen will birth an &6entirely new species&r, based on the originals. You can see these combinations and their mutation chance by &6checking their recipes in JEI&r.
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.desc4=For bees to "work," they need specific &6flowers&r, &6biome temperature&r, and (usually) &6light&r and &6access to sunlight&r.
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.task1=Any Princess
ftbuniversity.beeexplanation1.task2=Any Drone

ftbuniversity.beealyzer.subtitle=Make a Portable Analyzer
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc1=Bees have several traits that change how they work. The &bPortable Analyzer&r lets you see them, by inserting any bee along with some &6Honey Drops or Honeydew&r.
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc2=Bees have two types of traits: &6active&r and &6inactive&r. Active traits define how they work, and inactive traits can be passed down with breeding, possibly turning active. Red traits are &4dominant&r, and more likely to be passed down, and blue traits are &9recessive&r.
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc3=These traits are:
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc4=â€¢ &6Lifespan&r
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc5=â€¢ &6Production&r (how fast they generate drops)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc6=â€¢ &6Pollination&r (how fast they grow flowers and cross-breed trees)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc7=â€¢ &6Flower Type&r (what block they need to work)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc8=â€¢ &6Fertility&r (how many Drones it creates)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc9=â€¢ &6Territory&r (the size they patrol)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc10=â€¢ &6Effect&r (what they do to players in their territory)
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc11=You can move the bee to the &l&6II&r slot to see what climate and humidity they need, if they work in the day and/or night, if they work in the rain, and if they work underground.
ftbuniversity.beealyzer.desc12=Slots &l&6III&r-&l&6V&r show more information that you probably won't need.

ftbuniversity.ignoblebee.title=Imortalibee
ftbuniversity.ignoblebee.subtitle=Ignoble vs Pristine Stock
ftbuniversity.ignoblebee.desc1=Princesses and Queens can be either &bPristine&r or &bIgnoble Stock&r. &6Ignoble Stock have a chance of not giving a Princess upon death&r. Every generation of Ignoble Stock increases the chance by 2%%.
ftbuniversity.ignoblebee.desc2=It's best to focus on getting as many Drones from Ignoble Stock as possible, and then use those Drones to mutate a Pristine Princess into their species.

ftbuniversity.beemutation.title=It's Hip to Breed Bees
ftbuniversity.beemutation.subtitle=Learn about bee mutation
ftbuniversity.beemutation.desc1=&bMutation&r is the process of breeding two non-identical bees to &6create something new&r. Mutations can change the basic traits (see the Analyzer quest), as well as spawn an entirely new species.
ftbuniversity.beemutation.desc2=Certain &6specific combinations of species&r have a chance to &6mutate into a third species&r. It does not matter which species is the Drone or Princess, as long as they are different. Some mutations have certain &6extra conditions&r, like being in a specific biome.
ftbuniversity.beemutation.desc3=Bee crossbreeding &6shows as a recipe in JEI&r, so you can look at a bee's recipes and uses to see how they're made or what they can make. Hover over the percent chance to see if there are any conditions.

ftbuniversity.beehouse.title=Non GMO
ftbuniversity.beehouse.subtitle=Make a Bee House
ftbuniversity.beehouse.desc1=The &bBee House&r will allow you to work bees with no chance of mutation. This will allow you to just recycle the same princess and drones to get their drops. Bee Houses also cannot be automated.
ftbuniversity.beehouse.desc2=At the top right, you can see the &6current climate&r. At the top left you can see &6anything stopping the Queen from working&r (lack of flowers and wrong climate usually)
ftbuniversity.beehouse.desc3=If you have a Portable Analyzer in your inventory, you can analyze the bees in the Bee House. You can toggle this part of the menu by clicking the button over the bee slots.

ftbuniversity.apiary.subtitle=Make an Apiary
ftbuniversity.apiary.desc1=The &bApiary&r will allow you to work bees while keeping the chance to mutate. This allows you to get cooler, more complex bees.
ftbuniversity.apiary.desc2=The Apiary has room for up to three &bFrames&r, which can effect the Queen's traits (generally increasing production and decreasing the decay of Ignoble Stock).
ftbuniversity.apiary.task=Any Frame

ftbuniversity.apiaristchest.subtitle=Make an Apiarist's Chest
ftbuniversity.apiaristchest.desc1=The &bApiarist's Chest&r has 5 pages of 25 slots each that can &6store bees&r.
ftbuniversity.apiaristchest.desc2=On the left, you can see how many different kinds of bees you've discovered. Hover over a slot to see details on that bee, if it has been scanned in an Analyzer.

ftbuniversity.forestrycentrifuge.subtitle=Make a Centrifuge
ftbuniversity.forestrycentrifuge.desc=The &bCentrifuge&r uses RF to get &6usable materials from the various types of Combs&r.

ftbuniversity.apiaristarmor.title=Bee B Gone
ftbuniversity.apiaristarmor.subtitle=Make Apiarist's clothes
ftbuniversity.apiaristarmor.desc=Wearing an entire set of &bApiarist's clothes&r will stop the negative effects of certain bees.

ftbuniversity.alveary1.title=Weird Alveary
ftbuniversity.alveary1.subtitle=Make an Alveary
ftbuniversity.alveary1.desc1=The &bAlveary&r is essentially a modular multiblock Apiary. It is constructed out of a 3x3x3 cube of Alvery blocks topped by 9 Wood Slabs.
ftbuniversity.alveary1.desc2=On its own, the Alveary actually has less functionality than an Apiary, in that it can't have Frames. However, you can replace any of the Alveary blocks with other blocks, as detailed in the next quest.
ftbuniversity.alveary1.task=9x any Wooden Slab

ftbuniversity.alveary2.subtitle=Make an Alveary upgrade
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc1=These blocks can replace any Alveary block to give additional functionality. These blocks are:
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc2=â€¢ The &bAlveary Swarmer&r uses Royal Jelly to give a small chance of generating a &6Swarm Hive&r nearby, which are like natural hives but only drop Ignoble Stock.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc3=â€¢ The &bAlveary Fan&r uses RF to &6lower the temperature&r by around 20%%.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc4=â€¢ The &bAlveary Heater&r uses RF to &6raise the temperature&r by around 20%%.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc5=â€¢ The &bAlveary Hygroregulator&r will &6raise or lower the humidity&r by around 20%% when given Water or Lava. Crushed Ice will increase humidity by about 40%%, and lower the temperature by about 15%%.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc6=â€¢ The &bAlveary Stabiliser&r will allow Ignoble Stock to last more generations.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.desc7=â€¢ The &bAlveary Sieve&r will intercept Pollen that would have pollinated nearby trees, and gives it to you in item form. This can be clicked on another species of leaves to force them to cross-pollinate. To work it needs Woven Silk, which gets used up when Pollen is removed.
ftbuniversity.alveary2.task=Alveary Upgrades

ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.title=Aboriculture
ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.subtitle=Start tree breeding
ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.desc1=Like bee breeding, Forestry also adds &btree breeding&r. New trees means new textures for your base, as well as new &6fruits&r to eat. They can also be bred to give more fruit and grow them faster.
ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.desc2=Leaves with ripe fruits can be right-clicked to harvest. You can also bonemeal fruit leaves.
ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.desc3=To begin breeding trees, &6analyze two different vanilla saplings and plant them near working bees&r. It will probably take several generations of bees for them to cross-pollinate, so have patience.
ftbuniversity.forestrytrees.task=Any analyzed sapling

ftbuniversity.treetraits.title=Tree Traits
ftbuniversity.treetraits.subtitle=Analyzed Saplings
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc1=Like bees, &bsaplings can be analyzed&r to see their traits. These traits are:
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc2=â€¢ &6Saplings&r (how many saplings you get from its leaves)
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc3=â€¢ &6Matures&r (how fast it takes to grow without bone meal)
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc4=â€¢ &6Height&r
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc5=â€¢ &6Girth&r (how many saplings must be placed for the tree to grow)
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc6=â€¢ &6Yield&r (how many fruits it drops)
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc7=â€¢ &6Sappiness&r (how much Biomass you get from putting the sapling in a Fermenter)
ftbuniversity.treetraits.desc8=â€¢ &6Effect&r (no tree actually has an effect, so just ignore this)

ftbuniversity.treetraits2.title=Extra Trees
ftbuniversity.treetraits2.subtitle=Learn more about trees
ftbuniversity.treetraits2.desc1=Page &bII&r of the Analyzer will show the sapling's secondary traits:
ftbuniversity.treetraits2.desc2=If it's &6fireproof&r, its preferred &6soil&r (which always shows up as plains for some reason), what kind of &6fruit type&r it can support, what kind of &6fruit it currently has&r, and what &6fruit family that is&r.
ftbuniversity.treetraits2.desc3=If a tree is bred that has has the Apple fruit gene, but can't support Apples, it won't grow Apples but can &6pass that gene along to a tree that can&r.
ftbuniversity.treetraits2.desc4=Page &bIII&r shows the fruit, page &bIV&r shows the possible mutations, and page &bV&r shows some flavor text for that sapling.

ftbuniversity.pollinated.title=X-Ray Specs
ftbuniversity.pollinated.subtitle=Make some Spectacles
ftbuniversity.pollinated.desc1=&bSpectacles&r allow you to &6see leaves that have been pollinated&r. Pollinated leaves are lighter in color, and it should say at the top of the screen.
ftbuniversity.pollinated.desc2=The &bGrafter&r gives a &6100%% chance to drop a sapling&r when breaking Forestry leaves.
ftbuniversity.pollinated.task1=Spectacles
ftbuniversity.pollinated.task2=Grafter

ftbuniversity.butterflies.title=Boneless Bees
ftbuniversity.butterflies.subtitle=Butterflies also exist, kind of
ftbuniversity.butterflies.desc1=&6Butterflies&r are pretty much the most obscure, esoteric feature of any mod. Most people don't breed bees, even less people breed &otrees&r, which are the only way to get Butterflies. &6Forestry leaves have a very low chance to spawn a random Butterfly.&r
ftbuniversity.butterflies.desc2=Right-click a Butterfly with a &6Scoop&r to catch it, turning it into an item. &oAllegedly&r, throwing the item on the ground will allow it to return to being a mob, &cthough this appears to not work&r.
ftbuniversity.butterflies.desc3=You can &6mate&r two Butterflies by crafting them together. Once this mated Butterfly is returned to the world and it reaches the end of its lifespan, it will find some Leaves, spawn a Cocoon, and die. Some time later, a new Butterfly will emerge.
ftbuniversity.butterflies.desc4=Like Bees and trees, Butterflies can be &6scanned in the Portable Analyzer&r. Butterflies also &cdo not have any produce&r, they only work to &6spread Pollen&r. And, of course, make your world prettier.0

ftbuniversity.gendustry.title=Gendustry!
ftbuniversity.gendustry.subtitle=Learn about Gendustry
ftbuniversity.gendustry.desc=&eGendustry&r is an addon for Forestry that essentially makes the life of an apiarist a lot easier. Because of that, &cwe're locking it until you've made an Alveary&r, so as to not trivialize it.

ftbuniversity.pollenkit.subtitle=Make a Pollen Collection Kit
ftbuniversity.pollenkit.desc1=The &bPollen Collection Kit&r can be &6used on Leaves to get Pollen of that species&r, which you can use on other Leaves to forcibly crossbreed them.
ftbuniversity.pollenkit.desc2=They are one-use only, and will break after.

ftbuniversity.indusapiary.title=Electric Beekeeping
ftbuniversity.indusapiary.subtitle=Make an Industrial Apiary
ftbuniversity.indusapiary.desc1=The &bIndustrial Apiary&r is essentially a &oway&r better version of the Apiary.
ftbuniversity.indusapiary.desc2=It can't use Frames, but can take &6upgrades&r that make it emulate biomes, let it ignore rain or skylight, reduce bees' lifetimes, or increase their productivity.
ftbuniversity.indusapiary.desc3=It &6requires RF&r to run.

ftbuniversity.genups.title=Oh, Beehave!
ftbuniversity.genups.subtitle=Make an Industrial Apiary Upgrade
ftbuniversity.genups.desc1=The Industrial Apiary has 4 slots for &bUpgrades&r. Some upgrades can be stacked, boosting it even further.
ftbuniversity.genups.desc2=The tooltip of each upgrade will say what they do, and to how high they can stack.
ftbuniversity.genups.task=Any Industrial Apiary Upgrade

ftbuniversity.gencovers.title=Cover Me
ftbuniversity.gencovers.subtitle=Make a Cover
ftbuniversity.gencovers.desc1=&bCovers&r can be placed on any side of a Gendustry machine.
ftbuniversity.gencovers.desc2=The &bItem Eject and Import Covers&r are fairly obvious; the &bError Sensor Cover&r will output a redstone signal whenever the machine has any error.
ftbuniversity.gencovers.task=Any Cover

ftbuniversity.mutaprod.subtitle=Make a Mutagen Producer
ftbuniversity.mutaprod.desc=The &bMutagen Producer&r uses RF to &6convert Redstone into Mutagen&r, which is required for the Mutatron.

ftbuniversity.mutatron.subtitle=Make a Mutatron
ftbuniversity.mutatron.desc1=The &bMutatron&r will allow you to combine a Drone and Princess, &6forcing them to mutate into another species&r.
ftbuniversity.mutatron.desc2=Obviously, the Drone and Princess &ccannot be the same species&r.
ftbuniversity.mutatron.desc3=Each mutation uses up 1,000mB of Mutagen, some RF, and 1 Genetics Labware.

ftbuniversity.advmutatron.title=Why is The m &o&nLowercase&r&o?!&r
ftbuniversity.advmutatron.subtitle=Make an Advanced mutatron
ftbuniversity.advmutatron.desc=The &bAdvanced mutatron&r works exactly the same as the normal Mutatron, except you can &6choose which species to breed into&r.

ftbuniversity.geneticsampler.subtitle=Make a Genetic Sampler
ftbuniversity.geneticsampler.desc1=The &bGenetic Sampler&r will &6take a random chromosome from a bee&r (like its speed, lifespan, etc) and &6get a sample of it&r. This kills the bee.
ftbuniversity.geneticsampler.desc2=It takes one &bBlank Gene Sample&r and &bGenetics Labware&r per gene.

ftbuniversity.genetictemplate.subtitle=Make a Genetic Template
ftbuniversity.genetictemplate.desc1=You can craft Samples with a &bGenetic Template&r to put that gene on the Template.
ftbuniversity.genetictemplate.desc2=There are 13 chromosomes in total, but you do not have to fill them all into the Template.

ftbuniversity.imprinter.title=Non-non-GMO
ftbuniversity.imprinter.subtitle=Make a Genetic Imprinter
ftbuniversity.imprinter.desc1=The &bGenetic Imprinter&r allows you to copy all genes from a Genetic Template onto any bee.
ftbuniversity.imprinter.desc2=This &6requires Genetics Labware&r to work.

ftbuniversity.genetictransposer.subtitle=Make a Genetic Transposer
ftbuniversity.genetictransposer.desc1=The &bGenetic Transposer&r allows you to copy Samples or Templates.
ftbuniversity.genetictransposer.desc2=Put the Sample/Templet you want to copy in the &6top left slot&r, and empty ones in the &6bottom left.&r It also &6requires Genetics Labware&r.

ftbuniversity.proteindna.title=BNA
ftbuniversity.proteindna.subtitle=Make a Protein Liquifier and DNA Extractor
ftbuniversity.proteindna.desc1=The &bProtein Liquifier&r converts &6raw meats into Protein&r fluid.
ftbuniversity.proteindna.desc2=The &bDNA Extractor&r convert &6bees, butterflies, or saplings into Liquid DNA&r. It also requires Genetics Labware.
ftbuniversity.proteindna.rewards=Protein or DNA

ftbuniversity.geneticreplicator.title=Build-a-Bee
ftbuniversity.geneticreplicator.subtitle=Make a Genetic Replicator
ftbuniversity.geneticreplicator.desc=The &bGenetic Replicator&r will use RF, 1,000mB of Liquid DNA, 5,000mB of Protein, and a &ncompletely filled&r Genetic Template to &6create an Ignoble Queen&r.

###Extra Utilities 2
ftbuniversity.extrautils2chap.title=Extra Utilities 2

ftbuniversity.exu2manual.subtitle=Get the Extra Utilities 2 Manual
ftbuniversity.exu2manual.desc1=The &bExtra Utilities 2 Manual&r is a manual for Extra Utilities 2.
ftbuniversity.exu2manual.desc2=It's not a very &ogood&r one, but it's definitely there.

ftbuniversity.exu2drums.title=Octuple Compressed Fluids
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.subtitle=Make a Drum
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc1=&bDrums&r can store an incredibly large amount of a single fluid in a single block. Fludis can be inserted and extracted from any side.
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc2=Drums come in 4 tiers, each storing more than the last. In order, they store:
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc3=&bStone Drum&r: &616,000 mB&r
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc4=&bIron Drum&r: &6256,000 mB&r
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc5=&bReinforced Large Drum&r: &64,096,000&r
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.desc6=&bDemonically Gargantuan Drum&r: &665,563,000&r
ftbuniversity.exu2drums.task=Any Drum

ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.title=Compressum Est
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.subtitle=Compress each block
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.desc1=You can craft 9 Cobblestone, Dirt, Sand, Gravel, or Netherrack together to make a &bCompressed&r version of that block, which you can later uncraft back into the base form.
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.desc2=Some of these have multiple tiers. For instance, &6Octuple Compressed Cobblestone&r can store &n&l43,046,721 Cobblestone&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.task1=Compressed Cobblestone
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.task2=Compressed Dirt
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.task3=Compressed Sand
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.task4=Compressed Gravel
ftbuniversity.exu2compressed.task5=Compressed Netherrack

ftbuniversity.exu2spikes.title=Watch Out for Those Pointy Bits
ftbuniversity.exu2spikes.subtitle=Make a Spike
ftbuniversity.exu2spikes.desc1=&bSpikes&r hurt whatever touches them. Simple enough.
ftbuniversity.exu2spikes.desc2=Spikes come in multiple tiers, which deal more damage and have other special effects, as told by their tooltip.
ftbuniversity.exu2spikes.task=Any Spike

ftbuniversity.exu2enderlily.title=Infinite Ender Pearls, Technically
ftbuniversity.exu2enderlily.subtitle=Find an Ender Lily
ftbuniversity.exu2enderlily.desc1=&bEnder Lillies&r can be rarely found in dungeon chests, but are fairly common in the End.
ftbuniversity.exu2enderlily.desc2=They can be planted on a block and will &overy slowly&r grow, and can eventually be right-clicked to &6harvest a single Ender Pearl&r. They &6grow faster on End Stone&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2potions.title=I Require Your Strongest Potions
ftbuniversity.exu2potions.subtitle=Make any Exu2 Potion
ftbuniversity.exu2potions.desc1=Extra Utilities 2 adds several potions that do pretty neat things. The tooltips should explain most of them, and the name should explain the rest.
ftbuniversity.exu2potions.desc2=You only need to craft one of these for the quest to complete.

ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.title=Deep Underground
ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.subtitle=Make a Deep Dark Portal
ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.desc1=Standing on the &bDeep Dark Portal&r for a couple seconds will teleport you to the Deep Dark dimension, which is an infinitely massive cave.
ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.desc2=You will spawn in a room at the top of the dimension, which has a Portal back. Dig down and make either ladders or a staircase down.
ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.desc3=&cDarkness in the Deep Dark will harm you.&r Make sure to light up your area.
ftbuniversity.exu2deepdark.desc4=The Deep Dark is a pretty &6good place for quarries&r, since you don't have to worry about putting massive holes in the Overworld.

ftbuniversity.exu2clock.subtitle=Make a Redstone Clock
ftbuniversity.exu2clock.desc=The &bRedstone Clock&r emits a redstone pulse every second. It can be disabled with a strong redstone signal (ie a Lever placed directly on it).

ftbuniversity.exu2trash.title=Rubbish
ftbuniversity.exu2trash.subtitle=Make a Trash Can
ftbuniversity.exu2trash.desc=&bTrash Cans&r delete anything piped into them. There are three types: &6item&r, &6fluid&r, and &6energy&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2trash.task=Any Trash Can

ftbuniversity.exu2angel.subtitle=Make an Angel Block
ftbuniversity.exu2angel.desc=The &bAngel Block&r will be placed 1 block away from you in whatever direction you're facing, without having to place it against an existing block. This is especially useful for &6floating structures&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2mechanicals.title=Mechanical Whatsits
ftbuniversity.exu2mechanicals.subtitle=Make the Mechanical blocks
ftbuniversity.exu2mechanicals.desc1=The &bMechanical Crafter&r can be set a crafting recipe, and when it has all the ingredients in the input inventory &6it will craft the item and send it to the output inventory&r to be pumped out. You can set it to require redstone, toggle if ancillatory items (empty buckets etc) are sent to the output, and add Speed Upgrades.
ftbuniversity.exu2mechanicals.desc2=The &bMechanical Miner&r will break the block in front of it, &6putting the drop into its inventory&r. You can give it Speed Upgrades and an Enchanted Book to make it use that enchantment.
ftbuniversity.exu2mechanicals.desc3=The &bMechanical User&r &6simulates a player clicking&r an item in its inventory. You can toggle if it left or right-clicks, what &okind&r of click, and what slot to "hold". You can also give it speed upgrades.

ftbuniversity.exu2dropofevil.subtitle=Get a Drop of Evil
ftbuniversity.exu2dropofevil.desc1=The &bDrop of Evil&r rarely drops from Wither Skeletons and has several uses.
ftbuniversity.exu2dropofevil.desc2=You can click it on Grass to make &bCursed Earth&r, which will spread for a while and very rapidly spawn very powerful monters. It burns in the sun, and gets disabled by light. This is &6great for mob farms&r, though it's best if you save this step until the rest of the grinder is ready.
ftbuniversity.exu2dropofevil.desc3=Since Drops of Evil are so rare, it would be a good idea to spend your first one on a &6mob farm in a Nether Fortress&r, which you can use to get more.
ftbuniversity.exu2dropofevil.desc4=You can click it on a Spawner to make a &bResturbed Mob Spawner&r, which can be toggled with redstone and given &6Speed Upgrades&r. It can also be &6mined with a pickaxe&r without being lost.

ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.title=Terra-Freezing the Planet
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.subtitle=Make a Terraformer
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.desc1=The &bTerraformer&r is a multiblock machine that allows you to &6change the biome of the surrouding area&r, to a maximum radius of 64 blocks.
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.desc2=First, use a &bBiome Marker&r in the biome you want to change to to set it to that biome. Place it in a powered Terraformer where you want to terraform. It will give you a list of &bClimographs&r that must be placed within 4 blocks of the Terraformer (they don't necessarily need to touch).
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.desc3=&6Climographs&r (Humidifiers, Coolers, etc) require an &bAntenna&r be placed on them, energy, and something called &6TF&r. Each climograph has different requirements for TF; a &6Magic Infuser needs magic items&r, a &6Cooler needs cold items&r, etc. You can click the arrow in their GUIs to see what gives them TF.
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.desc4=Once everything is &6powered&r and the required climographs have a &6good source of TF&r, the area surrounding the Terraformer will transform into the biome set by the Marker.
ftbuniversity.exu2terraformer.task=Climographs

ftbuniversity.exu2muffler.title=Superb Sound Muffler
ftbuniversity.exu2muffler.subtitle=Make a Sound Muffler
ftbuniversity.exu2muffler.desc1=The &bSound Muffler&r stops any sound within 8 blocks of itself.
ftbuniversity.exu2muffler.desc2=Shockingly useful; put one near your Nether Portal, mob farms, annoyingly loud machines, anywhere that's too noisy for your tastes.

ftbuniversity.exu2lasso.subtitle=Make the Lassos
ftbuniversity.exu2lasso.desc1=The &bGolden Lasso&r can be right-clicked on a &6passive mob to pick it up&r, and can be placed down later.
ftbuniversity.exu2lasso.desc2=The &bCursed Lasso&r does the same, but works on &6hostile mobs&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2enchanter.subtitle=Make an Enchanter
ftbuniversity.exu2enchanter.desc1=The &bEnchanter&r uses RF and Lapis to enchant items, if it has &615 Bookshelves&r or &66 Magical Wood&r nearby.
ftbuniversity.exu2enchanter.desc2=Combining any enchantable item with a &6Lapis Lazuli will enchant it with a single minimum level enchantment&r; combine the item with a &6Nether Star to get a max level enchantment&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2enchanter.desc3=The Enchanter is also required for certain items, like &6Enchanted Ingots&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2transfernodes.title=Transfer Nodes
ftbuniversity.exu2transfernodes.subtitle=Make a Transfer Node system
ftbuniversity.exu2transfernodes.desc1=&6Transfer Nodes&r will slowly pull items or fluids out of the inventory they are placed in, and will try to send them along a path defined by &bTransfer Pipes&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2transfernodes.desc2=You can click a connection with any Wrench to make that connection &6one way&r. If the connection is blocked on both ways, they completely disconnect.

ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.title=Compact Automation
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.subtitle=Make Flat Transfer Nodes
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.desc1=&6Flat Transfer Nodes&r fit between two adjacent blocks to pull items/fluids from the block it is placed on and push into the block it is facing.
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.desc2=That means you could have a Chest placed directly on top of a Furnace, and a Flat Transfer Node placed between them would transfer items between them.
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.desc3=You can &6hold control to make it pull instead of push&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.desc4=Right-click one with any Wrench to open its GUI, where you can put a Filter. Left-click with a Wrench to break it.
ftbuniversity.exu2flatnodes.task=Either Flat Transfer Node

ftbuniversity.exu2retrieval.title=Pull!
ftbuniversity.exu2retrieval.subtitle=Make Retrieval Nodes
ftbuniversity.exu2retrieval.desc=&bRetrieval Nodes&r work pretty much exactly the same as Transfer Nodes, except they are &6placed on the destination instead of the source&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2filters.subtitle=Make a Filter
ftbuniversity.exu2filters.desc1=&bFilters&r can be placed in Nodes to &6choose what items/fluids are allowed to be moved&r. It has 12 slots, and options for requiring NBT and Metadata, as well as using the Ore Dictionary. It can also be toggled between being a Whitelist and a Blacklist.
ftbuniversity.exu2filters.desc2=You can &6nest Filters&r (putting Filters inside Filters) as well, and have them all function.
ftbuniversity.exu2filters.task=Filters

ftbuniversity.exu2transferfilters.subtitle=Make a Transfer Filter
ftbuniversity.exu2transferfilters.desc=The &bTransfer Filter&r can be placed on an inventory and given a Filter to &6set what is allowed to go into that inventory&r. You can also set the &oamount&r of those items that are allowed.

ftbuniversity.exu2transferpipefilter.subtitle=Make a Transfer Pipe Filter
ftbuniversity.exu2transferpipefilter.desc=A &bTransfer Pipe Filter&r can be placed between two Transfer Pipes and be given a Filter to &6set what items are allowed to pass through&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.title=What's a GP?
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.subtitle=Learn about Grid Power
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc1=&bGrid Power&r is Extra Utilities 2's energy system, which works very different from other mods'.
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc2=Grid Power is &6completely wireless&r and player-specific. Generators and users do not have to be anywhere near each other, so long as the generators are chunk loaded.
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc3=GP users don't use up GP; it's more accurate to say they &ooccupy&r it. Hovering over anything that uses GP shows a fraction: &6(occupied GP)/(total GP)&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc4=If the amount of GP being used is greater than the amount available, &ceverything using GP will stop working&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc5=If you have too many of the same generator, they all become less efficient. You can see the effective power of a mill by hovering over it.
ftbuniversity.exu2learngp.desc6=If you are playing with someone and you want to share GP, use the command &6/xu_powersharing&r. This is one-way though, so both players have to use the command if you want it to go both ways.

ftbuniversity.exu2manualmill.title=It's a Mill.
ftbuniversity.exu2manualmill.subtitle=Make a Manual Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2manualmill.desc1=The &bManual Mill& will generate &615GP&r, but only when used by a player.&r
ftbuniversity.exu2manualmill.desc2=It's not very useful except to power the Resonator, which will allow you to make other, better Mills.

ftbuniversity.exu2solarpanel.title=And This... is a Mill.
ftbuniversity.exu2solarpanel.subtitle=Make a Solar Panel
ftbuniversity.exu2solarpanel.desc=A &bSolar Panel&r will generate &61GP&r when it can see daylight.

ftbuniversity.exu2lunarpanel.title=This, However, is a Mill.
ftbuniversity.exu2lunarpanel.subtitle=Make a Lunar Panel
ftbuniversity.exu2lunarpanel.desc=A &bLunar Panel&r will generate &61GP&r when it can see... nightlight.

ftbuniversity.exu2windmill.title=Surprisingly, It's a Mill.
ftbuniversity.exu2windmill.subtitle=Make a Wind Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2windmill.desc=A &bWind Mill&r generates a &6fairly variable amount of GP&r from the wind. There must not be a block directly to the North/South of it.

ftbuniversity.exu2watermill.title=Mill...
ftbuniversity.exu2watermill.subtitle=Make a Water Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2watermill.desc1=A &bWater Mill&r generates &64GP&r per horizontal side touching flowing water, for a maximum of &616GP&r.
ftbuniversity.exu2watermill.desc2=Water Mills are generally the easiest to spam for the amount of GP they make.

ftbuniversity.exu2lavamill.title=Is It Really a Mill?
ftbuniversity.exu2lavamill.subtitle=Make a Lava Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2lavamill.desc=A &bLava Mill&r generates &62GP&r when next to a Lava source block, &63GP&r when next to the first stage of flowing Lava, &62GP&r when on second, and &61GP&r on third.

ftbuniversity.exu2firemill.title=Behold! A Mill.
ftbuniversity.exu2firemill.subtitle=Make a Fire Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2firemill.desc=A &bFire Mill&r generates &64GP&r when directly over fire.

ftbuniversity.exu2dragoneggmill.title=Eh? What is This?
ftbuniversity.exu2dragoneggmill.subtitle=Make a Dragon Egg Mill
ftbuniversity.exu2dragoneggmill.desc=A &bDragon Egg Mill&r generates &6500GP&r when a Dragon Egg is placed on top of it.

ftbuniversity.exu2resonator.subtitle=Make a Resonator
ftbuniversity.exu2resonator.desc1=The &bResonator&r is the first machine that uses GP. It works a bit like a furnace, but with different recipes.
ftbuniversity.exu2resonator.desc2=&6Put items in, make sure GP is available, get items out.&r

ftbuniversity.redcoal.subtitle=Make some Red Coal
ftbuniversity.redcoal.desc=&bRed Coal&r works better as furnace fuel the more GP it has, up to 700%% (56 items).

ftbuniversity.wirelessrfbattery.subtitle=Make a Wireless RF Battery
ftbuniversity.wirelessrfbattery.desc=Any RF stored in the &bWireless RF Battery&r can be transmitted from &bWireless RF Transmitters&r anywhere in the world to any machine within 4 blocks of itself.

ftbuniversity.exu2screen.title=R390EId
ftbuniversity.exu2screen.subtitle=Make a Screen
ftbuniversity.exu2screen.desc=The &bScreen&r uses a bit of GP to display any (smaller than 256kb) Imgur file in the world.

ftbuniversity.ineffableglass.title=Unable to Eff
ftbuniversity.ineffableglass.subtitle=Make Ineffable Glass
ftbuniversity.ineffableglass.desc1=&bIneffable Glass&r can be walked through. Pretty neat stuff. Sneaking makes it act like normal Glass.
ftbuniversity.ineffableglass.desc2=&b&lDark&r&b Ineffable Glass&r can do the same except, like Dark Glass, doesn't let light through.

ftbuniversity.playerchest.title=It's Like an Ender Chest, Except the Ender is &lYou&r
ftbuniversity.playerchest.subtitle=Make a Player Chest
ftbuniversity.playerchest.desc1=The &bPlayer Chest&r directly connects to &6your inventory&r. In its GUI, you can set the permission for each slot; whether you can extract, insert, both, or neither.
ftbuniversity.playerchest.desc2=This is extremely useful for many things. At your base, you could have something that &6constantly refills a specific slot in your hotbar with Torches&r, or removes full Shulker Boxes from the top right slot, empties them, and puts them back in! The possibilities are only limited to your ingenuity.

ftbuniversity.exu2speed.title=I am Speed
ftbuniversity.exu2speed.subtitle=Make the Speed Upgrades
ftbuniversity.exu2speed.desc1=Most ExU2 machines can be sped up with the &bUpgrade Speed&r. Each installed Upgrade requires slightly more GP than the last, starting at 1.
ftbuniversity.exu2speed.desc2=&mUpgrade Speeds&r &mUpgrades Speed&r Upgrades can only stack up to a specific amount, dictated by the tier. Basic ones can stack to &64&r, Magical can stack to &616&r, and Ultimate can stack to &664&r. 4 basic is the same as 4 Ultimate, the only difference is you can put more in.

ftbuniversity.exu2stack.title=I am Stack
ftbuniversity.exu2stack.subtitle=Make the Upgrade Stack
ftbuniversity.exu2stack.desc=The &bUpgrade Stack&r can be used with Transfer Nodes to extract and move an entire stack of an item at a time.

ftbuniversity.exu2mining.title=Mining Comma Upgrade
ftbuniversity.exu2mining.subtitle=Make the Upgrade Mining
ftbuniversity.exu2mining.desc=The &bUpgrade Mining&r can be installed on a Transfer Node placed on Cobblestone that is touching both Water and Lava sources to make it &6generate Cobblestone&r. Speed Upgrades will make it generate more per tick.

ftbuniversity.exu2rings.title=Fly Like a Bird Squid Angel
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.subtitle=Make the flying Rings
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.desc1=The &bChicken Wing Ring&r allows you to &6slow your fall&r for a time by holding space.
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.desc2=The &bRing of the Flying Squid&r allows you to &6fly into the air&r for a time.
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.desc3=The various &bAngel Rings&r allow infinite &6full creative flight&r. The only difference among them is their looks.
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.desc4=All of these require GP, naturally.
ftbuniversity.exu2rings.task=Any Angel Ring

ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.title=Transvector Something or Other
ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.subtitle=Make an Ender Porcupine
ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.desc1=The &bEnder Porcupine&r will cycle through all the blocks in its working area, mimicking them.
ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.desc2=In its GUI, you can set two corners of a cuboid, which are the X, Y, and Z coordinates relative to the Porcupine.
ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.desc3=The Porcupine will iterate through every block in the working area, which you can see by hovering over it. It requires 1GP for each block away the Porcupine is from the mimicked location.
ftbuniversity.exu2porcupine.desc4=While mimicking a block, you can pipe energy, items, and fluids into and out of the Porcupine and &6it will be treated as if it were the block&r. Mechanical Users and Miners will do the same, when pointed at the Porcupine.

ftbuniversity.exu2fireaxe.title=Mmph Mphna Mprh
ftbuniversity.exu2fireaxe.subtitle=Make a Fire Axe
ftbuniversity.exu2fireaxe.desc1=The &bFire Axe&r will &6chop down the entire tree&r when used. It also has infinite durability.
ftbuniversity.exu2fireaxe.desc2=Its most interesting feature however, is that the &6max limit for enchantments is doubled&r in an Anvil. That means, for instance, you could put Efficiency X on it by adding two Efficiency V books to it.

ftbuniversity.exu2kikoku.title=All According to Kikoku
ftbuniversity.exu2kikoku.subtitle=Make a Kikoku
ftbuniversity.exu2kikoku.desc1=The &bKikoku&r is a very powerful sword; with every strike, the &6maximum health of the victim is lowered&r (though it would take 4 hits to lower it by a single heart).
ftbuniversity.exu2kikoku.desc2=It also does &6void damage&r, which functions like void damage, as well as some &6armor-piercing&r damage.
ftbuniversity.exu2kikoku.desc3=The Kikoku also has &6infinite durability&r and &6enchantments' highest tiers are doubled&r in an Anvil, so you use Enchanted Books on it to get all the way up to Sharpness X and Looting VI!

ftbuniversity.exu2bow.title=Complex Bow
ftbuniversity.exu2bow.subtitle=Make a Compound Bow
ftbuniversity.exu2bow.desc1=The &bCompound Bow&r, when fully drawn, will shoot &6gravity-defying arrows&r. It also has infinite durability.
ftbuniversity.exu2bow.desc2=The Compound Bow's &6enchantments can be double the normal limit&r when installed via an Anvil.

ftbuniversity.exu2survival.subtitle=Make a Survival Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2survival.desc=The &bSurvival Generator&r generates a 5 times the normal amount of RF from furnace fuels, though it works very slowly.
ftbuniversity.exu2gensspeed.desc=This generator can be given the &6Upgrade Speed&r.

ftbuniversity.exu2furnacegen.subtitle=Make a Furnace Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2furnacegen.desc=The &bFurnace Generator&r generates an average amount of RF from furnace fuels at an average speed.

ftbuniversity.exu2overclocked.subtitle=Make an Overclocked Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2overclocked.desc=The &bOverclocked Generator&r generates 1/10th the normal amount of RF from furnace fuels at an extremely high speed.

ftbuniversity.exu2magmatic.subtitle=Make a Magmatic Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2magmatic.desc=The &bMagmatic Generator&r generates RF from Lava, at 100,000 RF per bucket.

ftbuniversity.exu2pink.subtitle=Make a Pink Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2pink.desc=The &bPink Generator&r generates RF from Pink Dye, anything crafted using Pink Dye, and anything that crafts &ointo&r Pink Dye, at 400 RF per item.

ftbuniversity.exu2heatedredstone.subtitle=Make a Heated Redstone Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2heatedredstone.desc=The &bHeated Redstone Generator&r generates RF from Lava and Redstone dust, with 50mB and 1 dust generating 20,000 RF over 6.25 seconds.

ftbuniversity.exu2frosty.subtitle=Make a Frosty Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2frosty.desc=The &bFrosty Generator&r generates RF from blocks like Ice and Snow. See its uses in JEI for a full list.

ftbuniversity.exu2culinary.subtitle=Make a Culinary Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2culinary.desc=The &bCulinary Generator&r generates RF from food, with better food generating more. See its uses in JEI for a full list.

ftbuniversity.exu2explosive.subtitle=Make an Explosive Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2explosive.desc=The &bExplosive Generator&r generates RF from Gunpowder or TNT. This will cause explosions that damage entities but not blocks, so don't put this somewhere you go too often.

ftbuniversity.exu2endergen.subtitle=Make an Ender Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2endergen.desc=The &bEnder Generator&r generates RF from Ender Pearls and Eyes of Ender.

ftbuniversity.exu2potgen.subtitle=Make a Potion Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2potgen.desc=The &bPotion Generator&r generates RF from potions, with more RF for the more steps required. Empty Glass Bottles will have to be piped out.

ftbuniversity.exu2slime.subtitle=Make a SLimey Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2slime.desc=The &bSlimey Generator&r generates RF from Slime and Milk. Empty Buckets will have to be piped out.

ftbuniversity.exu2disenchant.subtitle=Make a Disenchantment Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2disenchant.desc=The &bDisenchantment Generator&r generates RF from Enchanted Books, using a strangely complex formula. In short: the closer it is to the max level, as well as the more rare, the better.

ftbuniversity.exu2halitosis.subtitle=Make a Halitosis Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2halitosis.desc=The &bHalitosis Generator&r generates RF from Dragon's Breath. Empty Glass Bottles will have to be piped out.

ftbuniversity.exu2netherstar.subtitle=Make a Netherstar Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2netherstar.desc=The &bNetherstar Generator&r generates RF from Nether Stars. While working, it will inflict Wither II on nearby living creatures.

ftbuniversity.exu2death.subtitle=Make a Death Generator
ftbuniversity.exu2death.desc=The &bDeath Generator&r generates RF from Bones, Rotten Flesh, and the like. If a player enters a 3x3 area around it, they will get the &cDoom&r effect inflicted on them, which spells &6certain death unless cured&r after 60 seconds.

