###RFTools
ftbuniversity.rftchap.title=RFTools

ftbuniversity.rftbook.subtitle=Get an RFTools Manual
ftbuniversity.rftbook.desc=The &bRFTools Manual&r, as the name implies, is the manual for RFTools. It has words in it, and those words talk about RFTools. It's very cool, I assure you.

ftbuniversity.rftcoalgen.title=It Generates Energy &nUsing&r Coal, It Doesn't Make Coal
ftbuniversity.rftcoalgen.subtitle=Make a Coal Generator
ftbuniversity.rftcoalgen.desc1=The &bCoal Generator&r generates 36,000 RF at 60 RF/t per Coal.
ftbuniversity.rftcoalgen.desc2=It can only burn Coal, Charcoal, and Coal Blocks, but it can charge items directly.

ftbuniversity.endergenic.subtitle=Make an Endergenic Generator setup
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc1=&bEndergenic Generators&r are extremely intricate machines that &6generate RF when firing and receiving Ender Pearls to each other&r.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc2=An Endergenic Generator has 3 modes: &6idle&r, &6charging&r, and &6holding&r. The Generator cycles through these when given redstone pulses.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc3=While in charging mode, there is a 15 tick window in which it can receive an Ender Pearl. The closer it is to the 10th tick, the more RF is produced.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc4=If a Generator in charging mode receives a Pearl, it immediately goes into holding mode. Holding a Pearl drains RF.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc5=Using a &6Smart Wrench&r (or any other compatible wrench), you can link Endergenic Generators in a cycle. When the first Generator gets a signal while in holding mode, it will throw the Pearl to the linked Generator.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc6=Pearls are introduced into the cycle using the &bPearl Injector&r. Place the Injector adjacent (or directly above) to the first Endergenic Generator, and it will inject Ender Pearls it has stored when it gets a redstone pulse.
ftbuniversity.endergenic.desc7=The &bEnder Monitor&r can output a signal when the Generator on its purple side shoots a Pearl, receives a Pearl, or loses a Pearl.

ftbuniversity.endergeniclink.title=Click here for an image guide for an example setup
ftbuniversity.endergeniclink.subtitle=A single Pearl with this setup generates about 1.74 million RF

ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.title=ROW ROW
ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.subtitle=Make a Powercell
ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.desc1=&bPowercells&r are fairly simple RF-storing blocks. You can right-click any face with a wrench to toggle between input (blue), output (orange), and neither.
ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.desc2=Powercells come in three tiers: &bSimple&r, which store &6250,000RF&r; regular, which store &61,000,000RF&r; and &bAdvanced&r, which store &64,000,000RF&r. Higher tiers can also transfer more RF/t.
ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.desc3=Powercells can charge items with RF. They can also wirelessly connect to pool their storage as well. See the next quest for more details.
ftbuniversity.rftpowercell.task=Any Powercell

ftbuniversity.powercellcard.subtitle=Make Powercell Cards
ftbuniversity.powercellcard.desc1=Powercells can wirelessly connect to pool their storage using &bPowercell Cards&r.
ftbuniversity.powercellcard.desc2=Place a Powercell Card into the top left slot of the Powercell GUI, then place another in the slot that says &6Link&r. Place the newly linked Powercell Card into the top left of another Powercell to link them together.
ftbuniversity.powercellcard.desc3=&6Every linked Powercell will show as containing the sum of their combined storage.&r So, two linked Powercells would each say they have 2,000,000RF, but if you discharge one it also discharges the other. This is a great way to wirelessly transport power across large distances, though it loses efficiency the further away they are.

ftbuniversity.rftteleporter.title=Beam Me Up
ftbuniversity.rftteleporter.subtitle=Make a teleportation system
ftbuniversity.rftteleporter.desc1=The &bMatter Receiver&r acts as a destination for teleporting. In its GUI you can give it a name and set if its private or not. You can also set a whitelist of players at the bottom, so they can use it even if it's set to private.
ftbuniversity.rftteleporter.desc2=The &bMatter Transmitter&r will send the player standing on it to the desired location. Both the Receiver and Transmitter require RF to function, the amount of which increases based on distance.
ftbuniversity.rftteleporter.desc3=The &bDialing Device&r will allow you to connect a nearby Matter Transmitter to any Matter Receiver you have access to. Click a Transmitter from the top and a Receiver from the bottom, then click either &6Dial&r to make a permanent connection, or &6Dial Once&r for a temporary one. Then, simply stand on the Transmitter and away you'll go!

ftbuniversity.rftporter.title=Transportalponder
ftbuniversity.rftporter.subtitle=Make a Charged Porter
ftbuniversity.rftporter.desc1=The &bCharged Porter&r allows you to teleport to a bound Matter Receiver &6from anywhere in any dimension&r. Longer distances require more RF.
ftbuniversity.rftporter.desc2=Sneak right-click the Porter on a Receiver to bind it.

ftbuniversity.rftporter2.title=Transportalponderer
ftbuniversity.rftporter2.subtitle=Make an Advanced Charged Porter
ftbuniversity.rftporter2.desc=The &bAdvanced Charged Porter&r stores more RF and can have &6up to 8 bound Receivers&r. Sneak right-click on the air to choose which Receiver to teleport to.

ftbuniversity.rftdestanal.title=Is It Safe?
ftbuniversity.rftdestanal.subtitle=Make a Destination Analyzer
ftbuniversity.rftdestanal.desc1=If the Matter Receiver does not have enough RF, teleporting to it will cause pretty much instant death. The &bDestination Analyzer&r lets you know if it's safe to use.
ftbuniversity.rftdestanal.desc2=The Destination Analyzer is entirely passive and does not require RF. You can place it next to the Dialing Device to enable the &6Check&r button, which will say if it's safe.
ftbuniversity.rftdestanal.desc3=&oOr&r, if you're cool, you could place it next to the Matter Transmitter, and if it's dangerous &cthe beam will glow &4&lred&r.

ftbuniversity.rftmatboost.title=It's Safe.
ftbuniversity.rftmatboost.subtitle=Make a Matter Booster
ftbuniversity.rftmatboost.desc1=The &bMatter Booster&r can be placed next to a Matter Transmitter to allow it to &6safely teleport you to an unpowered Matter Receiver&r.
ftbuniversity.rftmatboost.desc2=Well, "safely." &cIt will still damage you&r, but it won't outright kill you.

ftbuniversity.rftcrafter1.subtitle=Make a Crafter Tier 1
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter1.desc1=&bCrafters&r allow you to &6automatically craft items&r using their internal inventories. Higher tiers can store more recipes.
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter1.desc2=At the top, click one of the recipe slots and then put in the recipe you want it to craft, then click &6Apply&r. You can also toggle whether that recipe will keep one of each ingredient in their slot, as well as if the results go into the output slots or back into the input slots.
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter1.desc3=Click the &6R&r button (in the GUI, not your keyboard) to remember the current slot layout, only allowing those items into those slots. Click &6F&r to forget them.
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter1.desc4=At the bottom right, you can change the redstone control mode and the speed that it crafts items at.

ftbuniversity.rftcrafter2.subtitle=Make a Crafter Tier 2
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter2.desc=The &bCrafter Tier 2&r has &64 crafting recipes&r instead of 2.

ftbuniversity.rftcrafter3.subtitle=Make a Crafter Tier 3
ftbuniversity.rftcrafter3.desc=The &bCrafter Tier 3&r has &68 crafting recipes&r.

ftbuniversity.rftliqmon.subtitle=Make a Liquid Monitor
ftbuniversity.rftliqmon.desc1=The &bLiquid Monitor&r allows you to give a redstone signal based on the amount of fluid in an adjacent tank.
ftbuniversity.rftliqmon.desc2=In the Monitor's GUI, choose a tank out of the list. At the bottom, choose whether it should emit a signal when the tank is &6below&r or &6above&r a specified percentage full, which is chosen using the slider. The redstone signal is sent through the back face.

ftbuniversity.rftrfmon.subtitle=Make an RF Monitor
ftbuniversity.rftrfmon.desc1=The &bRF Monitor&r allows you to give a redstone signal based on the amount of RF in an adjacent machine.
ftbuniversity.rftrfmon.desc2=In the Monitor's GUI, choose a machine out of the list. At the bottom, choose whether it should emit a signal when the machine is &6below&r or &6above&r a specified percentage full, which is chosen using the slider. The redstone signal is sent through the back face.

ftbuniversity.rftscreens.title=Monitor Monitor
ftbuniversity.rftscreens.subtitle=Make a Screen setup
ftbuniversity.rftscreens.desc1=&bScreens&r can display various things in your base in the world, such as the amount of energy in a machine, specific items in an inventory, if a certain wireless redstone signal is powered, and much much more.
ftbuniversity.rftscreens.desc2=Screens require power, which is provided via a nearby &bScreen Controller&r. In its GUI, click &6Scan&r to connect to nearby Screens, and &6Detach&r to disconnect from them.
ftbuniversity.rftscreens.desc3=Right-click a Screen with a Wrench to change its &6display mode&r. The Screen can be 1x1, 2x2, or 3x3, and each size can be invisible.

ftbuniversity.rftwire.title=The Latest in Redstone Wire Technology
ftbuniversity.rftwire.subtitle=Make a Wire
ftbuniversity.rftwire.desc=The &bWire&r works pretty much exactly like a line of Redstone dust. However, it can't turn corners, can go on walls and ceilings, and only moves signals from the blue end to the orange end. It also preserves signal strength.

ftbuniversity.rftwirelessredstone.title=Wireless Redstone
ftbuniversity.rftwirelessredstone.subtitle=Make a wireless redstone setup
ftbuniversity.rftwirelessredstone.desc1=The &bRedstone Transmitter&r and &bRedstone Receiver&r work together to allow wireless redstone connections at any distance.
ftbuniversity.rftwirelessredstone.desc2=&6Place down one, and then right-click it with another to link them together.&r A redstone signal entering the blue end of a Transmitter will make the orange end of the linked Receiver emit a full signal.
ftbuniversity.rftwirelessredstone.desc3=Sneak click the Receiver with an empty hand to open the GUI, where you can enable &6Analog mode&r. In Analog mode, the Receiver will emit the same strength signal that entered the Transmitter, instead of emitting it at full strength. 

ftbuniversity.rftcounter.subtitle=Make a Counter
ftbuniversity.rftcounter.desc1=The &bCounter&r will count the amount of redstone pulses it receives, then emit one when it gets to a defined amount, then starts over.
ftbuniversity.rftcounter.desc2=Open the GUI to change the amount of pulses required.

ftbuniversity.rfttimer.subtitle=Make a Timer
ftbuniversity.rfttimer.desc=The &bTimer&r will emit a redstone pulse after a defined amount of ticks pass. You can change this amount in the Timer's GUI, as well as if receiving a redstone signal pauses it.

ftbuniversity.rftsensor.subtitle=Make a Sensor
ftbuniversity.rftsensor.desc1=The &bSensor&r will emit a redstone signal when certain conditions are met. Open the GUI to set those conditions.
ftbuniversity.rftsensor.desc2=&6Block&r will emit a signal when a block is within the area. You can put a block in the top right slot to make it require specifically that block.
ftbuniversity.rftsensor.desc3=&6Fluid&r will emit a signal when a fluid is within the area. You can put a bucket in the top right slot to make it require specifically that fluid.
ftbuniversity.rftsensor.desc4=&6Growth&r will emit a signal when crops within the area are past a defined percentage grown. This percentage is typed into &6Number&r.
ftbuniversity.rftsensor.desc5=&6Entities&r, &6Players&r, &6Hostile&r, and &6Passive&r will emit a signal when a defined amount of that type of entity are within the area.

ftbuniversity.rftinvcheck.subtitle=Make an Inventory Checker
ftbuniversity.rftinvcheck.desc1=The &bInventory Checker&r will emit a redstone signal if the inventory in front of it has a specified amount of a specified item is in a specified slot.
ftbuniversity.rftinvcheck.desc2=You can also set it to ignore metadata or use the ore dictionary. You can also not set any item at all to allow it to work with anything.

ftbuniversity.rftlogicgate.title=Truth Tables
ftbuniversity.rftlogicgate.subtitle=Make a Logic Gate
ftbuniversity.rftlogicgate.desc=The &bLogic Gate&r looks a lot more complex than it is. It has three inputs and one output. In its GUI, it shows every possible combination of signals, and you can set the output for each combination.

ftbuniversity.rftanalog.title=Analogue?
ftbuniversity.rftanalog.subtitle=Make an Analog
ftbuniversity.rftanalog.desc1=The &bAnalog&r allows you to do complex calculations to modify the signal strength of the output based on the input and two variables.
ftbuniversity.rftanalog.desc2=While standing on the &norange&r side of the Analog, the &6left side is variable A&r and the &6right is variable B&r. I is input and O is output.
ftbuniversity.rftanalog.desc3=In the GUI, there are three equations for when A's signal strength is greater, equal to, or lower than B's.
ftbuniversity.rftanalog.desc4=You can change each equation to multiply the input's strength by a factor, and then add a constant to it. 

ftbuniversity.rftseq.subtitle=Make a Sequencer
ftbuniversity.rftseq.desc1=The &bSequencer&r's GUI allows you to set a pattern of offs and ons, and then cycles through them to emit signals.
ftbuniversity.rftseq.desc2=You can set when and how it loops with the button that defaults to &6Once1&r; the tooltips should explain how they work.
ftbuniversity.rftseq.desc3=You can also choose the amount of ticks the Sequencer pauses on each bit on, as well as set the sequence length to prematurely end it instead of lasting the whole 64 bits.

ftbuniversity.rftdigit.title=Hexidigital
ftbuniversity.rftdigit.subtitle=Make a Digit
ftbuniversity.rftdigit.desc1=The &bDigit&r will show the hexidecimal value of the strength of the redstone signal it is given.
ftbuniversity.rftdigit.desc2=For those who don't know, 0-9 in hexidecimal are just 0-9, but instead of 10 it has A, and instead of 11 it has B, and so on.

ftbuniversity.rftenviro.title=Beacon? What's That?
ftbuniversity.rftenviro.subtitle=Make an Environmental Controller
ftbuniversity.rftenviro.desc1=The &bEnvironmental Controller&r allows you to give yourself certain effects, like speed, saturation or even &6creative flight&r, in an area.
ftbuniversity.rftenviro.desc2=Place up to 7 &bEnvironmental Modules&r in the left slots. At the top, set a radius and the max and min heights it works at. You can also optionally set a whitelist of players, or if it works on mobs.
ftbuniversity.rftenviro.desc3=See the quest to the right to see how to craft Modules.
ftbuniversity.rftenviro.task=Environmental Modules

ftbuniversity.rftsyringe.title=And That's How I Lost My Medical License
ftbuniversity.rftsyringe.subtitle=Make a Syringe
ftbuniversity.rftsyringe.desc=Filled &bSyringes&r are required to craft Modules. To fill a Syringe, hold it in your hands and attack a mob.

ftbuniversity.rftspawner.subtitle=Make a Spawner system
ftbuniversity.rftspawner.desc1=The &bSpawner&r works in tandem with the &bMatter Beamer&r to spawn any mob, using a certain amount of three items.
ftbuniversity.rftspawner.desc2=Place and power the Spawner, and then place and power three Matter Beamers nearby. Use a Wrench on a Beamer then on the Spawner to bind them together.
ftbuniversity.rftspawner.desc3=Place a &6full Syringe&r into the top right slot of the Spawner. There, you can see the items and the amount you need to spawn that mob.
ftbuniversity.rftspawner.desc4=Mobs need &6key matter&r, &6bulk matter&r, and &6living matter&r. The key and bulk matters depend on the mob you're spawning, but living matter accepts any plant or animal drop.

ftbuniversity.rftelevator.subtitle=Make an Elevator system
ftbuniversity.rftelevator.desc1=&bElevators&r can smoothly send a platform up and down, bringing you with it. Place the bottom floor's first and give it power, then build the platform touching the Elevator's front face.
ftbuniversity.rftelevator.desc2=Place the other floor's Elevators &6directly above it&r where you want the platform to stop at. When any Elevator gets a redstone signal, the platform will be sent to it. &6You only need to provide the bottom floor's Elevator with power.&r
ftbuniversity.rftelevator.desc3=Elevators (and their passengers) will &6phase through any solid block in the way&r. You will still take &csuffocation damage&r, however.

ftbuniversity.rftelevatorscreen.subtitle=Make an Elevator Button Screen Module
ftbuniversity.rftelevatorscreen.desc1=It's frustrating to make a complex redstone circuit that allows you to send a signal to any Elevator from any other Elevator. You can use a &bElevator Button Screen Module&r to do this easier.
ftbuniversity.rftelevatorscreen.desc2=Sneak right-click the Module on the Elevator floor you're on, then put it in a powered Screen nearby (&6Elevators can phase through Screens&r, so you don't have to put it outside the shaft). Repeat this for every floor.
ftbuniversity.rftelevatorscreen.desc3=In the Module's GUI, you can choose the colors for the current floor and the other floors, the button style, the button &osize&r, and the names of 8 floors.
ftbuniversity.rftelevatorscreen.desc4=Simply &6right-click one of the buttons&r on the Screen to be sent to that floor.

ftbuniversity.rftshapecard.subtitle=Make a Shape Card
ftbuniversity.rftshapecard.desc1=&bShape Cards&r are used in several machines in RFTools. They allow you to &6set the working area&r of those machines.
ftbuniversity.rftshapecard.desc2=Right-click the Shape Card to set the shape and size, as well as the offset and if it's solid or hollow.
ftbuniversity.rftshapecard.desc3=The &6RFTools Shape Manual&r has much more detailed instructions.

ftbuniversity.rftcomposer.title=â™«
ftbuniversity.rftcomposer.subtitle=Make a Composer
ftbuniversity.rftcomposer.desc1=The &bComposer&r allows you to combine several Shape Cards into one final shape.
ftbuniversity.rftcomposer.desc2=Put all the shapes you want to combine in the top slots, and the final Shape Card in the bottom.

ftbuniversity.rftprojector.subtitle=Make a Projector
ftbuniversity.rftprojector.desc1=The &bProjector&r will &6display a hologram of the Shape Card&r inserted into it.
ftbuniversity.rftprojector.desc2=You can also set its angle, scale, and offset, as well as how a redstone signal from any side will effect it.

ftbuniversity.rftbuilder.title=The Actual Best Thing
ftbuniversity.rftbuilder.subtitle=Make a Builder
ftbuniversity.rftbuilder.desc1=The &bBuilder&r will &6fill in an area&r set by a Shape Card &6using blocks from the inventory above it&r.
ftbuniversity.rftbuilder.desc2=You can also &6sneak right-click a Shape Card onto it&r, then click two corners to set the working area.
ftbuniversity.rftbuilder.desc3=The Builder can do this and so much more; you should &6read the Shape Manual&r.

ftbuniversity.rftquarry.title=&lDiggy Diggy Hole&r
ftbuniversity.rftquarry.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Quarry)
ftbuniversity.rftquarry.desc1=The &bShape Card (Quarry)&r works like a regular Shape Card, except Builders will &omine&r the working area instead of placing blocks.
ftbuniversity.rftquarry.desc2=Blocks mined will insert their drops (as if mined with a regular pickaxe) into the inventory above the Builder. These blocks will be replaced with Dirt.
ftbuniversity.rftquarry.desc3=This is honestly the &6best way to get resources&r the majority of the time. Put it down somewhere that won't annoy anyone (like the Deep Dark), set it to the maximum possible size, and just let it run!

ftbuniversity.rftclearingquarry.title=World Hole
ftbuniversity.rftclearingquarry.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Clearing Quarry)
ftbuniversity.rftclearingquarry.desc=The &bShape Card (Clearing Quarry)&r works exactly the same as a regular Quarry card, except instead of replacing blocks with Dirt, it just leaves a hole.

ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.title=Shape Card (Quarry (Fortune (Clearing))
ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.subtitle=Make an upgraded Shape Card (Quarry)
ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.desc1=The &bShape Card (Fortune Quarry)&r works exactly like a regular Quarry card, except it &6applies a Fortune III enchantment to drops&r. Each block mined costs twice as much RF as a regular Quarry card.
ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.desc2=The &bShape Card (Silk Quarry)&r does the same, except with &6Silk Touch&r. Each mined block costs three times as much RF as a regular Quarry card.
ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.task1=Shape Cards (Fortune Quarry)
ftbuniversity.rftquarryupgrades.task2=Shape Cards (Silk Quarry)

ftbuniversity.rftvoidcard.title=Shape Card (â¬›â¬›â¬›â¬›)
ftbuniversity.rftvoidcard.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Void)
ftbuniversity.rftvoidcard.desc=The &bShape Card (Void)&r will &6destroy all blocks in its working area, leaving no drops&r. However, it requires &6zero RF&r per block, so this is great for clearing land.

ftbuniversity.rftpump.title=Pump it Up!
ftbuniversity.rftpump.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Pump)
ftbuniversity.rftpump.desc=The &bShape Card (Pump)&r will collect any fluid in its working area and deposit it into the tank directly above. Fluids sources will be replaced with Dirt.

ftbuniversity.rftclearingpump.title=Drought
ftbuniversity.rftclearingpump.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Clearing Pump)
ftbuniversity.rftclearingpump.desc=The &bShape Card (Clearing Pump)&r works exactly like a normal Pump card, except sources will not be replaced with Dirt.

ftbuniversity.rftplacingfluids.subtitle=Make a Shape Card (Placing Fluids)
ftbuniversity.rftplacingfluids.desc=The &bShape Card (Placing Fluids)&r will place fluids from the tank above itself in the working area.

ftbuniversity.rftoolsdimbok.subtitle=Get the RFTools Dimension Manual
ftbuniversity.rftoolsdimbok.desc1=&eRFTools Dimensions&r is an add-on for RFTools that allow you to create dimensions to your specifications at great cost and risk.
ftbuniversity.rftoolsdimbok.desc2=The &bRFtools Dimension Manual&r is the best source of information for how dimensions work.

ftbuniversity.dimletparts.title=Dimlet Components
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.subtitle=Get Dimlet components
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.desc1=&bDimlets&r allow you to specify what kind of dimension you want to create; if you have no Dimlets, the dimension is completely random.
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.desc2=Dimlets require components, which can be found in special structures that &6only generate in created dimensions&r. You can also find Dimlet Parcels in chests that give you random components.
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.task1=Any Dimlet Control Circuit
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.task2=Any Dimlet Energy Module
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.task3=Any Dimlet Memory Unit
ftbuniversity.dimletparts.task4=Any Dimlet Type Controller

ftbuniversity.dimletworkbench.subtitle=Make a Dimlet Workbench
ftbuniversity.dimletworkbench.desc1=You can craft Dimlets in the &bDimlet Workbench&r. On the right of the GUI is a searchable list of all possible Dimlets. Hover over a Dimlet to see what parts it needs.
ftbuniversity.dimletworkbench.desc2=Put those Dimlet components in the slots on the left, and then click the Dimlet out of the list to try to craft it.
ftbuniversity.dimletworkbench.desc3=You can also put a completed Dimlet in the top left slot and enable &6Extract&r to destroy it, getting some of its components.

ftbuniversity.rftabsorbers.subtitle=Make Absorbers
ftbuniversity.rftabsorbers.desc1=Some Dimlet recipes require filled &bAbsorbers&r. Absorbers are generally filled by placing them near the thing you want to absorb (current time, biome, liquids, etc) and letting them run. &6See their tooltips&r for more information.
ftbuniversity.rftabsorbers.desc2=Of these, the &6Time Absorber&r is the strangest to get working, so I'll explain it: Place it down outside, and give it a redstone pulse around the time you want it to absorb. The next day, give it a redstone pulse around the same time to add another 10%% . It has a cooldown, so you can't just spam pulses to increase it. A &6Timer set to 24,000 ticks&r works perfectly, as that is the exact amount of ticks per Minecraft day (without sleeping).
ftbuniversity.rftabsorbers.desc3=Mine a filled Absorber with a pickaxe to pick it up.

ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.subtitle=Make a Dimension Enscriber
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc1=To actually &ocreate&r the dimension, you need a &bDimension Enscriber&r. Place an &bEmpty Dimension Tab&r in the bottom left to begin.
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc2=If you have no Dimlets, just go right ahead and click &6Store&r. That will create an entirely random dimension, with nothing set whatsoever.
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc3=If you &odo&r have Dimlets, put those in the slots at the top. &6Dimlet grammar&r, the order that Dimlets must be installed, can be a bit confusing:
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc4=&6Modifier Dimlets (like materials/fluids) must be entered &obefore&r&6 the things they modify.&r
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc5=So for instance, a Material Dimlet (Copper Ore) followed by a Feature Dimlet (HugeOrbs) will generate huge orbs made out of Copper Ore.
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc6=If two dimensions have identical Dimlets, they will go to the same dimension instead of creating another identical one. If you want to create two different dimensions with the same Dimlets, give it some Digit Dimlets.
ftbuniversity.rftenscriber.desc7=You can also give dimensions names in the bottom left. Clicking &6Extract&r will take all the Dimlets out of it the Dimension Tab.

ftbuniversity.rftdimensionbuilder.subtitle=Make a Dimension Builder
ftbuniversity.rftdimensionbuilder.desc1=Place a Realized Dimension Tab into the slot in the &bDimension Builder&r to begin actually creating the dimension.
ftbuniversity.rftdimensionbuilder.desc2=&6Dimensions require RF to be created, and more RF to run.&r Hover over the Realized Dimension Tab to see how much it needs to begin and run. More complex dimensions need more RF, so be careful when designing one.
ftbuniversity.rftdimensionbuilder.desc3=Once a Dimension has been powered and built, &6it will place down a Matter Receiver&r in the dimension itself&r. You can teleport to it using a Matter Transmitter and Dialing Device, though you have to bring a way back yourself (I suggest a Porter).
ftbuniversity.rftdimensionbuilder.desc4=If the dimension runs out of RF, &cit becomes completely inhospitable&r until powered. &6&lMake sure the Dimension Builder is chunkloaded.&r

ftbuniversity.rftdimshards.subtitle=Mine Dimensional Ore
ftbuniversity.rftdimshards.desc=&bDimensional Shards&r are dropped by Dimensional Ore, which &6only generates in created Dimensions&r.

ftbuniversity.rftdimmon.subtitle=Make a Dimension Modifier
ftbuniversity.rftdimmon.desc=The &bDimension Modifier&r will show you the &6current charge of the dimension you are in&r. This is useful for letting you know if something went horribly wrong at your base, giving you time to leave.

ftbuniversity.rftinfuser.subtitle=Make a Machine Infuser
ftbuniversity.rftinfuser.desc=The &bMachine Infuser&r allows you to &6spend Dimension Shards to improve RFTools machines&r. Hover over a machine to see what its infusing bonus is.

ftbuniversity.rftphasedfield.subtitle=Make a Phased Field Generator
ftbuniversity.rftphasedfield.desc1=The &bPhased Field Generator&r will rapidly use its charge to &6allow you to enter uncharged dimensions&r.
ftbuniversity.rftphasedfield.desc2=It must be in your hotbar to function.

ftbuniversity.rftactivityprobe.subtitle=Make an Activity Probe
ftbuniversity.rftactivityprobe.desc=The &bActivity Probe&r, when placed in a dimension, will stop it from consuming power when no chunks in it are loaded.

###Environmental Tech
ftbuniversity.etechchap.title=Environmental Tech

ftbuniversity.digitalguide.subtitle=Get the Digital Guide
ftbuniversity.digitalguide.desc=The &bDigital Guide&r is your one-stop shop for all mods by ValkyrieofNight. We only have &eEnvironmental Tech&r, so that's all that's in the Guide.

ftbuniversity.etassembler.subtitle=Make an Assembler
ftbuniversity.etassembler.desc1=All Environmental Tech machines are multiblocks, built around their Controllers.
ftbuniversity.etassembler.desc2=The &bAssembler&r will automatically build the multiblock when used on the multiblock's Controller, given that you have the blocks required.

ftbuniversity.voidore1.title=RF to Ores
ftbuniversity.voidore1.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 1
ftbuniversity.voidore1.desc1=&bVoid Ore Miners&r are generally the biggest point of interest in the mod. They use RF to slowly &6generate ores&r. Higher tiers work faster, use more power, and choose from a larger pool to generate.
ftbuniversity.voidore1.desc2=&bTier 1&r uses &6660RF/t&r and generates an ore every &6400 ticks&r. It &6takes up a 7x4x7 area&r.
ftbuniversity.voidore1.desc3=For all Void Ore Miners, the &6Laser Core must have a direct line of sight to Bedrock or the void under&r.
ftbuniversity.voidore1.desc4=The &6Laser Lens' color can influence the weight of certain ores&r, making them more likely to generate.

ftbuniversity.etechreadguide=See the Digital Guide for the block requirements.

ftbuniversity.voidore2.title=Yep, You Have to Make &lEvery Single One&r
ftbuniversity.voidore2.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 2
ftbuniversity.voidore2.desc=&bTier 2&r uses &6575RF/t&r and generates an ore every &6320 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 7x5x7 area&r.

ftbuniversity.etechmodifiers=You can &6replace the Null Modifiers with other Modifiers to upgrade&r the multiblock.

ftbuniversity.voidore3.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 3
ftbuniversity.voidore3.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6750RF/t&r and generates an ore every &6160 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x6x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidore4.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 4
ftbuniversity.voidore4.desc=&bTier 4&r uses &6900RF/t&r and generates an ore every &680 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x7x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidore5.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 5
ftbuniversity.voidore5.desc=&bTier 5&r uses &61,000RF/t&r and generates an ore every &640 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x8x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidore6.subtitle=Make a Void Ore Miner Controller Tier 6
ftbuniversity.voidore6.desc=&bTier 6&r uses &6800RF/t&r and generates an ore every &620 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 13x8x13 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres1.title=RF to Non-Ore Blocks
ftbuniversity.voidres1.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 1
ftbuniversity.voidres1.desc1=&bVoid Resource Miners&r will &6generate Stone, Dirt, Grass, and the like&r using RF. Higher tiers do not get new resources, they only work faster.
ftbuniversity.voidres1.desc2=&bTier 1&r uses &6160RF/t&r and generates a resource every &6400 ticks&r. It &6takes up a 7x4x7 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres2.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 2
ftbuniversity.voidres2.desc=&bTier 2&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a resource every &6320 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 7x5x7 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres3.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 3
ftbuniversity.voidres3.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a resource every &6160 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x6x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres4.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 4
ftbuniversity.voidres4.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a resource every &680 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x7x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres5.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 5
ftbuniversity.voidres5.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a resource every &640 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x8x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidres6.subtitle=Make a Void Resource Miner Controller Tier 6
ftbuniversity.voidres6.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a resource every &620 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 13x8x13 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot1.title=RF to Plants
ftbuniversity.voidbot1.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Tier 1
ftbuniversity.voidbot1.desc1=&bVoid Botanic Miners&r will &6generate all plant matter (wood, saplings, flowers, etc)&r using RF. This includes plants from other mods, like Forestry and Botania! Higher tiers do not get new resources, they only work faster.
ftbuniversity.voidbot1.desc2=&bTier 1&r uses &6160RF/t&r and generates a plant every &6400 ticks&r. It &6takes up a 7x4x7 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot2.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Controller Tier 2
ftbuniversity.voidbot2.desc=&bTier 2&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a plant every &6320 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 7x5x7 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot3.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Controller Tier 3
ftbuniversity.voidbot3.desc=&bTier 3&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a plant every &6160 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x6x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot4.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Controller Tier 4
ftbuniversity.voidbot4.desc=&bTier 4&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a plant every &680 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x7x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot5.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Controller Tier 5
ftbuniversity.voidbot5.desc=&bTier 5&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a plant every &640 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up an 11x8x11 area&r.

ftbuniversity.voidbot6.subtitle=Make a Void Botanic Miner Controller Tier 6
ftbuniversity.voidbot6.desc=&bTier 6&r uses &6100RF/t&r and generates a plant every &620 ticks&r without upgrades. It &6takes up a 13x8x13 area&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight1.title=Lightning to RF
ftbuniversity.etlight1.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 1
ftbuniversity.etlight1.desc1=&bLightning Rods&r  &6generate a massive amount of RF&r when struck by lightning. It does not make RF when struck by lightning caused by other mods.
ftbuniversity.etlight1.desc2=Every 1,600-3,200 ticks, it has a chance to get struck by lightning. During a thunderstorm, it changes to once every 400-800 ticks.
ftbuniversity.etlight1.desc3=&6Higher tiers have a &n&llower&r&6 chance of being hit, but generate more RF.&r
ftbuniversity.etlight1.desc4=&bTier 1&r has a &660%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 93,750-750,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight2.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 2
ftbuniversity.etlight2.desc=&bTier 2&r has a &655%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 281,500-2,250,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight3.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 3
ftbuniversity.etlight3.desc=&bTier 3&r has a &650%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 1,312,500-10,500,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight4.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 4
ftbuniversity.etlight4.desc=&bTier 4&r has a &645%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 5,062,500-40,500,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight5.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 5
ftbuniversity.etlight5.desc=&bTier 5&r has a &640%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 19,500,000-156,000,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etlight6.subtitle=Make a Lightning Controller Tier 6
ftbuniversity.etlight6.desc=&bTier 6&r has a &635%% chance&r of being struck, and &6generates 74,250,000-594,000,000RF&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar1.title=Time to RF
ftbuniversity.etsolar1.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 1
ftbuniversity.etsolar1.desc1=&bSolar Arrays&r &6generate a fairly high amount of RF/t when it can see the sun&r. They work worse during storms.
ftbuniversity.etsolar1.desc2=Like there are 6 tiers of Controllers, there are &66 tiers of Solar Cells&r. Solar Cells of any tier can be used with any Controller, with &6higher tiers making more RF/t&r.
ftbuniversity.etsolar1.desc3=These quests will assume you're using the same tier for both.
ftbuniversity.etsolar1.desc4=&bTier 1&r will generate &6549RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar2.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 2
ftbuniversity.etsolar2.desc=&bTier 2&r will generate &64,075RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar3.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 3
ftbuniversity.etsolar3.desc=&bTier 3&r will generate &624,059RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar4.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 4
ftbuniversity.etsolar4.desc=&bTier 4&r will generate &6106,110RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar5.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 5
ftbuniversity.etsolar5.desc=&bTier 5&r will generate &6475,772RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etsolar6.subtitle=Make a Solar Array Controller Tier 6
ftbuniversity.etsolar6.desc=&bTier 6&r will generate &61,771,965RF/t&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged1.title=RF Beacon
ftbuniversity.etranged1.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 1
ftbuniversity.etranged1.desc1=&bRanged Nano Bot Beacons&r will &6give players within their range effects chosen by Modifiers&r.
ftbuniversity.etranged1.desc2=The Modifiers all &6share a name with the effect&r they would give you (Resistance gives you Resistance, etc). The Digital Guide shows which Modifiers can be installed to it.
ftbuniversity.etranged1.desc3=The RF cost is entirely dependant on the Modifiers.
ftbuniversity.etranged1.desc4=Higher tiers have &6higher range&r and can have &6more Modifiers&r.
ftbuniversity.etranged1.desc5=&bTier 1&r has a range of &632 blocks&r and room for &64 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged2.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 2
ftbuniversity.etranged2.desc=&bTier 2&r has a range of &648 blocks&r and room for &68 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged3.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 3
ftbuniversity.etranged3.desc=&bTier 3&r has a range of &664 blocks&r and room for &612 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged4.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 4
ftbuniversity.etranged4.desc=&bTier 4&r has a range of &680 blocks&r and room for &616 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged5.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 5
ftbuniversity.etranged5.desc=&bTier 5&r has a range of &696 blocks&r and room for &620 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etranged6.subtitle=Make a Ranged Nano Bot Beacon Tier 6
ftbuniversity.etranged6.desc=&bTier 6&r has a range of &6112 blocks&r and room for &624 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.title=Player Upgrades
ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 1
ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.desc1=&bPersonal Nano Bot Beacons&r will &6give their owner effects chosen by Modifiers with infinite range&r.
ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.desc2=There are Modifiers for &6every potion effect&r, as well as &6creative-style flight&r and &6flight-speed&r. The Digital Guide shows which Modifiers can be installed to it.
ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.desc3=The RF cost is entirely dependant on the Modifiers, though it takes 512 more RF/t than the Ranged equivalent.
ftbuniversity.etpersonal1.desc4=&bTier 1&r has room for &64 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal2.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 2
ftbuniversity.etpersonal2.desc=&bTier 2&r has room for &68 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal3.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 3
ftbuniversity.etpersonal3.desc=&bTier 3&r has room for &612 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal4.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 4
ftbuniversity.etpersonal4.desc=&bTier 4&r has room for &616 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal5.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 5
ftbuniversity.etpersonal5.desc=&bTier 5&r has room for &620 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etpersonal6.subtitle=Make a Personal Nano Bot Beacon Tier 6
ftbuniversity.etpersonal6.desc=&bTier 6&r has room for &624 Modifiers&r.

ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.title=Upgrades
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.subtitle=Make Modifiers
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.desc1=Most ETech multiblocks use Null Modifiers somewhere in the structure.
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.desc2=You can &6replace these Null Modifiers&r with other &bModifiers&r, depending on the machine, and their effects will be applied.
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.desc3=There's normally no in-game explanation for what they do, so &6we've manually added tooltips&r to them.
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.task1=Void Ore, Resource, and Botanic Miner Modifiers
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.task2=Solar Array Modifiers
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.task3=Ranged Beacon Modifiers
ftbuniversity.etmodifiers.task4=Personal Beacon Modifiers

###Advanced Rocketry
ftbuniversity.advrockchap.title=Advanced Rocketry

ftbuniversity.platepress.title=Arguably OP?
ftbuniversity.platepress.subtitle=Make the Small Plate Presser
ftbuniversity.platepress.desc1=The &bSmall Plate Presser&r is &otechnically&r a multiblock, as it has to be placed 2 blocks above Obsidian.
ftbuniversity.platepress.desc2=Between it and the Obsidian, you can place either an &6ore&r or a &6metal block&r.
ftbuniversity.platepress.desc3=Giving it a redstone signal will either &6crush the ore into 2 dust&r, or &6press the block into 4 plates&r.
ftbuniversity.platepress.desc4=It uses no RF whatsoever, and works as quickly as you can automate placing blocks and sending a redstone signal.

ftbuniversity.holoprojector.title=Multiblocks Made Easy
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.subtitle=Make a Holo-Projector
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc1=Most machines in &eAdvanced Rocketry&r are &6multiblocks&r, which makes the &bHolo-Projector&r vital.
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc2=Sneak right-click the Holo-Projector to see a list of multiblocks. Choose one, then right-click any block to &6show a hologram of that multiblock&r, showing where each block goes.
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc3=Scroll while sneaking to change which y-level of the multiblock is being shown.
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc4=Sometimes, the hologram will cycle through multiple blocks in one spot. Any of these blocks will work there.
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc5=Two special blocks are &6Coils&r and &6Motors&r; higher tier ones make the machine faster.
ftbuniversity.holoprojector.desc6=Once the multiblock is completed, right-click the main block with an empty hand to build it.

ftbuniversity.ararcfurnace.subtitle=Make an Electric Arc Furnace
ftbuniversity.ararcfurnace.desc1=The &bElectric Arc Furnace&r is the first AR multiblock you'll probably make.
ftbuniversity.ararcfurnace.desc2=Normally, the Arc Furnace is the only way to make certain ingots (like Titanium). However, other mods (like NuclearCraft) also add recipes for them. &6Getting one of those ingots will also automatically complete this quest.&r
ftbuniversity.coils=Coils
ftbuniversity.plugs=Power Input Plugs

ftbuniversity.precass.subtitle=Make a Precision Assembler
ftbuniversity.precass.desc1=The &bPrecision Assembler&r is required to craft &6Circuit Plates&r, and unlocks more efficient recipes for &6Circuit Boards&r.
ftbuniversity.precass.desc2=You can use any tier of Coil and Motor; higher tier ones are faster.
ftbuniversity.motors=Motors

ftbuniversity.rollingmachine.subtitle=Make a Rolling Machine
ftbuniversity.rollingmachine.desc1=The &bRolling Machine&r uses both items and fluids for crafting.
ftbuniversity.rollingmachine.desc2=It is required for crafting &6Sheets&r and &6Pressure Tanks&r, and provides a cheaper recipe for &6Plates&r.

ftbuniversity.lathe.subtitle=Make a Lathe
ftbuniversity.lathe.desc=The &bLathe&r provides cheaper recipes for &6Rods&r, and literally nothing else. As such, this quest is optional.

ftbuniversity.crystallizer.subtitle=Make a Crystallizer
ftbuniversity.crystallizer.desc=The &bCrystallizer&r is the only way to make &6Dilithium Crystals&r and &6Silicon Boules&r.

ftbuniversity.cutmach.subtitle=Make a Cutting Machine
ftbuniversity.cutmach.desc=The &bCutting Machine&r is required for &6Circuits&r and &6Silicon Wafers&r.

ftbuniversity.hovercraft.subtitle=Make a HoverCraft
ftbuniversity.hovercraft.desc1=The &bHoverCraft&r is a flying vehicle, essentially. It requires no fuel to run, and can fly at any height.
ftbuniversity.hovercraft.desc2=By default, &6A and D turn it&r, and &6Z goes up&r, and &6X goes down&r.

ftbuniversity.holoplansel.subtitle=Make a Holographic Planet Selector
ftbuniversity.holoplansel.desc1=The &bHolographic Planet Selector&r will emit a hologram above it, &6showing all the planets in the solar system&r.
ftbuniversity.holoplansel.desc2=You can right-click a planet to select it, then right-click again to zoom in on it, showing its moons.
ftbuniversity.holoplansel.desc3=Right-clicking &6Up a level&r will move you from a moon to its planet, a planet to its star, a star to its galaxy, etc.
ftbuniversity.holoplansel.desc4=Sneak right-click the block to open its GUI, where you can make the hologram bigger or smaller.
ftbuniversity.holoplansel.desc5=There's no real functionality to it, but it &6looks super cool&r.

ftbuniversity.electrolyser.subtitle=Make an Electrolyser
ftbuniversity.electrolyser.desc=The &bElectrolyser&r is used to &6turn Water into Oxygen and Hydrogen&r.

ftbuniversity.chemreact.subtitle=Make a Chemical Reactor
ftbuniversity.chemreact.desc1=The &bChemical Reactor&r is used to create &6Rocket Fuel&r.
ftbuniversity.chemreact.desc2=For it to work, &6Hydrogen and Oxygen must be pumped into the Fluid Input Hatches&r. This will be made into Rocket Fuel, which is sent to the Fluid Output Hatch.
ftbuniversity.chemreact.desc3=Additionally, inserting a Diamond and any armor (and a Super High Pressure Tank if it's a Chestplate) will enchant it with &6Airtight Seal&r, which allows it to store Oxygen for use in space. You need it on all pieces for it to work.

ftbuniversity.gascharge.subtitle=Make a Gas Charge Pad
ftbuniversity.gascharge.desc1=The &bGas Charge Pad&r is used to &6fill your armor with Oxygen&r.
ftbuniversity.gascharge.desc2=It can be used on either the Space Suit, or any chestplate with Airtight Seal.
ftbuniversity.gascharge.desc3=They can hold up to 36 buckets of Oxygen, which lasts about half an hour.

ftbuniversity.spacesuit.title=Modular Space Suit
ftbuniversity.spacesuit.subtitle=Make a Space Suit setup
ftbuniversity.spacesuit.desc1=The &bSpace Suit&r can have upgrades installed to it using the &bSuit Workstation&r.
ftbuniversity.spacesuit.desc2=These upgrades can make it store more Oxygen, provide flight, make you faster, etc. &6JEI info tabs&r have been added to each.
ftbuniversity.spacesuit.task=Upgrades

ftbuniversity.rockass.title=Launchpad McQuack
ftbuniversity.rockass.subtitle=Construct a launchpad
ftbuniversity.rockass.desc1=To launch a Rocket, one must have a launch pad.
ftbuniversity.rockass.desc2=Make a platform of &bLaunch Pads&r that's anywhere from a &63x3&r to a &616x16&r (it does not have to be square).
ftbuniversity.rockass.desc3=Place a &bRocket Assembling Machine&r on the outside, one layer above (so it's not actually touching the Launch Pad, but it's &6sharing an edge&r).
ftbuniversity.rockass.desc4=Place a pillar of &bStructure Towers&r next to the Launch Pads, starting on the same y level as them then going anywhere from &64&r to &664&r blocks up. Its height is what limits your Rocket's height.

ftbuniversity.fueling.title=Why is the s Lowercase?
ftbuniversity.fueling.subtitle=Make a Fueling station
ftbuniversity.fueling.desc1=The &bFueling station&r is used to fill Rockets with Rocket Fuel.
ftbuniversity.fueling.desc2=To work, it needs a &bLinker&r. To use it, sneak right-click the Linker on the block you want to link, then sneak right-click again on the block you want to link it to.
ftbuniversity.fueling.desc3=In this case, &6link it to the Rocket Assembly Machine&r, which will fill up any Rocket on its launch pad.
ftbuniversity.fueling.desc4=You can also right-click a Tank of Rocket Fuel onto the Rocket to fuel it directly.

ftbuniversity.basicrocket.title=Spacebound
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.subtitle=Build a Rocket
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc1=Now, it's finally time to &bbuild a Rocket&r.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc2=Every Rocket needs these components:
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc3=â€¢ Enough &bEngines&r to lift your Rocket. Advanced Engines provide more thrust.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc4=â€¢ Enough &bLiquid Fuel Tanks&r to fuel the Engines.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc5=â€¢ A &bSeat&r to sit on.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc6=â€¢ A &bPlanet ID Chip&r stored in a &bGuidance Computer&r.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc7=Rockets are entirely freeform; you can &6build them however you like&r. The only requirements are that it isn't too heavy, the Engines are on the bottom, and there's enough Fuel Tanks. Other than that, you can put any blocks in any combinations onto the Rocket.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc8=Once you're happy with your Rocket, open the Rocket Assembling Machine and click &6Scan&r. If the Rocket is approved, you can click &6Build&r!
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc9=A simple Rocket like this can only move from a planet to any orbiting satellites. That means, for now, the only place you can go is &6the moon&r.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc10=Once you're ready to leave (make sure it has enough fuel for a round trip, and don't forget your space suit!), sneak right-click the built Rocket, click &6Select Dst&r, then click on the orbiting body you want to fly to and then click &6Select&r.
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.desc11=Right-click the Rocket to get on, then &6press space to lift off&r!
ftbuniversity.basicrocket.task=Rocket Engines

ftbuniversity.moon.title=To the Moon
ftbuniversity.moon.subtitle=Visit the Moon
ftbuniversity.moon.desc1=The only satellite naturally orbiting the Earth is &ethe Moon&r.
ftbuniversity.moon.desc2=There's... not really much to do here. The &6gravity is lower&r, and you &6can't breathe&r, and that's basically it. The moon &odoes&r have &6a lot more Dilithium Ore&r, however!
ftbuniversity.moon.desc3=There's &cno dungeons&r or anything. However, there &ois&r a nice secret at x=67 z=2347!
ftbuniversity.moon.desc4=To get back home, change your Rocket's destination back to Earth, jump in, and take off again.
ftbuniversity.moon.task=Visit Dimension: &dLuna&r

ftbuniversity.spacestation.title=SPACESHIP!
ftbuniversity.spacestation.subtitle=Make a Space Station
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc1=In order to leave the planet, you need to start by making a &bSpace Station&r.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc2=Make another platform out of Launch Pads and a pillar of Structure Towers, but use a &bSpace Station Assembler&r instead.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc3=On the platform, place blocks however you like. The Rocket will land on the center of the Space Station, though this can be changed later.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc4=In the Assembler's GUI, place a &bSatellite Bay&r into the top left slot and an unprogrammed &bSpace Station Id Chip&r into the top right. &6Scan&r it, then &6Build&r if it's ok.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc5=The structure you built will be stored into a &6Space Station Container&r, and the Space Station Id Chip will be programmed to that station ID. You should make copies with the &6Satellite Assembling Machine&r before progressing.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc6=To put the Space Station into orbit, place a second Satellite Bay onto a Rocket, insert the Container into it, and launch it into space.
ftbuniversity.spacestation.desc7=It would be a good idea to put a copy of the programmed Station ID Chip into the Rocket's Guidance Computer, then ride it, since that way you won't lose the ship.

ftbuniversity.copychip.title=Copy That Floppy
ftbuniversity.copychip.subtitle=Learn how to copy an ID Chip
ftbuniversity.copychip.desc1=The &bSatellite Builder&r is mainly for building Satellites, as the name implies. However, it can also be used to &6make backups of ID Chips&r.
ftbuniversity.copychip.desc2=Place the original Chip into the top-center slot on the left, then an unprogrammed Chip of the same type directly to the right.
ftbuniversity.copychip.desc3=On the far right of the GUI, click &6Write to Secondary Chip&r. This will program the second Chip to match the first. This is extremely important, so you don't lose your only Space Station ID Chip, making it impossible to reach.
ftbuniversity.copychip.desc4=The Builder needs a Power Input Plug underneath.

ftbuniversity.spacestation2.title=I Can See My House From Here!
ftbuniversity.spacestation2.subtitle=Visit a Space Station
ftbuniversity.spacestation2.desc1=Your Space Station should now be in orbit around your home planet. It's probably fairly basic right now, but you can build on it to improve it.
ftbuniversity.spacestation2.desc2=Don't forget, &6you can't breathe in space&r! Make sure you have a good amount of Oxygen, as well as enough fuel to get home.
ftbuniversity.spacestation2.task=Visit Dimension: &2Space Station&r

ftbuniversity.sscontrollers.title=You Spin Me Right Round
ftbuniversity.sscontrollers.subtitle=Make the various Space Station Controllers
ftbuniversity.sscontrollers.desc1=The &bOrientation Controller&r allows you to &6spin&r your Space Station. This is mostly an aesthetic difference, changing the location of the celestial bodies in the skybox. Though, this can also change the light level of your ship.
ftbuniversity.sscontrollers.desc2=The &bSpace Station Gravity Controller&r allows you to &6change the Station's gravity&r from 11%% normal gravity to 100%%.
ftbuniversity.sscontrollers.desc3=The &bAltitude Controller&r allows you to change &6how far the Station is from the body it is orbiting&r. This is mostly an aesthetic difference, changing the amount of space the planet you're orbiting takes.

ftbuniversity.oxygenvent.subtitle=Make an oxygen setup
ftbuniversity.oxygenvent.desc1=Space is a vacuum, which means you can't breathe there.
ftbuniversity.oxygenvent.desc2=You can place and power an &bOxygen Vent&r, and as long as it's in an &6entirely enclosed area&r, it will fill up the room with Oxygen that you supply it. The largest room it can handle is 32x32x32.
ftbuniversity.oxygenvent.desc3=You can place up to two &bCO2 Scrubbers&r next to it (but not on top or bottom), and insert a &bCarbon Collection Cartridge&r in each. This will &6drastically lower the amount of Oxygen required&r.
ftbuniversity.oxygenvent.desc4=Over time, the Cartridges will break down and need to be &6repaired in the Chemical Reactor&r. They should last for 24 real-life hours, though.

ftbuniversity.pipeseal.title=That's a Lot of Damage!
ftbuniversity.pipeseal.subtitle=Make Pipe Seal
ftbuniversity.pipeseal.desc1=A room is considered enclosed if all the walls are made out of &6solid blocks&r. However, most cables and pipes are not solid, which is a bit of a problem.
ftbuniversity.pipeseal.desc2=You can place 4 &bPipe Seal&r around a 1x1 hole, and it will be considered sealed. This is pretty much a necessity if any of your Space Station is in the vacuum of space.

ftbuniversity.warpcore.title=Ludicrous Speed
ftbuniversity.warpcore.subtitle=Make a Warp Core
ftbuniversity.warpcore.desc1=The &bWarp Core&r turns your satellite into a space ship, &6allowing it to teleport to orbit other planets&r.
ftbuniversity.warpcore.desc2=It uses &6Dilithium Crystals&r for fuel; the farther you teleport, the more it uses.
ftbuniversity.warpcore.desc3=Place the &bWarp Controller&r anywhere in the ship; it doesn't have to be near the multiblock at all.
ftbuniversity.warpcore.desc4=In its first page, click &6Select Planet&r. This will show you every planet in your solar system. You can click a planet (or the star itself) then click &6Select&r, or double click it to see it and its moons. You can also click &6Up&r to go up a level (from planet to system, from system to galaxy).
ftbuniversity.warpcore.desc5=Once you've selected a planet, it will send you back to the main screen. Click &6Warp!&r to warp there. You can see the Dilithium cost at the bottom right.

ftbuniversity.arartifacts.title=AR-tifacts
ftbuniversity.arartifacts.subtitle=Learn about artifacts
ftbuniversity.arartifacts.desc1=Certain planets may require an &6Artifact&r be &6placed in one of the 5 slots&r in the Warp Controller's third page, before you can warp to them. There is no way to discover what item the Artifact is, the modpack dev must tell you explicitly via quests etc.
ftbuniversity.arartifacts.desc2=For this pack, we've made a &ototally fair and balanced world&r that has &6every metal and gem block as ores&r, and lots of them.
ftbuniversity.arartifacts.desc3=However, its Artifact is an &bInfinity Catalyst&r. So, while getting here will make you filthy stinkin' rich, you already have to be at least a bit odourously rich to get there.

ftbuniversity.ardiscover.title=Null Star
ftbuniversity.ardiscover.subtitle=Learn how to discover planets
ftbuniversity.ardiscover.desc1=Planets can be &6hidden&r by default, requiring you &6discover&r them before you can travel there. That is how we set the &6âˆ…&r system; all planets are hidden by default, and are also completely randomly generated.
ftbuniversity.ardiscover.desc2=Give the Warp Controller at least &6100 of each Data&r in the second page. In the third page, insert a blank &bPlanet ID Chip&r in the bottom slot, then click &6Search for planet&r.
ftbuniversity.ardiscover.desc3=This will drain 100 of each Data to attempt to discover a planet, though there &cisn't a 100%% chance of success&r. If a planet requires an &6Artifact&r, you need it to be in the top slot before searching for it.
ftbuniversity.ardiscover.desc4=If successful, it will &6program the ID Chip&r and allow that Warp Controller to see it. The programmed ID Chip can be inserted into other Warp Controllers, then the &6Program from chip&r button will save that planet to them, so they don't have to discover the planet as well.

ftbuniversity.bbopworld.title=BBOP Vox
ftbuniversity.bbopworld.subtitle=Visit the BBOP planet
ftbuniversity.bbopworld.desc1=This planet uses the &bBiome Bundle O' Plenty&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.bbopworld.desc2=BBOP essentially is Biome Bundle with Biomes O' Plenty added to it.

ftbuniversity.otgwarning=OTG worlds &ccause high amounts of lag when generating new chunks&r. If you're playing on a server, be wary of this.

ftbuniversity.bbworld.title=Bundle of Joy
ftbuniversity.bbworld.subtitle=Visit the Biome Bundle planet
ftbuniversity.bbworld.desc1=This planet uses the &bBiome Bundle&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.bbworld.desc2=It has over 200 new biomes, and 2000 new structures.

ftbuniversity.vvworld.title=Vanilla Vistas
ftbuniversity.vvworld.subtitle=Visit the Vanilla Vistas planet
ftbuniversity.vvworld.desc1=This planet uses the &bVanilla Vistas&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.vvworld.desc2=Instead of adding new biomes, it aims to enhance vanilla ones.

ftbuniversity.vvaworld.title=&lVanilla Vistas&r
ftbuniversity.vvaworld.subtitle=Visit the Vanilla Vistas Amplified planet
ftbuniversity.vvaworld.desc1=This planet uses the &bVanilla Vistas Amplified&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.vvaworld.desc2=It's essentially Vanilla Vistas, but taller.

ftbuniversity.lostcities.title=Lost Cities
ftbuniversity.lostcities.subtitle=Visit the Lost Cities planet
ftbuniversity.lostcities.desc1=This planet uses the &bLost Cities&r dimension, from the mod of the same name.
ftbuniversity.lostcities.desc2=The entire planet is covered in a massive ruined city, full of dungeons and loot.

ftbuniversity.sargasso.title=Super-Sargasso Sea
ftbuniversity.sargasso.subtitle=Visit the Super-Sargasso Sea
ftbuniversity.sargasso.desc1=In fiction, the &bSuper-Sargasso Sea&r is the place where all lost things are found.
ftbuniversity.sargasso.desc2=Thus, this dimension has a unique ore. When mined, this ore &6drops a chest full of loot&r. Every naturally-generating chest has a corresponding ore, like dungeons and nether fortresses.
ftbuniversity.sargasso.rewards=Chest Ores

ftbuniversity.alienjungle.title=Alien Jungle
ftbuniversity.alienjungle.subtitle=Visit the Alien Jungle planet
ftbuniversity.alienjungle.desc1=This planet uses the &bAlien Jungle&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.alienjungle.desc2=This preset is full of twisting tendrils, unique trees, and general alien-ness.

ftbuniversity.otgmoon.title=Moon Spheres
ftbuniversity.otgmoon.subtitle=Visit the Moon Spheres planet
ftbuniversity.otgmoon.desc1=This planet uses the &bMoon&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.otgmoon.desc2=This preset has low gravity, and occasionally has a biosphere embedded in a crater.

ftbuniversity.otgwaste.title=The Far Distant Year of 2022
ftbuniversity.otgwaste.subtitle=Visit the Wasteland planet
ftbuniversity.otgwaste.desc1=This planet uses the &bWasteland&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.otgwaste.desc2=This preset is full of ruined cities and custom structures.

ftbuniversity.otgcave.title=The Underground
ftbuniversity.otgcave.subtitle=Visit the Cave planet
ftbuniversity.otgcave.desc1=This planet uses the &bCave&r preset for &eOpen Terrain Generator&r.
ftbuniversity.otgcave.desc2=This preset has massive caverns full of life, as well as full-bright vision so you can properly appreciate it.

ftbuniversity.arbeacon.subtitle=Make a Beacon
ftbuniversity.arbeacon.desc1=The &bBeacon&r is a fairly obscure multiblock. If built on a planet that is not known by default, everyone else on the server will be able to see it.
ftbuniversity.arbeacon.desc2=Also, players with the &6Beacon Finder module&r on their Space Helmet will be able to see the location of Beacons on the planet they are on.

ftbuniversity.arelevator.title=Better Than Space Stairs, At Least
ftbuniversity.arelevator.subtitle=Make a Space Elevator
ftbuniversity.arelevator.desc1=The &bSpace Elevator&r is a more efficient way of travelling between a planet and its moons and stations. It can also be used to travel between stations.
ftbuniversity.arelevator.desc2=Construct two Space Elevators and insert a blank &bSpace Elevator Chip&r into each.
ftbuniversity.arelevator.desc3=Sneak right-click a &6Linker&r on one Elevator, and and then do it again on the target Elevator to link the two.
ftbuniversity.arelevator.desc4=You &6can link more than two Elevators together&r. That means, for instance, your ship can have an Elevator that is linked to Elevators on every planet. You'll still only be able to go to those planets if you're in orbit around them, but it's still &6better than launching a Rocket every time&r.
ftbuniversity.arelevator.desc5=Open the Elevator's GUI to choose your destination, then walk onto the platform to launch.
ftbuniversity.arelevator.reward=Space Elevator materials

ftbuniversity.docking.subtitle=Make a Docking Pad
ftbuniversity.docking.desc1=The &bDocking Pad&r can be used to &6specify where Rockets will land&r on a Space Station. 
ftbuniversity.docking.desc2=Sneak right-click a Rocket that is aimed at the Space Station, then click &6Select Dst&r. This will show a list of all avaialble locations on the Station. Choose one, and when you take off, the Rocket will land there instead of the middle of the Station.
ftbuniversity.docking.desc3=You can have &6multiple Docking Pads&r. You can also name them to make it easier to tell them apart. If there is no available Docking Pad, incoming Rockets will land in the center of the Station.
ftbuniversity.docking.desc4=&6Linking anything to the Docking Pad links to the Rocket on it.&r
ftbuniversity.docking.desc5=If a Linker that is linked to a Docking Pad is placed inside another Docking Pad, any Rocket that leaves the second Pad will head to the first. Doing this both ways can allow for &6automated travel between the two&r, for cargo transport or payload launches.

ftbuniversity.arforcefield.subtitle=Make a Force Field Projector
ftbuniversity.arforcefield.desc1=The &bForce Field Projector&r, when given a redstone signal, &6places up to 32 Force Field blocks&r in the direction it is facing. It does not need RF.
ftbuniversity.arforcefield.desc2=Force Field blocks are airtight, which is very useful.

ftbuniversity.rockmonsta.subtitle=Make a Rocket Monitoring Station
ftbuniversity.rockmonsta.desc1=The &bRocket Monitoring Station&r is &6required for unmanned Rocket launches&r.
ftbuniversity.rockmonsta.desc2=Link the RMS to a Rocket (or, preferably, a Launch or Docking Pad). In its GUI, you can see the Rocket's current altitude, velocity, and fuel level.
ftbuniversity.rockmonsta.desc3=At the bottom, you can see the progress of the Rocket's current mission, if any. We'll come back to those later.
ftbuniversity.rockmonsta.desc4=By default, giving the RMS a &6redstone signal&r will launch the Rocket. You can change this with the button at the top right.

ftbuniversity.unmanass.subtitle=Make an Unmanned Vehicle Assembler
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc1=The &bUnmanned Vehicle Assembler&r allows you to create &6horizontal unmanned Drones&r, which are used to &6collect Oxygen, Hydrogen, or Nitrogen from gas giants&r.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc2=Place the UVA, then place &6Structure Towers&r to the left and right to set the width, then up to set the height (minus one).
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc3=From the top Structure Tower, place more Tower blocks to set the depth. The building area is the volume within (but not including) the Structure Towers.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc4=The back of the vehicle faces the UVA. Place Engines and Liquid Fuel Tanks just like you would. They'll be pointing down instead of back, but that changes when the vehicle is built.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc5=Place &bPressurized Tanks&r anywhere in the vehicle. The more you place, the more it can store, and the longer missions will take.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc6=On the front, place &bGas Intakes&r. The more you place, the faster it works.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc7=And that's it! You don't need a Guidance Computer or anything. Sneak right-click the Drone to open its GUI, set what gas you want it to collect, and &6launch it with a linked Rocket Monitoring Station&r. It will first go down several dozen blocks, then shoot off into orbit.
ftbuniversity.unmanass.desc8=Obviously, these &conly work when orbiting a gas giant&r.

ftbuniversity.rocketload.title=Cooler Than Ender Chests
ftbuniversity.rocketload.subtitle=Make Rocket Loaders and Unloaders
ftbuniversity.rocketload.desc1=&bRocket Loaders&r can be used to pipe items into Rockets (or more accurately, Chests that are &oin&r the Rocket). Likewise, the &bRocket Unloader&r takes items out.
ftbuniversity.rocketload.desc2=The &bRocket Fluid Loader&r and &bUnloader&r are the same, but for fluids.
ftbuniversity.rocketload.task1=Rocket Item IO
ftbuniversity.rocketload.task2=Rocket Fluid IO

ftbuniversity.satellites.title=Satellites
ftbuniversity.satellites.subtitle=Make a Satellite
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc1=The &bSatellite Builder&r (which must be placed on top of a Plug) is used to make &bSatellites&r, which orbit planets to &6collect Data&r, &6generate energy&r, and eventually &6terraform planets&r.
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc2=Place the empty Satellite in the top left slot, and place an unprogrammed &bSatellite ID Chip&r in the top center slot.
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc3=Place the main component of the Satellite in the top right slot. You can only have one per Satellite; its task says what each component does. You'll likely want &6several of each Data-collecting Satellite&r.
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc4=In the top 3 slots on the right, place the Satellite's energy gen and storage items. In the 3 slots below, place &bData Storage Units&r.
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc5=Click &6Build&r, and it will put everything into the Satellite item and program the ID Chip to it. You may want to copy this ID Chip, in case it gets lost. See the quest "Copy That Floppy" for details.
ftbuniversity.satellites.desc6=&6Put this Satellite into the Satellite Bay of a Rocket&r, then launch it. By the time you land (either on your Station or the planet), the Satellite should have gone into orbit separately.
ftbuniversity.satellites.task1=Satellite components
ftbuniversity.satellites.task2=Satellite energy generation
ftbuniversity.satellites.task3=Satellite energy storage
ftbuniversity.satellites.optics=Optical Sensor (Distance data collection)
ftbuniversity.satellites.comp=Composition Sensor (Composition data collection)
ftbuniversity.satellites.mass=Mass Sensor (Mass data collection)
ftbuniversity.satellites.micro=Microwave Transmitter (Energy collection)
ftbuniversity.satellites.ore=Ore Mapper (Utility - See other quest)
ftbuniversity.satellites.biome=Biome Changer (Utility - See other quest)
ftbuniversity.satellites.solar1=Basic Solar Panel (0.1 RF/t)
ftbuniversity.satellites.solar2=Large Solar Panel (1 RF/t)
ftbuniversity.satellites.bat1=Small Battery (100 RF)
ftbuniversity.satellites.bat2=2x Small Battery (400 RF)

ftbuniversity.satterm.title=Big Data
ftbuniversity.satterm.subtitle=Make a Satellite Terminal
ftbuniversity.satterm.desc1=With your Satellite in orbit, you can begin collecting &6Data&r.
ftbuniversity.satterm.desc2=There are three types of data: &6distance&r, &6composition&r, and &6mass&r. These are collected using Satellites with specific components (see previous quest).
ftbuniversity.satterm.desc3=Place the &bSatellite Terminal&r and insert a programmed Satellite ID Chip. The Terminal's GUI will now display the Satellite's power as well as its max and current data amount.
ftbuniversity.satterm.desc4=Click &6Connect!&r to drain Data from the Satellite, moving it to the Terminal. Insert a &6Data Storage Unit&r into the left slot then click on the &6Store to Chip&r button to move Data from the Terminal to the DSU.
ftbuniversity.satterm.desc5=You can now use this Data elsewhere.

ftbuniversity.microrece.title=Dyson Swarm
ftbuniversity.microrece.subtitle=Make a Microwave Receiver
ftbuniversity.microrece.desc1=The &bMicrowave Receiver&r allows you to &6collect RF generated by Satellites&r that have the &6Microwave Transmitter&r.
ftbuniversity.microrece.desc2=In the Receiver's &bInput Hatch&r, insert the Satellites ID Chip. You can connect to as many Satellites as you have Input Hatches, which means it can output a fairly high amount of RF/t.
ftbuniversity.microrece.desc3=Obviously, the Satellites must be in orbit around the same planet the Receiver is on.

ftbuniversity.observatory.title=Asteroid Mining
ftbuniversity.observatory.subtitle=Make an Observatory
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc1=The &bObservatory&r consumes Distance Data to &6locate Asteroids&r, which you can mine for their minerals. They are also the only way to get Iridium, at least with AR by itself.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc2=It must be placed &6somewhere dark that can see the sky&r. Using &bLenses&r instead of Glass will increase the range, as will using a higher tier &bMotor&r.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc3=In the first page, you can see how much RF and Data it has, the observable distance, and turn it off and on.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc4=In the second page, click &6Scan!&r to spend 100 Distance Data to search for nearby Asteroids, which will show on the list on the left. Right click and drag to scroll, left click to select.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc5=Once an Asteroid is selected, the right side of the GUI will show the blocks it has and their amounts. Having Composition and Mass Datas (which would require using 3 Data Buses instead of 1) will decrease the amount of uncertainty. Asteroids are &6rather small&r, but fairly easy to mine once everything's set up.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc6=Once you've decided on an Asteroid (you can Scan again to refresh), place an &bAsteroid Chip&r into the bottom left slot and click the gear button to program it.
ftbuniversity.observatory.desc7=Normally, &cAsteroids have a surprisingly small amount of ores&r. However, the process of &6finding and mining them is cheap&r (Rocket Fuel basically just costs Water, after all), and everything past the Observatory can be &6automated&r. We've also gone through and added some custom Asteroids ourselves (and upped the numbers).
ftbuniversity.observatory.task=Glass or Lenses
ftbuniversity.observatory.rewards=Datas
ftbuniversity.observatory.reward1=Distance
ftbuniversity.observatory.reward2=Composition
ftbuniversity.observatory.reward3=Mass

ftbuniversity.adp.subtitle=Make an Astrobody Data Processor
ftbuniversity.adp.desc1=The &bAstrobody Data Processor&r is used to &6fill programmed Asteroid Chips with the Data they need&r.
ftbuniversity.adp.desc2=Insert the Asteroid Chip into the bottom slot, give it the three main Datas (either by inserting a DSU or using Wireless Transcievers), then toggle the switches for each.
ftbuniversity.adp.desc3=(The Chip's tooltip mentions 3 unused Datas, but those don't actually exist)
ftbuniversity.adp.desc4=The ADP is &cvery, very slow&r. It takes about a second to program each unit of Data, and you'll want to fill it with 1000 of each. Thus, you'll want to &6make several ADPs and program several Chips at the same time&r.
ftbuniversity.adp.desc5=The more Distance Data, the more likely you are to successfully land on the Asteroid. The more Mass, the more blocks will be mined. The more Composition, the more ore and less Cobblestone.

ftbuniversity.arwireless.title=Bluetooth Connection
ftbuniversity.arwireless.subtitle=Make Wireless Transcievers
ftbuniversity.arwireless.desc1=&bWireless Transcievers&r are used to wirelessly &6transfer Data&r. The only limit is that they both be in the same dimension, and both must be loaded.
ftbuniversity.arwireless.desc2=Transcievers can only be connected in pairs. They are linked with a &6Linker&r. You will have to turn them on in their GUIs, as well as toggle them from between extract and insert.

ftbuniversity.astmining.title=Pierce the Heavens
ftbuniversity.astmining.subtitle=Make a Rocket that can mine Asteroids
ftbuniversity.astmining.desc1=To mine Asteroids, you need to be able to handle unmanned Rockets. &6Complete the Rocket Monitoring Station quest&r before continuing.
ftbuniversity.astmining.desc2=A Mining Rocket must be topped with a &bDrill&r, and also must have Chests or any other block with an inventory. Mined blocks will be moved to here.
ftbuniversity.astmining.desc3=Use the RMS to launch the Rocket and watch its progress. Once it's done, it will return to where it launched from. You can extract the items with a &6Rocket Unloader&r.

ftbuniversity.blhgen.title=Unfortunately, Does Not Generate Black Holes
ftbuniversity.blhgen.subtitle=Make a Black Hole Generator
ftbuniversity.blhgen.desc1=The &bBlack Hole Generator&r allows you to essentially destroy items, converting them into RF.
ftbuniversity.blhgen.desc2=It &6must be on a Space Station in orbit around a Black Hole&r, with the Black Hole directly underneath.
ftbuniversity.blhgen.desc3=Stone, Cobblestone, Dirt, and Netherrack are the least effective, generating about 32,000 RF per stack. Literally every other item will generate &6249,500 RF per item&r.
ftbuniversity.blhgen.desc4=However, it &ccan only output at 500 RF/t&r. So, while you could just put a Cobblestone Generator next to it and get infinite RF, it's still only slightly better than a bunch of Solar Panels.

ftbuniversity.railgun.title=Interplanetary Delivery System
ftbuniversity.railgun.subtitle=Make a Railgun
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc1=The &bRailgun&r is used to send items within a planet and its orbiting bodies (moons and space stations, basically).
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc2=It costs a fairly high amount of RF to work. The formula is &7500,000 + (10 * distance)&r. It can also move items within the same dimension, costing 1 RF per block distance.
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc3=Railguns &6work in pairs&r: one sends, the other receives. If you want one to only send, it only needs an Input Hatch. If it only receives, it only needs an Output Hatch.
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc4=Use a &6Linker&r on the destination Railgun, then put it in the left slot of the sender.
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc5=In the text box, you can set the &6Minimum transfer size&r. It will not send until it has that amount of any item, so you can make sure it only sends when full.
ftbuniversity.railgun.desc6=Unfortunately, in most modpacks, it is extremely outclassed by the Ender Chest. Thus, this quest is optional.

ftbuniversity.arbioscan.subtitle=Make a Biome Scanner
ftbuniversity.arbioscan.desc1=The &bBiome Scanner&r will show a list of all biomes that generate on the planet you are in orbit around.
ftbuniversity.arbioscan.desc2=Note that OTG handles biomes differently, so OTG planets will look like they have no biomes.

ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.subtitle=Make a Laser Drill
ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.desc1=The &bLaser Drill&r will mine blocks from the planet it is in orbit around.
ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.desc2=It takes 1000 RF to mine a single block, and can mine up to 20 blocks a second (costing 20,000 RF/t). You also must have a &bBasic Lens&r in the slot in its GUI.
ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.desc3=In the GUI, set the x and z coordinates of where you want to mine. &6These chunks must be loaded&r. You can set to mine only that x and z, mine along the x or z, or start at that x and z and spiral outward.
ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.desc4=By default, the blocks mined will be destroyed. However, in the interests of &onot&r making giant holes &oanywhere in any planet&r, we've disabled that.
ftbuniversity.arlasdrill.desc5=Instead, it simply collects Cobblestone and ores. It basically generates them from nothing, but &cthe chunks still must be loaded&r. For some reason.

ftbuniversity.areagravity.subtitle=Make the Area Gravity Controller
ftbuniversity.areagravity.desc1=The &bArea Gravity Controller&r manipulates gravity in a spherical radius at the cost of RF.
ftbuniversity.areagravity.desc2=You can set the direction of gravity at the top right; there are two modes: additive and replacement. Adding 1 down is the same as replacing down with 2, for instance.
ftbuniversity.areagravity.desc3=At the bottom, you can set the radius and the target strength for the gravity.

ftbuniversity.atmterr.subtitle=Make the Atmosphere Terraformer
ftbuniversity.atmterr.desc1=The &bAtmosphere Terraformer&r is the largest, most expensive multiblock. Its final size is 17x12x17.
ftbuniversity.atmterr.desc2=Its function is to &6increase or decrease the atmospheric pressure of the planet is is orbitting around&r (though it won't work for planets using dimensions made by other mods, or vanilla), changing its biomes.
ftbuniversity.atmterr.desc3=It takes about &615 minutes&r to change the pressure by 0.1%%, requiring 40mB of &6Nitrogen&r and &6Oxygen&r per tick, as well as 1,000RF/t (or &6720,000mB of each&r and &618,000,000RF&r total).
ftbuniversity.atmterr.desc4=Once the atmospheric pressure reaches a critical point (0.25atm, 0.75atm, 2.00atm), the planet's biomes will be changed, though this is more easily noticed in new chunks.

