ftbuniversity.magicchap.title=Magic

###Botania
ftbuniversity.botchap.title=Botania

ftbuniversity.lexbot.subtitle=Get a Lexica Botania
ftbuniversity.lexbot.desc1=The &bLexica Botania&r is a comprehensive guide to all things Botania.
ftbuniversity.lexbot.desc2=If ever a quest doesn't give a good enough explanation for how something works, check that item's Lexica Botania page.
ftbuniversity.lexbot.desc3=Also, don't you dare say this should have been in the Technology group.

ftbuniversity.petalapoth.title=Birth Bath
ftbuniversity.petalapoth.subtitle=Make a Petal Apothecary
ftbuniversity.petalapoth.desc1=The &bPetal Apothecary&r is used to craft all the magical flowers added by Botania.
ftbuniversity.petalapoth.desc2=It has &6no GUI&r. Simply throw a bucket of water in, throw in all the ingredients, then throw in some Seeds to craft a flower.

ftbuniversity.puredaisy.title=Hi, I'm Daisy!
ftbuniversity.puredaisy.subtitle=Make a Pure Daisy
ftbuniversity.puredaisy.desc=The &bPure Daisy&r will convert adjacent &6Stone to Livingrock&r, and &6Wood Logs to Livingwood&r, as well as some others. See its recipe uses in JEI to see them.

ftbuniversity.manastorage.title=Mana Storage and Transfer
ftbuniversity.manastorage.subtitle=Make a Mana Pool, Mana Spreader, and Wand of the Forest
ftbuniversity.manastorage.desc1=The &bMana Pool&r can &6store up to &k1,000,00&r&6 Mana&r. Functional flowers will automatically connect to a nearby Mana Pool. You can also &6throw certain items in&r a filled Mana Pool to convert them into other items.
ftbuniversity.manastorage.desc2=The &bMana Spreader&r will send Mana. Mana-generating flowers will automatically connect to a nearby Mana Spreader. Spreaders will only send Mana if it has a &6valid destination&r. Mana Spreaders placed next to Mana Pools will &6shoot using the Pool's storage&r
ftbuniversity.manastorage.desc3=The &bWand of the Forest&r is essentially Botania's wrench. It has two modes: &6Bind&r and &6Function&r. In Bind mode, sneak right-click one block, then right-click another to bind the first to the second. Function mode has specific uses per block, which you can read in the Lexica Botania.

ftbuniversity.floatingflowers.title=Flower in the Sky
ftbuniversity.floatingflowers.subtitle=Make a Floating Flower
ftbuniversity.floatingflowers.desc=You can combine any functional flower with any floating regular flower to make a &bFloating functional flower&r, which &6can be placed anywhere&r without needing Grass or Dirt.
ftbuniversity.floatingflowers.task=Any Floating functional flower

ftbuniversity.botalccat.title=Equivalent Exchange
ftbuniversity.botalccat.subtitle=Make an Alchemy Catalyst
ftbuniversity.botalccat.desc1=The &bAlchemy Catalyst&r, when &6placed under a Mana Pool&r, changes/adds the recipes you get from throwing items into the Pool.
ftbuniversity.botalccat.desc2=See the Catalyst's uses in JEI to see these new recipes.

ftbuniversity.botconjcat.title=How many EMC per Mana?
ftbuniversity.botconjcat.subtitle=Make a Conjuration Catalyst
ftbuniversity.botconjcat.desc=The &bConjuration Catalyst&r works similarly to the Alchemy Catalyst, but instead of converting items, it &6duplicates them&r.

ftbuniversity.runicaltar.subtitle=Make a Runic Altar
ftbuniversity.runicaltar.desc1=The &bRunic Altar&r uses Mana and items to &6craft Runes&r, which are used in some crafting recipes.
ftbuniversity.runicaltar.desc2=Throw the ingredients on, feed it Mana via a Mana Spreader, and let it craft. When it's done absorbing Mana, throw some Livingrock on and click it with a Wand of the Forest.

ftbuniversity.terrasteel.title=Planetary Cluster Bowl
ftbuniversity.terrasteel.subtitle=Make a Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate
ftbuniversity.terrasteel.desc1=The &bTerrestrial Agglomeration Plate&r will use half a Mana Pool's worth of Mana to convert a Mana Pearl, a Manasteel Ingot, and a Mana Diamond into a Terrasteel Ingot.
ftbuniversity.terrasteel.desc2=Place 5 Livingrock in an X shape, 4 Lapis blocks in sides, and the Plate on top. Connect it to a Mana Pool using &6Sparks&r. Throw the ingredients on top, and it will begin.

ftbuniversity.alfheim.title=&mA Wonderful Vacation Getaway&r
ftbuniversity.alfheim.subtitle=Construct a portal to Alfheim
ftbuniversity.alfheim.desc1=The &bportal to Alfheim&r is more of a crafting mechanic than a portal; you can't actually go to Alfheim.
ftbuniversity.alfheim.desc2=Follow the building constructions according to the Lexica Botania, provide it with Mana, and throw in specific items to get other items back. &6It would be a good idea to start with the Lexica Botania itself.&r

ftbuniversity.gaia1.title=Strike the Earth
ftbuniversity.gaia1.subtitle=Fight the Guardian of Gaia
ftbuniversity.gaia1.desc1=The &bGuardian of Gaia&r is the boss added by Botania. To summon it, you have to make a special arena (see the Lexica Botania) and click a Terrasteel Ingot on the Beacon.
ftbuniversity.gaia1.desc2=The fight is fairly difficult, so it's suggested to use enchanted gear and potions/&6brews&r. If you have more players, the fight will be harder but you will get more drops.
ftbuniversity.gaia1.rewards=Incenses
ftbuniversity.gaia1.reward1=Incense Stick (Strength II)
ftbuniversity.gaia1.reward2=Incense Stick (Regeneration II)
ftbuniversity.gaia1.reward3=Incense Stick (Resistance II)

ftbuniversity.gaia2.title=Treasure Trove
ftbuniversity.gaia2.subtitle=Fight the harder Guardian of Gaia
ftbuniversity.gaia2.desc1=The &bharder Guardian of Gaia&r has a &lmuch harder&r battle, and drops even more loot, including the &6Dice of Fate&r which can spawn one of six unique and super useful items.
ftbuniversity.gaia2.desc2=To summon it, click a &6Gaia Ingot&r on the beacon in your fighting area.

ftbuniversity.endoflame.title=Burning Love
ftbuniversity.endoflame.subtitle=Make an Endoflame
ftbuniversity.endoflame.desc=The &bEndoflame&r generates Mana using any burnable item. The more items it would smelt, the more Mana.

ftbuniversity.autoendo.title=Auto Endo
ftbuniversity.autoendo.subtitle=Automate the Endoflame
ftbuniversity.autoendo.desc1=The Endoflame is probably the simplest flower, and the &beasiest to automate&r.
ftbuniversity.autoendo.desc2=Place a Wooden Pressure Plate nearby, invert the signal, then connect that to a Hopper feeding burnables into an &bOpen Crate&r directly above the Pressure Plate.
ftbuniversity.autoendo.desc3=Any time an item on the pressure plate is removed (ie, burned by the Endoflame), the signal to the Hopper will be cut off, which will allow it to drop more fuel.

ftbuniversity.entropinnyum.title=I Have One Question, and One Question Only: &cEXPLOSIONS?!&r
ftbuniversity.entropinnyum.subtitle=Make an Entropinnyum
ftbuniversity.entropinnyum.desc1=The &bEntropinnyum&r generates Mana from nearby &6explosions&r, which also prevents those explosions from breaking blocks.
ftbuniversity.entropinnyum.desc2=If the Entropinnyum currently has Mana in it, &4it will not prevent block damage&r. &oHowever&r, other forms of explosion protection still work.

ftbuniversity.thermalily.title=Burninger Love
ftbuniversity.thermalily.subtitle=Make a Thermalily
ftbuniversity.thermalily.desc1=The &bThermalily&r generates a large amount of Mana from Lava sources placed within a 3x3 area surrounding itself.
ftbuniversity.thermalily.desc2=It continually generates Mana for 30 seconds, and then has a &65 minute waiting period&r. If Lava is placed down during this waiting period, it will be used up without generating Mana, resetting the cooldown.

ftbuniversity.rosaarcana.subtitle=Make a Rosa Arcana
ftbuniversity.rosaarcana.desc=The &bRosa Arcana&r generates Mana from the &6experience of nearby players&r, as well as nearby xp orbs.

ftbuniversity.kekimurus.subtitle=Make a Kekimurus
ftbuniversity.kekimurus.desc=The &bKekimurus&r generates Mana using nearby placed Cake.

ftbuniversity.rafflowsia.title=Vandalistic Violet
ftbuniversity.rafflowsia.subtitle=Make a Rafflowsia
ftbuniversity.rafflowsia.desc1=The &bRafflowsia&r, aside from having a &oreally&r hard to spell name, generates Mana by destroying nearby placed man-made flowers. The more often the Rafflowsia breaks the same flower, the less Mana it generates.
ftbuniversity.rafflowsia.desc2=Don't place this near flowers you don't want to be destroyed, obviously.

ftbuniversity.spectrolus.title=&4&lR&c&la&6&li&e&ln&2&lb&a&lo&b&lw
ftbuniversity.spectrolus.subtitle=Make a Spectrolus
ftbuniversity.spectrolus.desc1=The &bSpectrolus&r generates Mana using Wool. It only accepts Wool of &6specific colors, in a specific order&r. Looking at it while holding a Wand of the Forest will show the next color.
ftbuniversity.spectrolus.desc2=This order is: White, Orange, Magenta, Light Blue, Yellow, Lime, Pink, Grey, Light Grey, Cyan, Purple, Blue, Brown, Green, Red, Black.

ftbuniversity.shulkmenot.title=The Tooltip Stole My Joke
ftbuniversity.shulkmenot.subtitle=Make a Shulk Me Not
ftbuniversity.shulkmenot.desc1=The &bShulk Me Not&r generates Mana &6when a Shulker attacks any other mob&r. This will kill both mobs, dropping no items or experience.
ftbuniversity.shulkmenot.desc2=This flower is pretty hard to automate, but it can make an &6insane amount of Mana&r.

ftbuniversity.autoshulk.title=Other Mods Do Things Too!
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.subtitle=Automate the Shulk Me Not
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.desc1=When fully automated, the &bShulk Me Not&r can generate an absolutely stupid amount of Mana. This quest will explain a method of automating it using RFTools.
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.desc2=Use a combination of &bSpawners&r and &bMatter Beamers&r to spawn any hostile mob and a Shulker.
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.desc3=Use 2 &bSensors&r set to &6Type: Entities&r and &6Number: 1&r to detect of there's a mob in its area. Invert the redstone signal and use it to power the Matter Beamers. This will make it spawn more Shulkers and hostile mobs whenever there are none, so it always runs.
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.desc4=Place a &bHeisei Dream&r somewhere nearby and provide it with Mana, and it will make the Shulker attack the other mob, which will set off the Shulk Me Not. Now, your biggest problem is moving and storing the monstrous amount of Mana this will give you.
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.link=Image Guide
ftbuniversity.autoshulk.link2=Click this to open a web page that shows every step with images

ftbuniversity.botmobfarm.title=Botanical Mob Farms
ftbuniversity.botmobfarm.subtitle=These are useful for mob farms
ftbuniversity.botmobfarm.desc=These flowers and and items make mob farms simple and easy.

ftbuniversity.dreadthorne.title=Dreadful
ftbuniversity.dreadthorne.subtitle=Make a Dreadthorne
ftbuniversity.dreadthorne.desc=The &bDreadthorne&r will use Mana to deal 2 hearts of damage to a random nearby adult mob. This is useful for passive animal farms.

ftbuniversity.daffomill.title=Blown Away
ftbuniversity.daffomill.subtitle=Make a Daffomill
ftbuniversity.daffomill.desc=The &bDaffomill&r will use Mana to push items. You can use a Wand of the Forest to change the direction, which you can see by the particles it emits.

ftbuniversity.pollidisiac.title=Eat the &oFood&r
ftbuniversity.pollidisiac.subtitle=Make a Pollidisiac
ftbuniversity.pollidisiac.desc=The &bPollidisiac&r will use Mana to make passive animals eat nearby dropped food items, like wheat or carrots.

ftbuniversity.hyacidus.title=If You Want a Job Done Right
ftbuniversity.hyacidus.subtitle=Make a Hyacidus
ftbuniversity.hyacidus.desc=The &bHyacidus&r will poison nearby mobs, allowing you to manually kill them for player-only drops and experience.

ftbuniversity.hopperhock.title=Vacuum Hopper
ftbuniversity.hopperhock.subtitle=Make a Hopperhock
ftbuniversity.hopperhock.desc1=The &bHopperhock&r will pick up nearby items and insert them into the adjacent inventory. Mana will increase its range.
ftbuniversity.hopperhock.desc2=You can place an &6Item Frame on the inventory&r and give it an item to &6set a whitelist with priority&r over non-item-framed inventories. Shift clicking it with a Wand of the Forest will toggle it from whitelisting to blacklisting.

ftbuniversity.vinculotus.title=No, Not Allowed!
ftbuniversity.vinculotus.subtitle=Make a Vinculotus
ftbuniversity.vinculotus.desc=The &bVinculotus&r will, using Mana, intercept any teleporting Enderman and force them to teleport to its position instead.

ftbuniversity.lifeaggre.subtitle=Make a Life Aggregator
ftbuniversity.lifeaggre.desc=The &bLife Aggregator&r will allow you to &6pick up a Monster Spawner&r and place it down somewhere else, although only once.

ftbuniversity.lifeimbuer.subtitle=Make a Life Imbuer
ftbuniversity.lifeimbuer.desc=The &bLife Imbuer&r, when placed on a Monster Spawner, will &6allow it to spawn mobs when a player is not nearby&r. This requires a fairly small amount of Mana to run.

ftbuniversity.agricarnation.title=Farmers Only
ftbuniversity.agricarnation.subtitle=Make an Agricarnation
ftbuniversity.agricarnation.desc=The &bAgricarnation&r will use Mana to speed up the growth of nearby plants.

ftbuniversity.jadedamaranthus.title=Botanical Floral Fertilizer
ftbuniversity.jadedamaranthus.subtitle=Make a Jaded Amaranthus
ftbuniversity.jadedamaranthus.desc=The &bJaded Amaranthus&r will use Mana to generate mystical flowers nearby.

ftbuniversity.fallenkanade.subtitle=Make a Fallen Kanade
ftbuniversity.fallenkanade.desc1=The &bFallen Kanade&r will use Mana to apply a regeneration effect to nearby players.
ftbuniversity.fallenkanade.desc2=For people using Blood Magic, &cthis flower does not function near Blood Altars&r.

ftbuniversity.rannuncarpus.subtitle=Make a Rannuncarpus
ftbuniversity.rannuncarpus.desc=The &bRannuncarpus&r will take nearby nearby dropped blocks and places them on a specific nearby block, chosen by whatever block is under the soil the flower is planted on.

ftbuniversity.rannlink.title=Automating the Pure Daisy
ftbuniversity.rannlink.subtitle=Credit to VallenFrostweaver for this design!

ftbuniversity.orechid.subtitle=Make the Orechids
ftbuniversity.orechid.desc1=The &bOrechid&r will use a rather large amount of Mana (about 18%% of a pool) to replace a nearby Stone block with an Ore. 
ftbuniversity.orechid.desc2=The &bOrechid Ignem&r does the same, except for Nether ores.
ftbuniversity.orechid.desc3=&6More common ores generate more often.&r See their uses in JEI to see their weights; it will show roughly how many of that ore you will get from converting a stack of Stone.

# Thank you to Youtube user Jansey for the Corporea tutorials!
ftbuniversity.corporea.title=Magical Digital Storage
ftbuniversity.corporea.subtitle=Set up a Corporea system
ftbuniversity.corporea.desc1=&bCorporea Sparks&r are the first part of &6Corporea networks&r, which allow you to request items from connected inventories. Networks can only handle active requests, nothing is done passively, nor can it ever &oadd&r items to the network.
ftbuniversity.corporea.desc2=Corporea Sparks automatically connect to other nearby Sparks of the same color, which can be changed using Floral Powder. Each network also requires a single &bMaster Corporea Spark&r.
ftbuniversity.corporea.desc3=Corporea Sparks can access items in the inventory directly below them. This does &cnot&r apply to the Master Corporea Spark, which has to be placed on an inventory but cannot access it... for some reason.

ftbuniversity.corpindex.title=Voice Command
ftbuniversity.corpindex.subtitle=Make a Corporea Index
ftbuniversity.corpindex.desc1=When near the &bCorporea Index&r, you can &6say in chat&r an item and the amount to request it from inventories connected to the Corporea Spark on top of it.
ftbuniversity.corpindex.desc2=You can ask for "&632 Stone&r" or "&6half a stack of stone&r," and both will work.
ftbuniversity.corpindex.desc3=Since the Index technically doesn't have an inventory, you can place the Master Corporea Spark on it without losing any functionality.

ftbuniversity.corpfun.title=Auto-request
ftbuniversity.corpfun.subtitle=Make a Corporea Funnel
ftbuniversity.corpfun.desc1=The &bCorporea Funnel&r will pull an item out of the network and insert it into the inventory up to 2 blocks below it, or spit it out into the world.
ftbuniversity.corpfun.desc2=Place a filled Item Frame on it to set which item is requested. Rotate it once to pull 2, again for 4, then 8, 16, 32, and 64. If it has multiple Item Frames, it will choose a random one to request.
ftbuniversity.corpfun.desc3=You could &6place these over your bulk storage&r inventories, like Drawers, to keep them full from an input chest.

ftbuniversity.corpinter.title=Autocrafting, Kinda
ftbuniversity.corpinter.subtitle=Make a Corporea Interceptor
ftbuniversity.corpinter.desc1=The &bCorporea Interceptor&r will emit a redstone pulse when the item in an Item Frame placed on it is requested, but none are available.
ftbuniversity.corpinter.desc2=This can be used in tandem with the &6Corporea Funnel&r to craft items that you are out of. For example, place a 1x1 &6Crafty Crate&r, place a &6Hopper&r aiming at it, place a &6Corporea Funnel&r with a Spark and an Item Frame with Stone on top of that, and place a &6Corporea Interceptor&r with a Spark and an Item Frame with a Button on top of &othat&r.
ftbuniversity.corpinter.desc3=When a Button is requested but none are available, the Interceptor will emit a Redstone Pulse, activating the Funnel, which will send the Stone to the Crafty Crate, &6which will craft the Button and drop it out the bottom&r.
ftbuniversity.corpinter.desc4=An &6unfortunate limitation&r of this is that you can only request one at a time. You can rotate the Funnel's Item Frame to increase this, but it will still always craft that amount.

ftbuniversity.corpret.title=Hold It!
ftbuniversity.corpret.subtitle=Make a Corporea Retainer
ftbuniversity.corpret.desc1=The &bCorporea Retainer&r is placed next to a Corporea Interceptor and will remember if the Interceptor... intercepts. If it gets a signal after this, it will forget and the thing that requested the Interceptor's item will request it again.
ftbuniversity.corpret.desc2=For a use-case example, &6place the Retainer next to the Interceptor from the previous quest&r. Place a Corporea Crystal Cube monitoring Buttons nearby, and point a Comparator from it to the Retainer.
ftbuniversity.corpret.desc3=Now, when a Button is requested while none are available, the Interceptor will emit a signal which yada yada, eventually crafting a Button, putting it somewhere in the network, which will let the Crystal Cube know, which will tell the Retainer, &6which will send the newly crafted Button back to the thing that requested it&r.

ftbuniversity.corpcrystalcube.title=Clairvoyant Storage
ftbuniversity.corpcrystalcube.subtitle=Make a Corporeal Crystal Cube
ftbuniversity.corpcrystalcube.desc1=The &bCorporeal Crystal Cube&r can be right-clicked with an item, and it will &6display the amount of that item is in the network&r.
ftbuniversity.corpcrystalcube.desc2=Comparators will also emit a signal based on the amount of that item available, which can be &overy interesting&r.

ftbuniversity.luminizer.subtitle=Make a Luminizer
ftbuniversity.luminizer.desc1=Right-clicking a &bLuminizer&r will send you to a bound Luminizer. You can bind multiple in series to move larger distances, or around corners.
ftbuniversity.luminizer.desc2=Multiple Luminizers can be bound to the same destination, though each can only have one.

ftbuniversity.detectlumin.subtitle=Make a Detector Luminizer
ftbuniversity.detectlumin.desc=The &bDetector Luminizer&r works just like a regular Luminizer, except it gives off a redstone signal when used.

ftbuniversity.togglelumin.subtitle=Make a Toggle Luminizer
ftbuniversity.togglelumin.desc=The &bToggle Luminizer&r works just like a regular Luminizer, except it will drop the rider when given a redstone signal.

ftbuniversity.forklumin.subtitle=Make a Fork Luminizer
ftbuniversity.forklumin.desc1=The &bFork Luminizer&r can only go in one of two directions, chosen by an &bAnimated Torch&r up to 2 blocks above or below it.
ftbuniversity.forklumin.desc2=The Fork Luminizer isn't bound to any Luminizer, it will send the rider to the Luminizer in the direction the Animated Torch is aiming.
ftbuniversity.forklumin.desc3=The Animated Torch's direction can be reflected by giving it a pulse of Mana, generally from a &bPulse Mana Spreader&r.

ftbuniversity.luminlauncher.subtitle=Make a Luminizer Launcher
ftbuniversity.luminlauncher.desc=The &bLuminizer Launcher&r, when given a redstone signal, will force nearby entities (players, mobs, and items) to ride an adjacent Luminizer.

ftbuniversity.botbrewery.subtitle=Make a Botanical Brewery
ftbuniversity.botbrewery.desc1=The &bBotanical Brewery&r uses Mana and items to create brews, which are essentially multi-use potions.
ftbuniversity.botbrewery.desc2=Brews can come in three forms: &bVials&r, which are the most basic with 4 uses; &bIncense Sticks&r, which are burned on &6Incense Plates&r and are more like Beacons; and &bFlasks&r, which have 6 uses instead of 4.
ftbuniversity.botbrewery.task=Any brew in any form

ftbuniversity.craftycrate.subtitle=Make a Crafty Crate
ftbuniversity.craftycrate.desc1=The &bCrafty Crate&r will automatically craft using the items piped into it. The first item will go in the top left slot, the second in the top middle, etc. &rThe item will only be crafted once all slots are full.&r
ftbuniversity.craftycrate.desc2=By &6default&r, it will try to do a &63x3 crafting recipe&r. This is great for doing stuff like compressing Cobblestone etc, but no so great for pretty much everything else.
ftbuniversity.craftycrate.desc3=You can use &bCrafting Patterns&r to change the shape that it tries to craft. So for instance, a &61x1&r pattern will &6only put items in the top left slot&r, etc.
ftbuniversity.craftycrate.task=Any Crafting Pattern

###Blood Magic
ftbuniversity.bmchap.title=Blood Magic

ftbuniversity.bmbook.subtitle=Get the Sanguine Scientem
ftbuniversity.bmbook.desc1=The &bSanguine Scientem&r is &eBlood Magic&r's book.
ftbuniversity.bmbook.desc2=However, it's actually &cshockingly poor of a guide&r. For instance, the first thing you're supposed to read, &6Demonic Will and Snares&r, is the second page of the third chapter.
ftbuniversity.bmbook.desc3=However however, it does a fairly good job of explaining things, if you know what you're looking for. However, it is full of flavor-text, so discerning the useful bits may be a bit hard.

ftbuniversity.will.title=Where There's a Will
ftbuniversity.will.subtitle=Get Demonic Will
ftbuniversity.will.desc1=&bDemonic Will&r is the first crafting component you need to start Blood Magic.
ftbuniversity.will.desc2=To get some, throw &bRudimentary Snares&r at hostile mobs &6until they emit white particles&r, then kill them.
ftbuniversity.will.desc3=Demonic Will has a variable &6Will Quality&r. This is largely random.

ftbuniversity.hellfire.title=Hellfire! Dark Fire!
ftbuniversity.hellfire.subtitle=Make a Hellfire Forge
ftbuniversity.hellfire.desc1=The &bHellfire Forge&r uses &6Will&r to power certain crafting recipes.
ftbuniversity.hellfire.desc2=The slot on the far right is the &6fuel&r slot. There, insert either Demonic Will, or &6Tartaric Gems&r that store it.
ftbuniversity.hellfire.desc3=The four outer slots on the left are the &6input&r slots. The center is the &6output&r slot.

ftbuniversity.tartaric.title=Will Battery
ftbuniversity.tartaric.subtitle=Make a Petty Tartaric Gem
ftbuniversity.tartaric.desc1=&bTartaric Gems&r work sort of like &6batteries for Will&r. They absorb any Demonic Will that you pick up, while in your inventory.
ftbuniversity.tartaric.desc2=A Tartaric Gem with will can be used in the fuel slot of a Hellfire Forge.

ftbuniversity.tartaric2.title=Tartaric Tiers
ftbuniversity.tartaric2.subtitle=Make a higher-tier Tartaric Gem
ftbuniversity.tartaric2.desc1=Tartaric Gems come in several tiers, which correlate to Blood Altar tiers.
ftbuniversity.tartaric2.desc2=Higher tier Gems &6store more Will&r, as well as &6have access to higher-tier recipes&r.
ftbuniversity.tartaric2.task=Higher-tier Tartaric Gems

ftbuniversity.senttools.title=It's Fine, They Like It
ftbuniversity.senttools.subtitle=Make a Sentient tool
ftbuniversity.senttools.desc1=&bSentient tools&r become slightly more powerful if you have a higher-tier Tartaric Gem in your inventory.
ftbuniversity.senttools.desc2=Meaning, &6the higher tier Gem&r you have, the &6faster&r it is, and the &6harder it hits&r.
ftbuniversity.senttools.task=Sentient tools

ftbuniversity.sentsword.title=Born to Stab!
ftbuniversity.sentsword.subtitle=Make a Sentient Sword
ftbuniversity.sentsword.desc1=The &bSentient Sword&r deals &6more damage the higher tier Tartaric Gem&r you have in your inventory.
ftbuniversity.sentsword.desc2=Additionally, monsters killed with it will &6always have a chance of dropping Will&r, even without using Snares.
ftbuniversity.sentsword.desc3=This means you can insert it into, say, a Mechanical User or Player Simulator to &6automatically kill monsters for their Will&r.

ftbuniversity.spectools.title=Spectral Tools
ftbuniversity.spectools.subtitle=Learn about Spectral tools
ftbuniversity.spectools.desc=If you have a Tartaric Gem with &6at least 1000 will&r (meaning it would have to be Common or higher), you can &bthrow a Sentient tool or sword&r and it will come to life, &6following and protecting you&r.

ftbuniversity.sentarmor.title=Junketsu
ftbuniversity.sentarmor.subtitle=Make a Sentient Armor Gem
ftbuniversity.sentarmor.desc1=The &bSentient Armor Gem&r, when used while you have a Tartaric Gem, &6instantly equips a full set of Sentient armor&r.
ftbuniversity.sentarmor.desc2=Sentient armor is &6more protective the higher tier Gem you have&r. &oTechnically&r it doesn't have infinite durability, but you can just use the gem twice to get a new suit instantly.
ftbuniversity.sentarmor.desc3=If you are already wearing armor, it will be stored in the Gem, re-equipping when you use it again.
ftbuniversity.sentarmor.desc4=Additionally, any &6enchantments&r on your armor will be applied to the Sentient armor.

ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.title=Blood For the Blood Altar
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.subtitle=Make a Blood Altar
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc1=The &bBlood Altar&r is where you &6craft things using Life Essence&r, which is &6measured in Life Points (LP)&r.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc2=It has &65 tiers&r, the first being just the Blood Altar alone, and the fifth being 17x7x17 (with the Altar being on the 5 block up in the center).
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc3=The Altar holds up to 10,000mB of Life Essence (&61LP=1mB Life Essence&r). To fill it, use the &bSacrifical Dagger&r nearby, dealing 1 heart of damage, giving the Altar 200LP.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc4=To use LP, right-click an item into the Altar (you can also pipe items in). If this is a valid recipe, and the Altar is the correct tier, it will start draining LP from the Altar until it is done, transforming the item.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc5=If it runs out of LP before the recipe finishes, it will reset, &cwasting the LP&r.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar.desc6=See the Altar's uses in JEI to see what recipes it has.

ftbuniversity.altarguide.subtitle=Make the Inspectoris Scandelum
ftbuniversity.altarguide.desc1=The &bInspectoris Scandelum&r can show a &6building guide for every tier of the Blood Altar&r.
ftbuniversity.altarguide.desc2=Sneak right-click the book to cycle through tiers, then sneak right-click it on the Altar to show where blocks must go.
ftbuniversity.altarguide.desc3=Blank Runes can be any Rune type, and Stone Bricks can be any solid block. Additionally, the gaps between rings of Runes can be filled with any block you want, or left empty.

ftbuniversity.altarfluids.title=Altar Fluid Transfer
ftbuniversity.altarfluids.subtitle=Learn about the Altar's fluid IO
ftbuniversity.altarfluids.desc1=The Blood Altar, normally, &6can only transfer Life Essence at 20mB/t&r using pipes.
ftbuniversity.altarfluids.desc2=This can &nonly be increased at higher tiers&r, using Displacement and Acceleration Runes.

ftbuniversity.orb1.title=Tier 1 Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb1.subtitle=Make a Weak Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb1.desc1=The &bWeak Blood Orb&r is the first tier of Blood Orb.
ftbuniversity.orb1.desc2=Blood Orbs allow you to store LP in your &6personal network&r. This is basically an &6abstract LP battery that powers certain things&r. Your network isn't stored in your Blood Orb, it simply is.
ftbuniversity.orb1.desc3=Using a higher tier Blood Orb increases the max LP that can be stored in your network. The Weak Blood Orb can store &6up to 5,000LP&r.
ftbuniversity.orb1.desc4=Right-clicking the Blood Orb deals &61 heart of damage&r and &6adds 200LP to your network&r. You can also &6insert it into a Blood Altar&r (after it's been bound to you), and it will absorb its LP into your network as well.
ftbuniversity.orb1.desc5=Recipes that say they use the Blood Orb do not destroy it. Certain recipes may require a specific tier or higher to work.

ftbuniversity.lavcryst.subtitle=Make a Lava Crystal
ftbuniversity.lavcryst.desc1=The &bLava Crystal&r uses LP from your network to allow it to be used as &6furnace fuel&r.
ftbuniversity.lavcryst.desc2=First, bind it to yourself by right-clicking it, then put it into the fuel slot of a Furnace.
ftbuniversity.lavcryst.desc3=Putting it into a Furnace &6costs 750LP&r, but &reach item smelted only &6costs 50LP&r.

ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.title=Blood Pack
ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.subtitle=Make an LP-generating chestplate
ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.desc1=The &bBlood-Letter's Pack&r will slowly damage you to half health, generating and storing LP in itself.
ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.desc2=The &bCoat of Arms&r generates LP and stores it in itself when you are in combat.
ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.desc3=Both can be emptied into an Altar by &6sneak right-clicking the Altar with them&r.
ftbuniversity.bloodpacks.task=LP-generating chestplates

ftbuniversity.sigils1.title=Tier 1 Sigils
ftbuniversity.sigils1.subtitle=Make a tier 1 Sigil
ftbuniversity.sigils1.desc1=&bSigils&r are magic items that &6use LP to do specific things&r.
ftbuniversity.sigils1.desc2=The &bDivision Sigil&r will &6tell you how much LP you have&r in your network. Holding it in your hand then loking at a Blood Altar will &6display its information&r in the top left corner of the screen.
ftbuniversity.sigils1.desc3=The &bWater Sigil&r will &6create a Water source block&r when used, costing 100 LP.
ftbuniversity.sigils1.desc4=The &bLava Sigil&r will &6create a Lava source block&r when used, costing 1000 LP.

ftbuniversity.arcaneash.title=Alchemic Arrays
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.subtitle=Get Arcane Ashes
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.desc1=&bArcane Ashes&r are an integral component of &6alchemic arrays&r.
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.desc2=Place the Ashes on the ground, then place a &6reagant&r, and then place a &6catalyst&r. See the Ashes' use in JEI for recipes.
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.desc3=For example, to make a &6Divination Sigil&r, use Redstone as the reagant, and a Blank Slate as the catalyst.
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.desc4=Not all alchemic arrays create items; the Sanguine Scientem's chapter "&nThe Alchemist&r" has a list of all &6functional arrays&r.
ftbuniversity.arcaneash.desc5=These arrays can do stuff like move entities, enslave Skeletons, and grant buffs to nearby players.

ftbuniversity.alchemytable.title=Big Model
ftbuniversity.alchemytable.subtitle=Make an Alchemy Table
ftbuniversity.alchemytable.desc1=The &bAlchemy Table&r allows you to craft things using LP from your Blood Orb.
ftbuniversity.alchemytable.desc2=A lot of items that are necessary for progression can only be crafted here.

ftbuniversity.incense1.title=Blood Booster
ftbuniversity.incense1.subtitle=Make an Incense Altar
ftbuniversity.incense1.desc1=The &bIncense Altar&r is the focal point of a multiblock that allows you to &6boost the power of your Daggers&r for a time.
ftbuniversity.incense1.desc2=Place it down on top of a 3x3 platform of any material.
ftbuniversity.incense1.desc3=While near the Incense Altar, any Daggers in your inventory will become &6incensed&r. Using an incensed Dagger will &6instantly remove 90%% of your health, giving an additional 20%% LP per heart&r.
ftbuniversity.incense1.desc4=This has a cooldown; doing this gives the &6Soul Fray&r effect, which drastically lowers the amount of LP you give for its duration.

ftbuniversity.incense2.title=Incense Tier 2
ftbuniversity.incense2.subtitle=Get Wooden Paths
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc1=The boost from an Incense Altar depends on its &6tranquility&r. The higher the tranquility, the higher the boost.
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc2=Place a 3x3 of &bWooden Paths&r on each side of the Incense Altar's platform, creating a + shape. These platforms must be on the same y-level, but can be up or down 1 block from the center.
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc3=In the 4 3x3s in the corners, you can place certain blocks to &6increase the tranquility&r. These can also be one block above or below the Paths.
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc4=These blocks come in specific categories. Using more of a single category has &6diminishing returns&r: If you have 2 crops, it's worth less than 1 crop and 1 tree.
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc5=These blocks, and their categories, can be found in the quest directly to the left.
ftbuniversity.incense2.desc6=Completely maximizing the tranquility at this tier can give you up to a &6bonus of 60%%&r.
ftbuniversity.incense2.task=Wooden Paths

ftbuniversity.tranquility.title=Peace and Tranquility
ftbuniversity.tranquility.subtitle=Tranquility block categories
ftbuniversity.tranquility.desc=Each task is a category, and their items are the blocks within them.
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task1=Crops
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task2=Earthen
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task3=Fire
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task4=Lava
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task5=Tree
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task6=Plants
ftbuniversity.tranquility.task7=Water

ftbuniversity.incense3.title=Incense Tier 3
ftbuniversity.incense3.subtitle=Get Stone Paths
ftbuniversity.incense3.desc1=Place a 3x2 of &bStone Paths&r at the end of the Wooden Paths. Again, these platforms must be on the same y-level as each other, but can be up or down 1 from the Wooden Paths.
ftbuniversity.incense3.desc2=This gives you an &6additional 64 blocks&r to increase tranquility.
ftbuniversity.incense3.desc3=Lower-tier Paths can be replaced with higher-tier ones, if you prefer.
ftbuniversity.incense3.desc4=The maximum bonus at this tier is &6120%%&r.
ftbuniversity.incense3.task=Stone Paths

ftbuniversity.incense4.title=Incense Tier 4
ftbuniversity.incense4.subtitle=Get Worn Stone Paths
ftbuniversity.incense4.desc1=Place a 3x2 of &bWorn Stone Paths&r at the end of the Stone Paths. The usual placement rules apply.
ftbuniversity.incense4.desc2=This gives you an &6additional 96 blocks&r to increase tranquility.
ftbuniversity.incense4.desc3=The maximum bonus at this tier is &6200%%&r.
ftbuniversity.incense4.task=Worn Stone Paths

ftbuniversity.incense5.title=Incense Tier 5
ftbuniversity.incense5.subtitle=Get Obsidian Paths
ftbuniversity.incense5.desc1=Place a 3x2 of &bObsidian Paths&r at the end of the Worn Stone Paths. This is the final tier.
ftbuniversity.incense5.desc2=This gives you an &6additional 128 blocks&r to increase tranquility.
ftbuniversity.incense5.desc3=The maximum bonus at this tier is &6300%%&r.
ftbuniversity.incense5.task=Obsidian Paths

ftbuniversity.bloodaltar2.title=Blood Altar Tier 2
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar2.subtitle=Upgrade your Altar to tier 2
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar2.desc1=Place a ring of 8 &bBlank Runes&r 1 block beneath the Blood Altar to &6increase it to tier 2&r.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar2.desc2=This gives you access to several new recipes, but it otherwise functions the same.

ftbuniversity.runes.title=Altar Upgrades
ftbuniversity.runes.subtitle=Make Runes
ftbuniversity.runes.desc1=&bRunes&r can &6replace the Blank Runes&r in the Blood Altar structure to upgrade it in some way.
ftbuniversity.runes.desc2=Each task has the Runes available in each tier. Each Rune has a &6JEI info tabs&r that show what they do.
ftbuniversity.runes.task1=Tier 2
ftbuniversity.runes.task2=Tier 3
ftbuniversity.runes.task3=Tier 4

ftbuniversity.orb2.title=Tier 2 Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb2.subtitle=Make an Apprentice Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb2.desc1=The &bApprentice Blood Orb&r increases your network's capacity to &625000LP&r.
ftbuniversity.orb2.desc2=It also can be used in more recipes, but otherwise functions the same.

ftbuniversity.dagsac.title=Selfish
ftbuniversity.dagsac.subtitle=Make a Dagger of Sacrifice
ftbuniversity.dagsac.desc1=The &bDagger of Sacrifice&r, when within 3 blocks of a Blood Altar, will &6instantly kill mobs, filling the Altar with LP&r.
ftbuniversity.dagsac.desc2=The amount varies based on the mob type. &6Animals&r give 250LP, &6monsters&r give 500LP, and &6villagers&r give 2000LP.

ftbuniversity.sigils2.title=Tier 2 Sigils
ftbuniversity.sigils2.subtitle=Make a tier 2 Sigil
ftbuniversity.sigils2.desc=These &bSigils&r are generally more powerful than tier 1. They each have &6JEI info tabs&r saying what they do.

ftbuniversity.bmpots.subtitle=Make a Potion Flask
ftbuniversity.bmpots.desc1=The &bPotion Flask&r can be filled with several potions, which &6can be drunk 8 times&r.
ftbuniversity.bmpots.desc2=A &bSimple Lengthening&r/&bPower Catalyst&r can be added to either increase the duration or power of the potion.
ftbuniversity.bmpots.task=Simple Catalysts

ftbuniversity.bloodaltar3.title=Blood Altar Tier 3
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar3.subtitle=Upgrade your Altar to tier 3
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar3.desc=Use the &6Inspectoris Scandelum&r for how to upgrade your Altar. At this stage, the structure would be &67x4x7&r, with the Altar on the 3rd layer.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar3.task1=Runes
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar3.task2=Lights

ftbuniversity.orb3.title=Tier 3 Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb3.subtitle=Make a Magician Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb3.desc=The &bMagician Blood Orb&r increases your network's capacity to &6150,000LP&r.

ftbuniversity.sigils3.title=Tier 3 Sigils
ftbuniversity.sigils3.subtitle=Make a tier 3 Sigil
ftbuniversity.sigils3.desc=These &bSigils&r are even more powerful. They also have &6JEI info tabs&r saying how they work.

ftbuniversity.peritia.subtitle=Make the Tome of Peritia
ftbuniversity.peritia.desc1=The &bTome of Peritia&r &6stores experience&r.
ftbuniversity.peritia.desc2=Sneak right-click to store your xp, and right-click to extract.

ftbuniversity.livarmor.title=Senketsu
ftbuniversity.livarmor.subtitle=Make Living Armor
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc1=&bLiving Armor&r will &6upgrade itself while worn&r based on the things you do. You have to wear the full set for it to upgrade.
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc2=For instance, if you sprint a lot, you'll get get a speed buff. If you shoot a lot of arrows, you'll occasionally shoot a second arrow.
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc3=These upgrades are automatic, and use up &6upgrade points&r, which you have a limited amount of. That means you may get some &cunwanted upgrades&r.
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc4=Removing upgrades requires a tier 4 Blood Altar, and will be explained later.
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc5=We've gone through and added JEI info tabs for each of the &6Living Armor Upgrade Tomes&r, describing what they do and how they're leveled.
ftbuniversity.livarmor.desc6=Some upgrades can only be gained by crafting the Upgrade Tomes.

ftbuniversity.boundtools.title=Bound Tools
ftbuniversity.boundtools.subtitle=Make a Bound tool
ftbuniversity.boundtools.desc1=&bBound tools&r have &6infinite durability&r, instead &6using your LP network&r.
ftbuniversity.boundtools.desc2=Bound tools must be activated by sneak right-clicking them, &6draining 20LP every 4 seconds it is active&r.
ftbuniversity.boundtools.desc3=While sneaking, hold right-click on an activated Bound tool, then release to &6clear an 11x11x11 cube&r above you, at the cost of &610,000LP&r. If you can't afford this, &cyou will die&r.
ftbuniversity.boundtools.desc4=The &bBound Sword&r works differently; it has no right-click function, and drains LP from your network when it damages a mob. Mobs killed have a chance of dropping &6Weak Blood Shards&r.

ftbuniversity.rituals1.title=Rituals
ftbuniversity.rituals1.subtitle=Make a ritual setup
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc1=&6Rituals&r are essentially multiblock structures that use your LP network to do things, like spawn Lava source blocks, feed nearby players, or pull ores from the ground.
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc2=The &6focal point&r of every ritual structure is the &bMaster Ritual Stone&r. Incidentally, it can be &6disabled with a redstone signal&r.
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc3=Additionally, you need several normal &bRitual Stones&r. These will be placed around the Master Ritual Stone during the creation of the structure.
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc4=To actually make the structures, you need a &bRitual Diviner&r. Sneak right-click it to &6cycle through rituals&r, then &6right-click on the Master Ritual Stone&r to place down Ritual Stones according to that ritual.
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc5=When the structure is completed, right-click a &bWeak Activation Crystal&r on the Master Ritual Stone to start it. This costs LP, based on the ritual.
ftbuniversity.rituals1.desc6=The chapter "&6The Ritual Master&r" in the Sanguine Scientem has a list of all rituals and their functions.

ftbuniversity.demcruc.title=Atmospheric &mVis&r Will
ftbuniversity.demcruc.subtitle=Make a Demon Crucible
ftbuniversity.demcruc.desc1=Each chunk has an &6aura&r, which holds up to 100 Will. This will does not generate naturally, and has to be filled by you.
ftbuniversity.demcruc.desc2=That's where the &bDemon Crucible&r comes in. Simply give it Will, either the item itself or through a Tartaric Gem&r, and it will instantly diffuse into the chunk's aura.
ftbuniversity.demcruc.desc3=Will &cdoes not move to adjacent chunks&r. If you want multiple chunks to have Will, you have to use multiple Crucibles.
ftbuniversity.demcruc.desc4=Will from the Aura will refill Tartaric Gems that are in Hellfire Forges in their chunk. 

ftbuniversity.demcryst.subtitle=Make a Demon Crystallizer
ftbuniversity.demcryst.desc1=The &bDemon Crystallizer&r will slowly draw Will out of the aura, forming it into a &6Demon Will Crystal Cluster&r. Fully formed, it will have 7 spikes.
ftbuniversity.demcryst.desc2=You can mine the Cluster to pick it up. However, if you have &61000 normal Will&r in your inventory, right-clicking the Cluster will &6remove all but the main spike&r.
ftbuniversity.demcryst.desc3=The main spike takes about 100 Will to form, but each smaller Spike only uses about 50.

ftbuniversity.auragauge.title=Yay, More GUI Elements
ftbuniversity.auragauge.subtitle=Make a Demon Will Aura Gauge
ftbuniversity.auragauge.desc1=The &bDemon Will Aura Gauge&r, when anywhere in your inventory, will display the aura's Will in the top left of the screen.
ftbuniversity.auragauge.desc2=It has 5 slots, one for each type of Will. Sneaking will show the exact amounts of each.

ftbuniversity.bmrouting.title=Item Routing
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.subtitle=Make a Router setup
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc1=&eBlood Magic&r adds a way to move items through a network of Routing Nodes.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc2=Firstly, every network requires a &bMaster Routing Node&r. You can only have one per network. It doesn't really do anything, it just has to be there.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc3=Next to the inventory you wish to pull from, place an &bInput Routing Node&r. Next to the inventory you wish to insert into, place an &bOutput Routing Node&r. Connect them to each other and to the Master Node with a &bNode Router&r.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc4=Each side has its own filter. If you want to set a filter for what gets pulled from the block above the node, click U (for "up") on the right.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc5=Place a &bFilter&r of any kind in the leftmost slot, once you've chosen the side. Then, insert the item you want to add to the whitelist.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.desc6=Click the slot the item is in to select it. In the # text box, you can set an amount (how much to keep in, if Input, or how much to push out, if Output). You can also set a priority, 0-9.
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.task1=Nodes
ftbuniversity.bmrouting.task2=Filters

ftbuniversity.bloodaltar4.title=Tier 4 Blood Altar
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar4.subtitle=Upgrade your Altar to tier 4
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar4.desc=Use the &6Inspectoris Scandelum&r for how to upgrade your Altar. At this stage, the structure would be &611x6x11&r, with the Altar on the 4th layer.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar4.task=Runes

ftbuniversity.orb4.title=Tier 4 Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb4.subtitle=Make a Master Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb4.desc=The &bMaster Blood Orb&r increases your network's capacity to &61,000,000LP&r.

ftbuniversity.teleposer.subtitle=Make a Teleposer
ftbuniversity.teleposer.desc1=A &bTeleposer&r, when given a redstone signal, will swap whatever is above it with whatever is above the linked Teleposer.
ftbuniversity.teleposer.desc2=To link Teleposers, first right-click the main Teleposer with a &bTeleposition Focus&r, then right-click on the destination Teleposer. Return to the main one, click it with an empty hand, then insert the Focus. The contents will swap when the main Teleposer (and &nonly&r the main one) gets a redstone signal.
ftbuniversity.teleposer.desc3=The are 4 tiers of Focus. The first teleports a single block, the second teleports a 3x3x3, then 5x5x5, then 7x7x7.
ftbuniversity.teleposer.task=Teleposition Foci

ftbuniversity.rituals2.subtitle=Make a Ritual Diviner [Dusk]
ftbuniversity.rituals2.desc1=The &bRitual Diviner [Dusk]&r has access to &6greater rituals&r.
ftbuniversity.rituals2.desc2=Additionally, its tooltip will display information about the selected ritual.
ftbuniversity.rituals2.desc3=Left-clicking a Master Ritual Stone will change the direction it will act on.
ftbuniversity.rituals2.desc4=One of the most important greater rituals is the &6Well of Suffering&r, which damages mobs in its zone, filling a nearby Blood Altar.

ftbuniversity.dismantler.title=Cleanup
ftbuniversity.dismantler.subtitle=Make a Ritual Dismantler
ftbuniversity.dismantler.desc=The &bRitual Dismantler&r, when used on a Master Ritual Stone, will instantly break and pick up all the Ritual Stone components. Clicking again will pick up the Master Stone.

ftbuniversity.tinkerer.subtitle=Make a Ritual Tinkerer
ftbuniversity.tinkerer.desc1=The &bRitual Tinkerer&r allows you to change certain settings for certain rituals.
ftbuniversity.tinkerer.desc2=The Ritual Tinkerer has several modes:
ftbuniversity.tinkerer.desc3=&6Information&r: right-click an active Master Ritual Stone to learn what it does
ftbuniversity.tinkerer.desc4=&6Set Will Consumed&r: right-click an active Master Ritual Stone while you have a Will Crystal of a specific type in your hotbar, and the ritual will use that Will type from the aura
ftbuniversity.tinkerer.desc5=&6Define Area&r: sneak rig-click the Master Stone, then choose either a single block or 2 corners of an area to target, depending on the ritual

ftbuniversity.clusters.subtitle=Make a Will Crystal Cluster
ftbuniversity.clusters.desc=&bWill Crystal Clusters&r can be placed anywhere, and will grow using Will from the aura, exactly like as if they were on a Demon Crystallizer.
ftbuniversity.clusters.task=Will Crystal Clusters

ftbuniversity.willtypes.title=Will Types
ftbuniversity.willtypes.subtitle=Get a nonstandard type of Will
ftbuniversity.willtypes.desc1=Make and activate the ritual &6Resonant of the Faceted Crystal&r. On top of the Master Ritual Stone, place a &6Demon Crystallizer&r and allow it to grow a Demon Will Crystal Cluster with &6at least 5 spikes&r.
ftbuniversity.willtypes.desc2=Once this happens, the ritual will take one of the spikes from the Crystal and place it on one of the 4 colored Ritual Stones, which will be of a &bnew kind of Will&r.
ftbuniversity.willtypes.desc3=You can use this with the ritual &6Gathering of Forsaken Souls&r, which damages mobs in its area to grow nearby Crystal Clusters.
ftbuniversity.willtypes.task=Nonstandard Will Clusters

ftbuniversity.pylon.subtitle=Make a Demon Pylon
ftbuniversity.pylon.desc=The &bDemon Pylon&r will &6pull Will from the 4 surrounding chunks&r, attempting to equalize them.

ftbuniversity.gemtypes.title=Tartaric Types
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.subtitle=Get a nonstandard type of Tartaric Gem
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc1=Grand Tartaric Gems can be crafted with Will Crystals to &bchange the type of Will they use&r. They can only be &6recharged in the Hellfire Forge&r, and only if their Will type is in the chunk's Aura.
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc2=&6Tools and weapons&r using these nonstandard Wills have special effects added to them:
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc3=â€¢ &bCorrosive&r inflicts Wither and Poison on mobs
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc4=â€¢ &bDestructive&r increases attack damage, but lowers speed
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc5=â€¢ &bVengeful&r lowers attack speed but increases damage and movement speed (attack damage + speed changes are lower than Destructive's)
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc6=â€¢ &bSteadfast&r increases attack damage, and gives Absorption after kills
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc7=For the &6Sentient Bow&r:
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc8=â€¢ &bCorrosive&r applies poison
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc9=â€¢ &bDestructive&r causes explosions
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc10=â€¢ &bVengeful&r applies slowness, and moves faster
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc11=â€¢ &bSteadfast&r applies levitation
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc12=For &6Sentient armor&r:
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc13=â€¢ &bCorrosive&r instantly removes wither and poison
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc14=â€¢ &bDestructive&r boosts attack damage and lowers attack speed
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc15=â€¢ &bVengeful&r increases speed
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.desc16=â€¢ &bSteadfast&r increases protection and knockback resistance
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.task1=Corrosive
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.task2=Destructive
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.task3=Vengeful
ftbuniversity.gemtypes.task4=Steadfast

ftbuniversity.sigils4.title=Tier 4 Sigils
ftbuniversity.sigils4.subtitle=Make a tier 4 Sigil
ftbuniversity.sigils4.desc=Following the pattern, &btier 4 Sigils&r are even more powerful than tier 3. This is also the final tier.

ftbuniversity.bloodaltar5.title=Tier 5 Blood Altar
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar5.subtitle=Upgrade your Altar to tier 5
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar5.desc=Use the &6Inspectoris Scandelum&r for how to upgrade your Altar. This is the highest tier, and is 17x7x17, with the Altar on the 5th layer.
ftbuniversity.bloodaltar5.task=Runes

ftbuniversity.orb5.title=Tier 5 Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb5.subtitle=Make an Archmage Blood Orb
ftbuniversity.orb5.desc=The &bArchmage Blood Orb&r increases your network's capacity to &610,000,000LP&r.

ftbuniversity.awacryst.subtitle=Make an Awakened Activation Crystal
ftbuniversity.awacryst.desc=Certain rituals can only be activated with the &bAwakened Activation Crystal&r.

ftbuniversity.angelus.subtitle=Make the Draft of Angelus
ftbuniversity.angelus.desc=Drinking the &bDraft of Angelus&r will increase your Living Blood's maximum upgrade points from 100 to 200.

ftbuniversity.angelus.title=Ritual of Living Evolution
ftbuniversity.angelus.subtitle=Learn about the Ritual of Living Evolution
ftbuniversity.angelus.desc=The &bRitual of Living Evolution&r costs 50,000LP to increase your Living armor's maximum upgrade points to 300.

ftbuniversity.uptomes.title=Living Armor Upgrade Tomes
ftbuniversity.uptomes.subtitle=Get a Living Armor Upgrade Tome
ftbuniversity.uptomes.desc1=The ritual &6Sound of the Cleansing Soul&r uses 50,000LP to &6clear all upgrades from your Living armor&r, dropping them as &bLiving Armor Upgrade Tomes&r.
ftbuniversity.uptomes.desc2=Right-clicking one of these will apply it to your Living armor. You can also combine them like Enchanted Books in an Anvil to increase their level.

ftbuniversity.bracelet.subtitle=Make a Training Bracelet
ftbuniversity.bracelet.desc=The &bTraining Bracelet&r can be crafted with a Trait Tome. With this combined Bracelet in your inventory, worn Living armor can &6only aquire and level the traits in the Bracelet&r.

ftbuniversity.downtomes.title=Living Armor Downgrade Tomes
ftbuniversity.downtomes.subtitle=Make a Living Armor Downgrade Tome
ftbuniversity.downtomes.desc1=The ritual &6Penance of the Leadened Soul&r can create &bLiving Armor Downgrade Tomes&r.
ftbuniversity.downtomes.desc2=These Tomes, when applied, give you a certain &6debuff&r while also &6giving you more upgrade points&r.
ftbuniversity.downtomes.desc3=We've added JEI info tabs to say what they do.

###Thaumcraft 6
ftbuniversity.thaumchap.title=Thaumcraft 6

ftbuniversity.thaumstart.title=Glow in the Dark Crystal
ftbuniversity.thaumstart.subtitle=Mine Vis Crystals
ftbuniversity.thaumstart.desc1=To start Thaumcraft, simply mine &bVis Crystal&r formations in the world.
ftbuniversity.thaumstart.desc2=After this, you should get a message in chat telling you to &6sleep&r. Upon waking up, you will have a book with the next step.
ftbuniversity.thaumstart.desc3=You &ccannot skip steps&r in Thaumcraft, recipes and the like are completely inaccessible until unlocked.
ftbuniversity.thaumstart.task=Any primal Vis Crystal

ftbuniversity.thaumaaspects.title=What's the Magic Word
ftbuniversity.thaumaaspects.subtitle=Learn about Vis, Essentia, and Aspects
ftbuniversity.thaumaaspects.desc1=&bVis&r (pronounced "vee") is the &6basic magic energy&r that exists in the atmosphere. &6Some chunks have more, some have less.&r When a chunk's Vis is used, adjacent chunks will replenish it with theirs. Chunks with &6more Vis Crystals&r tend to have higher Vis.
ftbuniversity.thaumaaspects.desc2=&bEssentia&r is Vis that is "flavored" to certain &6concepts&r, called &bAspects&r. Most blocks and items have a certain amount of Essentia for certain Aspects, like &6Flint and Steel would have Ignis, which is Fire&r. Hold shift while hovering over an item to see its Aspects.
ftbuniversity.thaumaaspects.desc3=The &bprimal Aspects&r make up all other Aspects, and are the only Vis Crystal formations that &6generate naturally&r in the world.

ftbuniversity.thaumaddon.title=Thaumic Addons
ftbuniversity.thaumaddon.subtitle=Learn about Thaumcraft addons
ftbuniversity.thaumaddon.desc1=University has several &bThaumcraft addons&r. They greatly expand Thaumcraft in certain ways, either adding support for other mods (like AE2) or adding new things entirely.
ftbuniversity.thaumaddon.desc2=Though they do not have quests, each have their own page in the Thaumonomicon, which are always on the right side of the GUI.

ftbuniversity.flux.title=Magic Pollution
ftbuniversity.flux.subtitle=Learn about Flux
ftbuniversity.flux.desc1=&bFlux&r is essentially &6magic waste&r. It can build up when essentia is allowed to enter the atmosphere unfilitered.
ftbuniversity.flux.desc2=Flux is definitely not something you want, at least at your base. When Flux builds up too much, it can coalesce into a &6Flux Rift&r. 
ftbuniversity.flux.desc3=Flux Rifts will generate on the highest block in the chunk, and then grows as it consumes more Flux, destroying any block it touches.
ftbuniversity.flux.desc4=These Rifts will eventually go away on their own, leaving a &6Taint Seed&r (which is a great source of Vitium, so you may want to purposefully cause this somewhere far from your base).
ftbuniversity.flux.desc5=One of the most common sources of Flux is allowing a Crucible to dissipate its contents.

ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.subtitle=Make a Flux Condenser
ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.desc1=If you'd rather not wait for Flux to dissipate on its own, you can use the &bFlux Condenser&r.
ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.desc2=On top of the Flux Condenser, place &bFlux Condenser Latices&r. The optimal setup would be a 5x5 layer centered on top of the Condenser.
ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.desc3=Feed any Essentia (&cexcept Vitium&r) to the sides of the Flux Condenser through Essentia Tubes, and it will slowly &6drain Flux from the chunk&r, and then store it in the Latices.
ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.desc4=Fluxed Latices stop working, and have to be &6cleaned with an Essentia Filter&r.
ftbuniversity.fluxcondenser.desc5=As Taint is removed, it can be output through the bottom and stored as Vitium.

ftbuniversity.causecoll.subtitle=Make a Causality Collapser
ftbuniversity.causecoll.desc1=The &bCausality Collapser&r can be &6thrown at Flux Rifts&r to &6instantly collapse them&r, releasing "primal energy."
ftbuniversity.causecoll.desc2=After collapsing, the Rift may drop &6Void Seeds&r and a damaged &6Primordial Pearl&r.

ftbuniversity.thaumonom.title=They Took Our Job!
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.subtitle=Make a Thaumonomicon
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc1=Reading the book, it will tell you to &6craft 3 different Vis Crystals with some Redstone, a Bowl, and Flint&r. This will create &bSalis Mundus&r.
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc2=Use the Salis Mundus on a Bookshelf to make a &bThaumonomicon&r.
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc3=The Thaumonomicon is Thaumcraft's &6guide book&r. As you &6progress&r, more pages and chapters will unlock.
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc4=Tiles that are flashing have tasks you have to complete inside them.
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc5=&nTechnically&r, the Thaumonomicon works as &6its own independent quest system&r. However, the quests here will teach &6without flavor-text&r, as well as giving &6pointers&r the book does not.
ftbuniversity.thaumonom.desc6=Seriously though, read the Thaumonomicon. It teaches everything really well.

ftbuniversity.arcanework.subtitle=Make an Arcane Workbench
ftbuniversity.arcanework.desc1=The &bArcane Workbench&r has slots for every primal Vis Crystal, which are required for certain recipes.
ftbuniversity.arcanework.desc2=Recipes also use a certain amount of &6Vis from the chunk&r.
ftbuniversity.arcanework.desc3=To make the Arcane Workbench, &6use Salis Mundus on a Crafting Table&r.

ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.title=Study Nook
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.subtitle=Make and learn to use a Research Table
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc1=When trying to unlock knowledge in the Thaumonomicon, you may need to craft certain items, know certain aspects, or have Observations and Theories.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc2=You get Observations with the &6Thaumometer&r, but you make Theories in the &bResearch Table&r.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc3=Place a &6Wooden Table&r and use &bScribing Tools&r on it to convert it to a Research Table. To begin, insert some &6Paper&r and click &6Create Theory&r.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc4=The lightbulbs at the top represent your &6inspiration&r. Your max inspiration increases as you progress through the mod.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc5=Click the paper on the left to show some research cards. Each option uses some inspiration, and &6gives progress towards a theory in a specific field&r, like Alchemy or Artifice.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc6=Some research cards require you &6have specific items in your inventory&r, like Vis Crystals. Others may also destroy the item after using it, those have a &e!&r on them.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc7=Choosing a research card will use up some inspiration, do a bit of durability damage to the Scribing Tools, use a Paper, add some progress in theorycrafting, and then allow you to redraw.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc8=Once you are out of inspiration, you can click &6Complete Theory&r to actually gain the progress made. At any point, you can also &6Scrap Theory&r to give up, starting over.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc9=In the Thaumonomicon, the &6Types of Knowledge&r page in &6Fundamentals&r to see your progress on Theories and Observations.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.desc10=The Scribing Tool can be &6repaired with Inc Sacs&r.
ftbuniversity.thaumresearch.task=Scribing Tools

ftbuniversity.researchaids.title=Research Aids
ftbuniversity.researchaids.subtitle=Learn about research aids
ftbuniversity.researchaids.desc1=&bResearch aids&r are blocks you can put in the area around your Research Table to have &6more control&r over what research cards appear.
ftbuniversity.researchaids.desc2=You can only choose &6one research aid at a time&r, which also uses up inspiration.
ftbuniversity.researchaids.desc3=&6Curiosities&r are rare items that can be right-clicked to add Theories and Observations. They also unlock special research cards if in your inventory, usually in a specific category.
ftbuniversity.researchaids.task=Research Aids, and their cards
