ftbuniversity.flight.subtitle=Make something to let you fly
ftbuniversity.flight.desc=All of these items will give you &bsome sort of flight&r. Not all of them are creative-stlyle, though.
ftbuniversity.flight.task=Flight items

ftbuniversity.quarries.title=Quarries
ftbuniversity.quarries.subtitle=Make any Quarry
ftbuniversity.quarries.desc=All of these machines use energy to &bmine or generate ores&r.

###Misc2
ftbuniversity.miscmisc.title=Misc-er

ftbuniversity.handheldcrafting.title=All the Power of a Crafting Table in the Palm of Your Hand
ftbuniversity.handheldcrafting.subtitle=Make a Handheld Crafting Table
ftbuniversity.handheldcrafting.desc=The &bHandheld Crafting Table&r works like a Crafting Table, but in your hand! Wow!

ftbuniversity.laggoggles.title=LagGoggles
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.subtitle=Learn how to use LagGoggles
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc1=&eLagGoggles&r is a mod that allows you to &6identify sources of lag in your world&r. It works best when used with cheats enabled (or as a server OP), but still works without.
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc2=To begin, hit &6Insert&r. Scroll over the top button to change the amount of time you will be analyzing the world, then click it to begin.
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc3=Choose whether you are measuring &6the world's ticks per second&r, or &6your client's frames per second&r. After that, wait until the timer runs out.
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc4=Blocks and entities that cause lag will be &6highlighted&r, with red being worse. If you look to the sky, &6chunks&r themselves will also be color-coded for how much lag they produce.
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc5=Back in the LagGoggles GUI, you can also click &6Analyze Results&r. This will open a list of the laggiest individual entities, entity types, and event subscribers (basically, a mod feature).
ftbuniversity.laggoggles.desc6=Once you're done, click &6Hide latest scan results&r in the GUI.

ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.title=Aurora Borealis?
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.subtitle=Learn how to disable potentially annoying mods
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.desc1=The mod &eSound Physics&r tries to make sounds more realistic, and is why caves echo etc.
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.desc2=If you don't like it, you can go to &6Mod Options...&r, search "Sound Physics", then &cDisable&r it (or configure it to your liking).
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.desc3=The mod &eDynamic Surroundings&r adds audio and visual effects to make the world more realistic. This is why walking, crafting, and equipping items makes sounds. It's also where speech bubbles, auroras, and fancier rain come from.
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.desc4=Like Sound Physics, you can search up "Dynamic Duroundings" in Mod Options and disable/configure it how you like.
ftbuniversity.annoyingsounds.desc5=The mod &eFancy Block Particles&r changes the particles from breaking blocks etc to be more fancy. This can be disabled if you don't like it.

ftbuniversity.mmmmmmmmmmmm.title=Dummies Are Not For Fighting!
ftbuniversity.mmmmmmmmmmmm.subtitle=Make a Test Dummy
ftbuniversity.mmmmmmmmmmmm.desc1=The &bTest Dummy&r will &6display the amount of damage dealt to it&r, so you can accurately see how powerful your weapons are.
ftbuniversity.mmmmmmmmmmmm.desc2=You can click &6armor&r on it to equip it. Sneak punching with an empty hand will remove the armor.
ftbuniversity.mmmmmmmmmmmm.desc3=Sneak right-click with an empty hand to &6disassemble&r it.

ftbuniversity.hooked.title=Hooked On a Feeling
ftbuniversity.hooked.subtitle=Make a Hook
ftbuniversity.hooked.desc1=&bHooks&r, from the mod &eHooked&r, are &6worn as Baubles&r and allow you to shoot a grappling hook in the direction you're looking, dragging you to where it hits.
ftbuniversity.hooked.desc2=The &bWooden Hook&r has a rather pathetic range, but is good for simple traversal.
ftbuniversity.hooked.desc3=Every tier above allows you to fire &6multiple hooks&r, generally moving you to their midpoint. You can this to climb walls like some kind of &6horrifying octupus monster&r, which is very fun.
ftbuniversity.hooked.desc4=The &6tooltip&r will explain their controls, as well as what makes each Hook special.
ftbuniversity.hooked.task=Hooks

ftbuniversity.cognitohazard.title=Cognitohazard
ftbuniversity.cognitohazard.subtitle=Complete this quest to die instantly
ftbuniversity.cognitohazard.desc=Obviously, this is optional.

ftbuniversity.chisel.title=Art Major
ftbuniversity.chisel.subtitle=Make a Chisel
ftbuniversity.chisel.desc1=A &bChisel&r (from the mod &eChisel&r) can be used to convert blocks into better-looking versions.
ftbuniversity.chisel.desc2=In JEI, &6search for &n@Chisel&r to find all Chisel blocks. Chiseled versions of vanilla blocks have been hidden to prevent JEI spam, but original blocks are still visible.
ftbuniversity.chisel.task=Chisels

ftbuniversity.nbits.title=Micromanage
ftbuniversity.nbits.subtitle=Make a Chisel (from Chisels n Bits)
ftbuniversity.nbits.desc1=A &bChisel&r (from the mod &eChisels & Bits&r), when left-clicked on a block, will &6remove a bit of it, literally&r.
ftbuniversity.nbits.desc2=A &6Bit&r is 1/4096'th of a block. 16 Bits in every direction make up a block. You can place Bits back down into the world for decorative purposes. If a block is full of Bits of the same type, it will reform into a normal block.
ftbuniversity.nbits.desc3=&6Hold Left Alt&r while holding a Chisel or a Bit to change the breaking/placing method (bit by bit, snapped to a grid, etc).
ftbuniversity.nbits.desc4=Chisels & Bits uses the &eMCMultiPart&r API, which allows it to be in the same block as cables etc from certain other mods, like &eMekanism&r and &eLogistics Pipes&r.
ftbuniversity.nbits.task=CnB Chisels

ftbuniversity.bitbag.title=Bag of Bit Holding
ftbuniversity.bitbag.subtitle=Make a Chiseled Bit Bag
ftbuniversity.bitbag.desc1=One block is made out of 4096 Bits. That is 64 stacks of Bits per block. The &bChiseled Bit Bag&r will &6automatically pick up Bits&r and stores them, up to 512 a slot.
ftbuniversity.bitbag.desc2=&6It will also keep a stack of each Bit type in your inventory full.&r
ftbuniversity.bitbag.task=Any Chiseled Bit Bag

ftbuniversity.bittank.title=Fluid Bits
ftbuniversity.bittank.subtitle=Make a Chiseled Fluid Bit Tank
ftbuniversity.bittank.desc1=Right-click a full bucket on a &bChiseled Fluid Bit Tank&r to fill it, then right-click with an empty hand to remove a stack of Bits of that fluid.
ftbuniversity.bittank.desc2=Fluid Bits do not flow, and all fluid bits work exactly the same as Water.

ftbuniversity.vectorplates.title=Direction &oand &nMagnitude!&r
ftbuniversity.vectorplates.subtitle=Make a Vector Plate
ftbuniversity.vectorplates.desc1=&bVector Plates&r will &6move entities&r standing on them in the direction they are pointing. Higher tiers work faster. Sneaking will resist their effect.
ftbuniversity.vectorplates.desc2=&bAnchor Plates&r will lock entities in place, making it &6impossible for them to move&r. Endermen are still able to teleport away, however. Again, sneaking disables them.
ftbuniversity.vectorplates.desc3=Vector Plates do not prevent monsters from spawning on them, so they work amazingly in tandem with &6Cursed Earth&r.
ftbuniversity.vectorplates.task=Vector Plates

ftbuniversity.dutraps.subtitle=Make a Trap
ftbuniversity.dutraps.desc1=&bTraps&r give certain negative effects when stood on, usually implied by their name.
ftbuniversity.dutraps.desc2=Each has a JEI info tab that says what they do.
ftbuniversity.dutraps.task=Traps

ftbuniversity.dufilters.title=Automated Bouncer
ftbuniversity.dufilters.subtitle=Make a Mob Filter
ftbuniversity.dufilters.desc1=&bMob Filters&r only allow mobs of a specific type to pass through them.
ftbuniversity.dufilters.desc2=&bInverted Mob Filters&r are the opposite, only allowing certain types of mobs to touch them.
ftbuniversity.dufilters.task1=Mob Filters
ftbuniversity.dufilters.task2=Inverted Mob Filters

ftbuniversity.ducharms.title=Charmed
ftbuniversity.ducharms.subtitle=Make a Charm
ftbuniversity.ducharms.desc1=&bCharms&r give certain passive effects when worn as a Bauble.
ftbuniversity.ducharms.desc2=Each has a JEI info tab that explains their effect.
ftbuniversity.ducharms.task=Charms

ftbuniversity.shadyvillager.title=Totally Legitimate Businessvillager
ftbuniversity.shadyvillager.subtitle=Trade with a Shady Merchant
ftbuniversity.shadyvillager.desc=Despite the name, the &bShady Merchant&r is completely trustworthy, and I spend all of my money there. I suggest you do too.
ftbuniversity.shadyvillager.task=All trades

ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.title=Super Sound Muffler
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.subtitle=Make a Super Sound Muffler
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc1=The &bSuper Sound Muffler&r allows you to &6mute sounds&r in an area. Unlike Extra Utilities 2's, SSM allows you to pick and &6choose which sounds to mute&r.
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc2=In &6Whitelist&r mode, everything in the list is not muted. In &6Blacklist&r mode, only what's in the list is muted.
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc3=To add sounds to the list, click &6Add&r. Type in the name of the sound event, choose it out of the list, and click Add again.
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc4=Sound events are in code-terms, but should be fairly easy to guesstimate. Instead of searching &6moo&r, you would search &6cow&r and then see find &6minecraft:entity.cow.ambient&r.
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc5=The SSM also has a &bBauble Edition&r, which you can configure and wear to mute that sound everywhere you go!
ftbuniversity.supersoundmuffler.desc6=Unfortunately, it &ccannot mute IC2 sounds&r, because IC2 is a special mod that does what &oit&r wants. It has a volume slider in settings, though.

ftbuniversity.microblocks.title=Forge Multipart
ftbuniversity.microblocks.subtitle=Make a Saw
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc1=&eForge Multipart&r is a mod that is designed to allow multiple blocks to be in the same blockspace.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc2=It has mostly been superceded by &eMCMultiPart&r, but &eProjectRed&r uses FMP instead.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc3=Craft any block with a &bSaw&r to &6saw it in half&r. If placed above, it will cut vertically. If placed next to, it will cut horizontally. You can &6cut a block multiple times&r to get even smaller cuts.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc4=You can also craft 8 Slabs/Panels/Covers together to get a &6hollow&r version of each.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc5=You can put two cut blocks back together by crafting them, allowing you to get the full block back.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc6=When holding any cut block and aiming at a surface, you can see the &6orientation it will be placed in&r. Hover over different edges of the block to change the orientation. You can place cut blocks of different materials in the same blockspace.
ftbuniversity.microblocks.desc7=Additionally, FMP allows you to place multiple Torches, Levers, Buttons, and the like (as well as any combination) &6in the same blockspace&r!
ftbuniversity.microblocks.task1=Any FMP Saw
ftbuniversity.microblocks.task2=Oak Log Portions
ftbuniversity.microblocks.task3=Hollow Oak Log Portions

ftbuniversity.projectredwires.title=Assorted Lengths of Wire
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.subtitle=Make ProjectRed Wires
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.desc1=&bRed Alloy Wires&r are the most basic, acting pretty much exactly like Redstone Dust. However, it can also be placed on walls and ceilings.
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.desc2=&bInsulated Wire&r connects to Red Alloy Wire, and only transmit signals to other Insulated Wire of the same color. They do not connect to blocks that use redstone signals, like levers of lamps.
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.desc3=&bBundled Cable&r can connect to Insulated Wire, and carries their signals per color. These can also be color coded for even more compact wires.
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.desc4=&bFramed Wires&r are freestanding, and do not need to be placed on a block. You need to place non-framed Wires/Cables to send or receive a signal to them. There is a Framed version of every Wire/Cable.
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.desc5=ProjectRed uses &eForge Multipart&r, so you can put Covers etc on Wires to disguise or separate them. Framed Wires can go through Hollow parts.
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.task1=Insulated Wires
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.task2=Bundled Cables
ftbuniversity.projectredwires.task3=Framed Wires

ftbuniversity.projectredgates.title=Facts and Logic
ftbuniversity.projectredgates.subtitle=Make any logic gate
ftbuniversity.projectredgates.desc1=ProjectRed also adds &blogic gates&r, like AND, OR, NOT, etc.
ftbuniversity.projectredgates.desc2=I'm not even going to pretend to try teaching all of them. If you need them, you probably already know what they are. Their names should be pretty self-explanatory, at least for the simple ones.
ftbuniversity.projectredgates.task=Any Logic Gate

ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.title=Compact Machines
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.subtitle=Start Compact Machines
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc1=&eCompact Machines&r is a mod that adds &bCompact Machines&r, which are &6bigger on the inside&r.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc2=There are 6 tiers of Compact Machine, ranging from having 3x3x3 internally to 13x13x13.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc3=To make a Compact Machine, place 4 &bMiniaturization Field Projectors&r at a distance, &6facing the center&r, on the &6same y-level&r. For a 3x3x3 working area, place them on the center of the edges of a &69x9 square&r, 1 block above the ground.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc4=The farther away they are, the more room you have to work with. If placed correctly, they will emit a &6hologram&r of the working area in the center.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc5=To use the MFPs, &6place blocks in the working area&r according to their recipe (for instance, Redstone Dust on an Iron Block), then &6throw the catalyst item in&r (in this case, another Redstone Dust).
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.desc6=Once a Compact Machine is crafted, place it in the world. Click it with a &bPersonal Shrinking Device&r to enter it.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines1.task=Any Compact Machine

ftbuniversity.compactmachines2.title=The Quantum Zone
ftbuniversity.compactmachines2.subtitle=Enter a Compact Machine
ftbuniversity.compactmachines2.desc1=As long as the &6chunk that the Compact Machine is in is loaded&r, the interior of &6the Compact Machine is loaded&r.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines2.desc2=You can put &6Compact Machines inside of Compact Machines&r. That means you could theoretically have your entire base in several Compact Machines placed inside each other!

ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.title=Quantum Tunneling
ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.subtitle=Make a Tunnel
ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.desc1=&bTunnels&r can be placed on the walls of the Compact Machine interior to allow it to &6connect to anoutside face&r. Right-click the Tunnel to change what side it's connected to.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.desc2=When connected to an outside face, &6pipes can connect on both sides&r, so you can move RF, items, and the like from one side to the other.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.desc3=A &bRedstone Tunnel&r is required to move redstone signals through.
ftbuniversity.compactmachines3.task=Either Tunnel

ftbuniversity.mecapab.subtitle=Make an ME Capability Adaptor
ftbuniversity.mecapab.desc1=Compact Machines uses a specific function called &6capabilities&r to see if blocks should interact with Tunnels. Most other mods also use capabilities, so their pipes will automatically connect.
ftbuniversity.mecapab.desc2=However, &6AE2 does not use capabilities&r. That means, by default, you &6cannot connect ME Cable through Tunnels&r.
ftbuniversity.mecapab.desc3=The addon mod &eCapability Adapter&r adds the &bME Capability Adaptor&r, which &6carries channels using capabilities&r.
ftbuniversity.mecapab.desc4=Place a Capability Adaptor on &6both sides of the Tunnel&r, then from there connect ME Cables and such.
ftbuniversity.mecapab.desc5=In modpacks without Capability Adaptors, you can dodge this issue using the &6ME Quantum Network Bridge&r.
ftbuniversity.mecapab.task=ME Capability Adapter

ftbuniversity.agricraft1.title=AgriCraft
ftbuniversity.agricraft1.subtitle=Make Crop Sticks
ftbuniversity.agricraft1.desc1=&eAgriCraft&r is a mod that is supposed to combine IC2's crops with Forestry's bee breeding.
ftbuniversity.agricraft1.desc2=Using AgriCraft, you can get Seeds that &6grow extremely quickly&r and &6give several of its produce&r.
ftbuniversity.agricraft1.desc3=To begin, place down some &bCrop Sticks&r on the block you want to farm on. Most crops need Farmland, but some may need something else. See JEI for details.
ftbuniversity.agricraft1.desc4=Once the Crop Sticks are placed, right-click the Seeds you want to grow onto them. From there, it works pretty much like normal crops.

ftbuniversity.agricraft2.title=Crops
ftbuniversity.agricraft2.subtitle=Get some AgriCraft seeds
ftbuniversity.agricraft2.desc1=When &bcertain seeds&r are planted on Crop Sticks or scanned in a Seed Analyzer, they get some NBT tags that specify them as being AgriCraft.
ftbuniversity.agricraft2.desc2=With &bcertain other crops&r, like Carrots and Potatos, they get turned into &6new items entirely&r.
ftbuniversity.agricraft2.task1="Normal" seeds
ftbuniversity.agricraft2.task2=AgriCraft seeds

ftbuniversity.agricraft3.title=10/10/10
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.subtitle=Make a Seed Analyzer
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc1=The &bSeed Analyzer&r allows you to see the stats of the Seeds you insert into it. This also &6fills the Agricultural Journal&r if you insert it into the bottom right slot.
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc2=Crops have 3 stats:
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc3=â€¢ &6Growth&r: the speed at which it grows
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc4=â€¢ &6Yield&r: the amount of produce it gives on harvest
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc5=â€¢ &6Strength&r: its resistance to weeds
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc6=To increase these stats, &6place two Crop Sticks on the same block&r. This has a chance of mutating, based on adjacent Crop Sticks.
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc7=If they are the same crop, the new Seeds will have &6slightly increased stats&r. If you want to optimize your chances, make it a &6+ shape&r, with the Cross-Crop Sticks in the center.
ftbuniversity.agricraft3.desc8=That is, assuming it doesn't grow &cWeeds&r instead. That's bad, but extremely likely. Read the Weeds quest below for more information.

ftbuniversity.agricraft4.title=Metal Crops
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.subtitle=Make each tier of metal seeds
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.desc1=AgriCraft also adds &bseeds for most metals and gems&r. These, of course, &6can be 10/10/10'd&r.
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.desc2=For simplicity's sake, I've separated them into &6tiers&r. Tier 1 is crossbred from normal crops, Tier 2 uses Tier 1, Tier 3 uses Tier 2, etc.
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.desc3=To get these new species of seed, &6crossbreed 2 different species together&r. See the quest directly to the right for more information.
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task1=Tier 1
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task2=Tier 2
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task3=Tier 3
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task4=Tier 4
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task5=Tier 5
ftbuniversity.agricraft4.task6=Tier 6

ftbuniversity.botseeds.title=Botania Seeds
ftbuniversity.botseeds.subtitle=Get a Mystical Flower seed
ftbuniversity.botseeds.desc1=AgriCraft also has &bBotania support&r.
ftbuniversity.botseeds.desc2=They do exactly what you think they would do.
ftbuniversity.botseeds.task=Mystical Flower seeds

ftbuniversity.agriweed.title=Not Even the Fun Kind
ftbuniversity.agriweed.subtitle=Deal with Weeds
ftbuniversity.agriweed.desc1=&bWeeds&r are &cextremely annoying&r. They can &6randomly populate empty Crop Sticks&r, including Cross-Crop Sticks. This means you'll probably have to baby your crossbreeding area religiously.
ftbuniversity.agriweed.desc2=Weeds can &6spread, taking over other Crop Sticks&r, &ckilling the crops on them&r.
ftbuniversity.agriweed.desc3=Crops with &6high Strength&r have a higher resistance to Weeds.
ftbuniversity.agriweed.desc4=There's &6not really much you can do to prevent them&r. The only thing you can do is stop them from spreading.

ftbuniversity.irrigation.title=Irrigation Irritation
ftbuniversity.irrigation.subtitle=Make a Sprinkler setup
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc1=The &bSprinkler&r hydrates a &67x7 area&r below them, as well as &6occasionally bonemealing&r crops in its area. However, they require a bit of setup.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc2=First, place a &bWooden Water Tank&r. Fill it with water, by any means.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc3=Then, place a line of &bWooden Irrigation Channels&r from the Tank to the places you want to irrigate. They cannot go up or down.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc4=Finally, place the &bSprinkler&r on the underside of a Channel. It will start working whenever the Channel has water in it.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc5=Optionally, you can add a &bWooden Channel Valve&r. This prevents water from flowing through it when given a redstone signal.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.desc6=This title shamelessly taken from the guide online, credit to ShneekeyTheLost.
ftbuniversity.irrigation.task=Wooden Irrigation Channels

ftbuniversity.craftcalc.subtitle=Make a Crafting Calculator
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc1=The &bCrafting Calculator&r is an &nextremely&r useful item. You can teach it recipes, and it will &6display the base ingredients of an item&r.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc2=To start, open the Crafting Calculator, search for the item you want in JEI, and &6drag it into the top left slot&r. At the bottom, it will show the ingredients the Calculator thinks it needs. Since you haven't given it a recipe yet, it will simply show the item itself.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc3=To &6teach it a recipe&r, click the button at the top right. Here, you can add &6labels&r (which represent items, fluids, OreDict terms, and placeholders, as well as their amounts) for the inputs, outputs, as well as the block used to craft it.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc4=You can also &6Use JEI's + button&r to instantly create labels for that recipe. Additionally, dragging an item from JEI into a slot creates a label for it.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc5=At the top of this GUI, you can set the recipe's &6group&r (so you can organize your recipes), &6save&r the recipe (so it can be used), &6add label&r (which should be fairly obvious), &6clear grid&r (resets the GUI), &6edit recipe&r (if you are changing an existing recipe), and &6disambiguate&r (specify a label, in case it's too generic).
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc6=Once a recipe has been taught, go back to the Calculator's first menu. Put the label you want in the top left slot, and it will &6display the ingredients it needs in the bottom&r. You can also set the amount you want in the text box.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc.desc7=These recipes &6nest&r, meaning if you have the recipes for a Bookshelf, Planks, Books, and Paper, it will show the correct amounts of Logs, Leather, and Sugar Cane you need.

ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.title=Placeholders
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.subtitle=Learn how to use placeholders
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.desc1=Recipes only have 14 slots for input labels. This is good enough for most recipes, but not all.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.desc2=A &bplaceholder&r is a label that essentially &6represents up to 14 other labels&r. That means a recipe with 2 placeholders could actually have up to 28 inputs.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.desc3=Go into the new recipe screen, click Add Label, go to Placeholder, then give it a name. Place this in the output. Place up to 14 input labels, then save it as a recipe.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.desc4=Then in the actual item recipe that you want, instead of putting those 14 input labels, &6put the Placeholder there instead&r.
ftbuniversity.craftcalc2.desc5=Placeholders are fairly tedious to make, so I recommend &6bookmarking&r (hit A while hovering over) all the items in the main recipe, then removing them as they're added to the placeholder's recipe.

ftbuniversity.somnia.title=Perchance to Dream
ftbuniversity.somnia.subtitle=Learn about Somnia Awoken
ftbuniversity.somnia.desc1=&eSomnia Awoken&r is a mod that changes how sleeping works. Instead of basically skipping to day time, it &6speeds up time while you sleep&r.
ftbuniversity.somnia.desc2=Additionally, instead of just sleeping at night, being awake builds up &6fatigue&r, which is displayed in the bottom right corner. We've set it to only show if it's too low to sleep.
ftbuniversity.somnia.desc3=You cannot sleep while you have under 20 fatigue. Normally, having over 70 fatigue starts to give you side effects, but we've disabled that to be as unobtrusive as possible.
ftbuniversity.somnia.desc4=While sleeping, the top of the screen will show how much faster the world is moving, how much longer before you wake up (though you can force yourself to wake up whenever), and the current time of day.
ftbuniversity.somnia.desc5=If you right-click a Bed with a &bClock&r, you can &6set the time of day you want to wake up at&r.

ftbuniversity.timeinabottle.subtitle=Make Time in a Bottle
ftbuniversity.timeinabottle.desc1=&bTime in a Bottle&r is used to &6tick-accelerate blocks&r, speeding them up by a massive amount.
ftbuniversity.timeinabottle.desc2=Using the Bottle on a block &6spends time&r, which is passively collected while the Bottle is in your inventory.
ftbuniversity.timeinabottle.desc3=The first click costs 30 seconds, the second costs 60, then 120, 240, then finally 480.
ftbuniversity.timeinabottle.desc4=With each click, the speed doubles. The effect lasts 30 seconds.

ftbuniversity.buildgadget.subtitle=Make a Building Gadget
ftbuniversity.buildgadget.desc=The &bBuilding Gadget&r allows you to quickly build simple structures, like walls.
ftbuniversity.gengadget.desc1=Sneak right-click a block to set it to place that block.
ftbuniversity.gengadget.desc2=Hold the "Settings Menu" key (set it in Controls) to open a menu where you can change its settings.

ftbuniversity.exchangegad.subtitle=Make an Exchanging Gadget
ftbuniversity.exchangegad.desc=The &bExchanging Gadget&r allows you to break blocks in the world, replacing them with blocks in your inventory.

ftbuniversity.copypaste.subtitle=Make a Copy-Paste Gadget
ftbuniversity.copypaste.desc1=The &bCopy-Paste Gadget&r allows you to copy an area and place it somewhere else, without destroying the original. You can also import structures from online!
ftbuniversity.copypaste.desc2=Right-click one corner of the area you want to copy, then sneak right-click the other. 
ftbuniversity.copypaste.desc3=In its radial menu, swap to paste mode. Look at a block, and it will show a hologram of the structure, anchored on the first block you clicked before. You can anchor it and then sneak right-click to change its position manually.

ftbuniversity.destructgad.subtitle=Make a Destruction Gadget
ftbuniversity.destructgad.desc1=The &bDestruction Gadget&r allows you to void an area, destroying the blocks without dropping their items. You can undo this with a keybind.
ftbuniversity.destructgad.desc2=Sneak right-click to set the amount of blocks in each direction to break.

ftbuniversity.constpaste.title=Construction Paste
ftbuniversity.constpaste.subtitle=Get Construction Paste
ftbuniversity.constpaste.desc1=&bConstruction Paste&r can be used by Gadgets if you are out of the actual block. They will look exactly like the block, but have no special functionality themselves.
ftbuniversity.constpaste.desc2=To make Construction Paste, make a &bConstruction Block Powder&r and place it next to water. Break that to get the Paste.

ftbuniversity.pastecont.title=Paste Containers
ftbuniversity.pastecont.subtitle=Make a Paste Container
ftbuniversity.pastecont.desc1=&bPaste Containers&r can store Construction Paste more efficiently, so you don't have an entire inventory full of it.
ftbuniversity.pastecont.desc2=Any Paste you pick up while you have a Container will automatically enter it. You can also right-click the Container to insert all Paste in your inventory.

ftbuniversity.template.subtitle=Make a Template Manager
ftbuniversity.template.desc1=The &bTemplate Manager&r allows you to move Copy-Paste Gadget structures to/from items, so you can save them for later. It also allows you to get structures from online.
ftbuniversity.template.desc2=Place the Gadget in the left slot and Paper (or a Template) in the right.
ftbuniversity.template.desc3=Click &6Save&r to move the Gadget's structure to the Paper, saving it as a Template.
ftbuniversity.template.desc4=Click &6Load&r to move the Template's structure to the Gadget, overwriting whatever's already there.
ftbuniversity.template.desc5=Click &6Copy&r to copy the Gadget's structure as text, putting it into your computer's clipboard, allowing you to paste it somewhere else with control-v (not just in-game, any text window).
ftbuniversity.template.desc6=Click &6Paste&r to paste your clipboard into the Gadget. This obviously only works if your clipboard has a functional structure's text copied to it.
ftbuniversity.template.desc7=This is where online structures are saved. You can find them on Direwolf20's Discord server, or on reddit.com/r/9x9.

ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.title=Spooky Ghost Energy
ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.subtitle=Make a Spectre energy setup
ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.desc1=RF that is piped into the &bSpectre Energy Injector&r is inserted into its owner's &6spectre energy buffer&r, which can hold up to &61,000,000 RF&r.
ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.desc2=&bSpectre Chargers&r will use RF from the player's buffer to charge items in their inventory. &bSpectre Coils&r do the same, but charge the block they are placed on.
ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.task1=Spectre Chargers
ftbuniversity.spectreenergy.task2=Spectre Coils

##Creative
ftbuniversity.creativechap.title=Endgame

ftbuniversity.ecg.subtitle=Make the Extended Crafting Guide
ftbuniversity.ecg.desc1=Many expert mode modpacks end with you &6crafting Creative-only items&r, giving you infinite fluids, items, fluids, etc. So, we've done the same here!
ftbuniversity.ecg.desc2=These (along with the items from &eAvaritia&r) will be some of the &6final things you do&r in the modpack, and they will you require you &6go through pretty much every mod&r in the pack.
ftbuniversity.ecg.desc3=These recipes all use &eExtended Crafting&r, which allows for crafting grids above 3x3. The &bExtended Crafting Guide&r will explain how it works.

ftbuniversity.ectables.title=Bigger Crafting
ftbuniversity.ectables.subtitle=Make a bigger Crafting Table
ftbuniversity.ectables.desc1=These &bCrafting Tables&r have increasingly &6larger grid sizes&r, from 3x3 to 9x9.
ftbuniversity.ectables.desc2=Higher tier Tables &ncan&r craft recipes from previous tiers, though JEI will not be able to show you where things go.
ftbuniversity.ectables.task=Crafting Tables

ftbuniversity.singularities.title=Singularities
ftbuniversity.singularities.subtitle=Make a Quantum Compressor
ftbuniversity.singularities.desc1=The &bQuantum Compressor&r takes several million RF, &6converting 10k of certain items into a Singularity&r, which is used to craft &6The Ultimate Singularity&r, which is an end-game crafting component.
ftbuniversity.singularities.desc2=Only certain materials have Singularities. Additionally, you have to have an &6Ultimate Catalyst&r in the left slot for it to work.

ftbuniversity.combocraft.title=Combination Crafting
ftbuniversity.combocraft.subtitle=Make a combination crafting setup
ftbuniversity.combocraft.desc1=The &bCrafting Core&r works with any &bPedestals&r in a &67x7 area&r, using items on them in recipes.
ftbuniversity.combocraft.desc2=Right-clicking the &6top&r of the Core will &6place an item on it&r; right-clicking the &6side&r will &6open its GUI&r.

ftbuniversity.neutronium.title=This is Not My Aesthetic
ftbuniversity.neutronium.subtitle=Make a Neutron Collector
ftbuniversity.neutronium.desc1=Every 7111 ticks, the &bNeutron Collector&r generates 1 &6Pile of Neutrons&r.
ftbuniversity.neutronium.desc2=You're going to &6need a &llot&r of Neutronium, so you may want to make a lot of these.
ftbuniversity.neutronium.desc3=The addon &eDense Neutron Collectors&r adds 3 more tiers, which generate Nuggets, Ingots, and Blocks, in order.
ftbuniversity.neutronium.task=Neutron Collectors

ftbuniversity.autoint.subtitle=Make an Automation Interface
ftbuniversity.autoint.desc1=The &bAutomation Interface&r allows you to automate Extended Crafting recipes.
ftbuniversity.autoint.desc2=&6Place it on top&r of an Advanced+ Crafting Table &6&nthat already has a valid recipe in it&r, and provide it power.
ftbuniversity.autoint.desc3=In the AI's GUI, click &6Save Recipe&r. Now, any items piped into it will try to be inserted into the correct slots of the Crafting Table.
ftbuniversity.autoint.desc4=When the Table is able to craft, it will output the item to the AI's right slot.

ftbuniversity.avafoods.title=Kinda Useless Without SaturationOverflow
ftbuniversity.avafoods.subtitle=Make the Avaritia foods
ftbuniversity.avafoods.desc1=The &bUltimate Stew&r and &bUltimate Meatballs&r need &opretty much&r every food. The Stew is for plant-foods, and the Meatballs are for meat-foods.
ftbuniversity.avafoods.desc2=They both fully fill you up and provide 400 saturation. Normally, saturation is capped at 20, but we have the mod &eSaturationOverflow&r that uncaps it, so a single one of these can last you a &owhile&r.

ftbuniversity.avaaxe.title=Why Is This Not Animated?
ftbuniversity.avaaxe.subtitle=Make Nature's Ruin
ftbuniversity.avaaxe.desc1=&bNature's Ruin&r has infinite durability.
ftbuniversity.avaaxe.desc2=Additionally, sneak right-clicking will &6break all plant blocks in a 13x13x13 cube&r, dropping a Matter Cluster on you with their drops. &cThis includes Planks and Chests.&r It is &nall&r plant/wooden blocks.

ftbuniversity.avapick.title=Terra Shatter SSSSSS Rank
ftbuniversity.avapick.subtitle=Make the World Breaker
ftbuniversity.avapick.desc1=&bWorld Breaker&r has infinite durability and is enchanted with Fortune X from the start. It also has, by far, the fastest mining rate of any pickaxe.
ftbuniversity.avapick.desc2=Sneak right-clicking will toggle &6hammer mode&r, which &6mines a 16x16x16 cube&r. It &cmines all stone, dirt, and metallic blocks, including your base&r. Be very careful using it.

ftbuniversity.avasword1.title=/kill
ftbuniversity.avasword1.subtitle=Make the Sword of the Cosmos
ftbuniversity.avasword1.desc1=The &bSword of the Cosmos&r has infinite durability, and &6kills everything instantly&r.
ftbuniversity.avasword1.desc2=It does this by setting the entity's health to 0 directly, rather than doing damage. That means it kills &neverything&r. All monsters, all bosses, all &oplayers&r even those in creative!

ftbuniversity.avaarmor.title=Fancy Pants
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.subtitle=Make a set of Infinity armor
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.desc1=The &bInfinity Helmet&r has infinite durability, keeps the player fed, provides air, and gives night vision.
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.desc2=The &bInfinity Breastplate&r has infinite durability, removes all negative potion effects, and allows creative flight.
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.desc3=The &bInfinity Leggings&r have infinite durability and provides fire resistance.
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.desc4=The &bInfinity Boots&r have infinite durability, provide a jump boost, and massively increase your travel speed.
ftbuniversity.avaarmor.desc5=Wearing the full set makes you &6completely resistant to all damage from all sources&r, including void damage and the /kill command.

ftbuniversity.avabow.title=Spray and Pray
ftbuniversity.avabow.subtitle=Make the Longbow of the Heavens
ftbuniversity.avabow.desc1=The &bLongbow of the Heavens&r has infinite durability. Though it requires an arrow be in your inventory, it won't actually use it.
ftbuniversity.avabow.desc2=Holding down right-click will automatically fire arrows that deal 10 hearts of damage. If the arrow misses, it will summon 10 more.

ftbuniversity.avashov.title=&lExcavator&r
ftbuniversity.avashov.subtitle=Make Planet Eater
ftbuniversity.avashov.desc1=&bPlanet Eater&r has infinite durability and instantly digs dirt-based blocks.
ftbuniversity.avashov.desc2=Sneak right-clicking will toggle &6destroyer mode&r, which &6digs all dirt-based blocks in a 16x16x16 area&r, dropping them as a Matter Cluster on top of you.

ftbuniversity.avahoe.title=Hoe're You Doing?
ftbuniversity.avahoe.subtitle=Make the Hoe of the Green Earth
ftbuniversity.avahoe.desc1=The &bHoe of the Green Earth&r has infinite durability.
ftbuniversity.avahoe.desc2=Right-clicking dirt will create a 9x9 square of Farmland centered on that block, replacing any Tall Grass (or similar) blocks in the way.

ftbuniversity.avasword2.title=Surprisingly Cheap for Avaritia
ftbuniversity.avasword2.subtitle=Make the Skullfire Sword
ftbuniversity.avasword2.desc=The &bSkullfire Forge&r will make Skeletons drop Wither Skeleton Skulls.

ftbuniversity.mowtal.subtitle=Make the Earth Talisman
ftbuniversity.mowtal.desc1=The &bEarth Talisman&r is an item that is planned to be dropped by a future mob.
ftbuniversity.mowtal.desc2=Its tooltip says basically everything you need to know about it.

ftbuniversity.creativestorage.title=Unlimited Storage
ftbuniversity.creativestorage.subtitle=Make either infinite capacity upgrade
ftbuniversity.creativestorage.desc1=The &bCreative Storage Upgrade&r and &bInfinite Capacity&r upgrade can be installed to either a Drawer or Barrel, and will &6allow for a near-unlimited amount of items to be stored in it&r.
ftbuniversity.creativestorage.desc2=This isn't extremely powerful, so it's relatively cheap as far as creative items go.
ftbuniversity.creativestorage.task=Infinite capacity upgrades

ftbuniversity.creativepaste.subtitle=Make a Creative Paste Container
ftbuniversity.creativepaste.desc=The &bCreative Paste Container&r provides &6unlimited Paste for Building Gadgets&r.

ftbuniversity.creativecheese.subtitle=Make Creative Cheese
ftbuniversity.creativecheese.desc=&bCreative Cheese&r can &6instantly tame rats&r.

ftbuniversity.shardwand.subtitle=Make the Shard Wand
ftbuniversity.shardwand.desc=Sneak right-clicking any RFTools machine with the &bShard Wand&r will instantly &6maximize its infusion level&r.

ftbuniversity.creativespike.subtitle=Make the Creative Spike
ftbuniversity.creativespike.desc=The &bCreative Spike&r will &6instantly kill any mob or player that touches it&r. Mobs will drop experience and player-only loot.

ftbuniversity.creativewct.subtitle=Make the Creative Wireless Crafting Terminal
ftbuniversity.creativewct.desc=The &bCreative Wireless Crafting Terminal&r works exactly like a regular WCT, but has &6infinite range and RF storage&r.

ftbuniversity.creativecombine.subtitle=Make the Rat Upgrade: Combined(Creative)
ftbuniversity.creativecombine.desc=The &bRat Upgrade: Combined(Creative)&r can &6store up to 27 upgrades&r inside of it, and then can be given to a Rat to &6apply them all&r.

ftbuniversity.ratcreative.subtitle=Make the Rat Upgrade: Creative
ftbuniversity.ratcreative.desc=The &bRat Upgrade: Creative&r makes it so Rats &6can only take damage from their owner&r.

ftbuniversity.ic2debug.subtitle=Make the Debug Item
ftbuniversity.ic2debug.desc=The &bDebug Item&r can be inserted into the charging slot of any machine to &6infinitely supply it with EU&r.

ftbuniversity.cheatthaum.subtitle=Make the Cheater's Thaumonomicon
ftbuniversity.cheatthaum.desc=The &bCheater's Thaumonomicon&r will &6instantly complete all research&r.

ftbuniversity.fluxsponge.subtitle=Make a Flux Sponge
ftbuniversity.fluxsponge.desc1=The &bFlux Sponge&r will &6drain all flux in a 9x9 chunk area&r.
ftbuniversity.fluxsponge.desc2=Using while sneaking will make it also &6remove flux rifts&r.

ftbuniversity.creativedagger.subtitle=Make a Creative Sacrificial Dagger
ftbuniversity.creativedagger.desc=The &bCreative Sacrificial Dagger&r can &6instantly fill an Altar&r by sneak right-clicking it.

ftbuniversity.creativecrystal.subtitle=Make a Creative Activation Crystal
ftbuniversity.creativecrystal.desc=The &bCreative Activation Crystal&r will &6activate any ritual&r.

ftbuniversity.creativedrum.subtitle=Make a Creative Drum
ftbuniversity.creativedrum.desc1=The &bCreative Drum&r can be crafted with any bucket to fill it, then &6an infinite amount of that fluid can be piped out&r.
ftbuniversity.creativedrum.desc2=Craft the Drum by itself to reset it to normal.

ftbuniversity.ic2creative.subtitle=Make a Creative Generator
ftbuniversity.ic2creative.desc1=The &bCreative Generator&r &6generates 320 EU/t for free&r.
ftbuniversity.ic2creative.desc2=While normally this would destroy LV machines, this does not.

ftbuniversity.creativemill.subtitle=Make a Creative Mill
ftbuniversity.creativemill.desc=The &bCreative Mill&r &6generates 10,000 GP for free&r.

ftbuniversity.creativeenergy.subtitle=Make a Creative Energy Source
ftbuniversity.creativeenergy.desc1=The &bCreative Energy Source&r &6generates an infinte amount of RF at maximum speed&r on every side.
ftbuniversity.creativeenergy.desc2=It can also be crafted into any of the other creative generators from other mods.
ftbuniversity.creativeenergy.task=All creative energy generators

ftbuniversity.creativecompress.subtitle=Make the Creative Compressor
ftbuniversity.creativecompress.desc=The &bCreative Compressor&r will &6set the pressure of its system to the level you decide&r, from -1 to 30 bar.

ftbuniversity.creativepool.subtitle=Make the Everlasting Guilty Pool
ftbuniversity.creativepool.desc=The &bEverlasting Guilty Pool&r has an &6unlimited amount of mana&r. It otherwise functions identically to a normal Mana Pool.

ftbuniversity.creativegas.subtitle=Make a Creative Gas Tank
ftbuniversity.creativegas.desc1=The &bCreative Gas Tank&r &6supplies an infinite amount of the specified gas&r.
ftbuniversity.creativegas.desc2=Craft it with full Basic Gas Tank to set what gas it supplies.

ftbuniversity.creativeharvest.subtitle=Make a Creative Harvest
ftbuniversity.creativeharvest.desc1=You can craft a &bCreative Harvest&r with any block. Place it, then you can &6infinitely mine it, getting that block's drop forever&r.
ftbuniversity.creativeharvest.desc2=You cannot craft it with anything that has NBT (chests, machines, etc). &cDo not try&r, in case we missed any, as &cit will crash your game&r.
ftbuniversity.creativeharvest.desc3=To pick it up, sneak right-click it with an empty hand.

ftbuniversity.creativetablet.subtitle=Make a Creative Mana Tablet
ftbuniversity.creativetablet.desc=The &bCreative Mana Tablet&r provides &6unlimited mana in your inventory&r.

ftbuniversity.creativevending.title=Item Duplication
ftbuniversity.creativevending.subtitle=Make either item duplication upgrade
ftbuniversity.creativevending.desc1=The &bCreative Vending Upgrade&r and &bCreative Barrel&r upgrade can be applied to Drawers or Barrels, and will &6allow for an infinite amount of their item to be piped out without emptying&r.
ftbuniversity.creativevending.desc2=This is likely to be the last item you make in the game.
ftbuniversity.creativevending.task=Item duplication upgrades

